UCD.name: DATA ELEMENT ERROR INDICATION
UCD.function: To identify an erroneous stand-alone, composite or component data element, and to identify the nature of the error.

UCF.name: GROUP RESPONSE
UCF.function: To identify a group in the subject interchange and to indicate acknowledgement or rejection (action taken) of the UNG and UNE segments, and to identify any error related to these segments. It can also identify errors related to the USA, USC, USD, USH, USR, UST, or USU security segments when they appear at the group level. Depending on the action code, it may also indicate the action taken on the messages and packages within that group.

UCI.name: INTERCHANGE RESPONSE
UCI.function: To identify the subject interchange, to indicate interchange receipt, to indicate acknowledgement or rejection (action taken) of the UNA, UNB and UNZ segments, and to identify any error related to these segments. It can also identify errors related to the USA, USC, USD, USH, USR, UST, or USU security segments when they appear at the interchange level. Depending on the action code, it may also indicate the action taken on the groups, messages, and packages within that interchange.

UCM.name: MESSAGE/PACKAGE RESPONSE
UCM.function: To identify a message or package in the subject interchange, and to indicate that message's or package's acknowledgement or rejection (action taken), and to identify any error related to the UNH, UNT, UNO, and UNP segments. It can also identify errors related to the USA, USC, USD, USH, USR, UST, or USU security segments when they appear at the message or package level.

UCS.name: SEGMENT ERROR INDICATION
UCS.function: To identify either a segment containing an error or a missing segment, and to identify any error related to the complete segment.

UGH.name: ANTI-COLLISION SEGMENT GROUP HEADER
UGH.function: To head, identify and specify an anti-collision segment group.

UGT.name: ANTI-COLLISION SEGMENT GROUP TRAILER
UGT.function: To end and check the completeness of an anti-collision segment group.

UIB.name: INTERACTIVE INTERCHANGE HEADER
UIB.function: To head and identify an interchange.

UIH.function: To head, identify and specify a message.

UIR.name: INTERACTIVE STATUS
UIR.function: To report the status of the dialogue.

UIT.name: INTERACTIVE MESSAGE TRAILER
UIT.function: To end and check the completeness of a message.

0074.name: NUMBER OF SEGMENTS IN A MESSAGE

UIZ.name: INTERACTIVE INTERCHANGE TRAILER
UIZ.function: To end and check the completeness of an interchange.

UNE.name: GROUP TRAILER
UNE.function: To end and check the completeness of a group.

UNG.name: GROUP HEADER
UNG.function: To head, identify and specify a group of messages and/or packages, which may be used for internal routing and which may contain one or more message types and/or packages.

UNH.name: MESSAGE HEADER
UNH.function: To head, identify and specify a message.

UNO.name: OBJECT HEADER

UNP.function: To end and check the completeness of an object.

UNS.name: SECTION CONTROL

UNT.function: To end and check the completeness of a message.

UNZ.function: To end and check the completeness of an interchange.

USA.name: SECURITY ALGORITHM
USA.function: To identify a security algorithm, the technical usage made of it, and to contain the technical parameters required.

USB.name: SECURED DATA IDENTIFICATION
USB.function: To contain details related to the AUTACK.

USC.name: CERTIFICATE
USC.function: To convey the public key and the credentials of its owner.

USD.name: DATA ENCRYPTION HEADER
USD.function: To specify size (i.e. length of data in octets of bits) of encrypted data following the segment terminator of this segment.

0556.name: LENGTH OF DATA IN OCTETS OF BITS

USE.name: SECURITY MESSAGE RELATION
USE.function: To specify the relation to earlier security messages, such as response to a particular request, or request for a particular answer.

USF.name: KEY MANAGEMENT FUNCTION
USF.function: To specify the type of key management function and the status of a corresponding key or certificate.

USH.name: SECURITY HEADER
USH.function: To specify a security mechanism applied to a EDIFACT structure (i.e.: either message/package, group or interchange).

USL.name: SECURITY LIST STATUS
USL.function: To specify the status of security objects, such as keys or certificates to be delivered in a list, and the corresponding list parameters.

USR.name: SECURITY RESULT
USR.function: To contain the result of the security mechanisms.

UST.name: SECURITY TRAILER
UST.function: To establish a link between security header and security trailer segment groups.

USU.name: DATA ENCRYPTION TRAILER
USU.function: To provide a trailer for the encrypted data.

0556.name: LENGTH OF DATA IN OCTETS OF BITS

USX.name: SECURITY REFERENCES
USX.function: To refer to the secured EDIFACT structure and its associated date and time.

USY.name: SECURITY ON REFERENCES
USY.function: To identify the applicable header, and to contain the security result and/or to indicate the possible cause of security rejection for the referred value.

0096.name: Segment position in message body
0096.desc: The numerical count position of a specific segment that is within the actual received message body. The numbering starts with, and includes, the UNH segment as segment number 1. To identify a segment that contains an error, this is the numerical count position of that segment. To report that a segment is missing, this is the numerical count position of the last segment that was processed before the position where the missing segment was expected to be. A missing segment group is denoted by identifying the first segment in the group as missing.

0098.name: Erroneous data element position in segment
0098.desc: The numerical count position of the stand-alone or composite data element in error. The segment code and each following stand-alone or composite data element defined in the segment description shall cause the count to be incremented. The segment tag has position number 1.

0104.name: Erroneous component data element position
0104.desc: The numerical count position of the component data element in error. Each component data element position defined in the composite data element description shall cause the count to be incremented. The count starts at 1.

0133.name: Character encoding, coded

0136.name: Erroneous data element occurrence
0136.desc: The numerical occurrence of the repeating stand-alone or composite data element in error. Each occurrence (as indicated by the repetition separator) shall cause the count to be incremented. The count starts at 1.

0138.name: Security segment position
0138.desc: The numerical count position of a specific security segment that is within the actual received security header/trailer segment group pair, identified by its security reference number. The numbering starts with, and includes, the USH segment as segment number 1. To identify a security segment that contains an error, this is the numerical count position of that security segment. To report that a security segment is missing, this is the numerical count position of the last security segment that was processed before the position where the missing security segment was expected to be. A missing security segment group is denoted by identifying the first segment in the security segment group as missing.

496.desc: Single step declaration, in accordance with the WCO Customs Data Model, to Customs by which goods are declared for Customs import procedure based on the 1999 Kyoto Convention.

497.name: WCO first step of two-step import declaration
497.desc: First part of a simplified declaration, in accordance with the WCO Customs Data Model, to Customs by which goods are declared for Customs import procedure based on the 1999 Kyoto Convention.

498.name: WCO second step of two-step import declaration
498.desc: Second part of a simplified declaration, in accordance with the WCO Customs Data Model, to Customs by which goods are declared for Customs import procedure based on the 1999 Kyoto Convention.

499.name: Previous transport document
499.desc: Identification of the previous transport document.

520.name: Insurance certificate
520.desc: Document/message issued to the insured certifying that insurance has been effected and that a policy has been issued. Such a certificate for a particular cargo is primarily used when good are insured under the terms of a floating or an open policy; at the request of the insured it can be exchanged for a policy.

521.name: Special requirements permit related to the transport of cargo
521.desc: A permit related to a transport document granting the transport of cargo under the conditions as specifically required.

522.name: Dangerous Goods Notification for Tanker vessel
522.desc: Dangerous Goods Notification for a vessel carrying liquid cargo in bulk.

523.name: Dangerous Goods Notification for non-tanker vessel
523.desc: Dangerous Goods Notification for a vessel carrying cargo other than bulk liquid cargo.

524.name: WCO Conveyance Arrival Report
524.desc: Declaration, in accordance with the WCO Customs Data Model, to Customs regarding the conveyance arriving in a Customs territory.

525.name: WCO Conveyance Departure Report
525.desc: Declaration, in accordance with the WCO Customs Data Model, to Customs regarding the conveyance departing a Customs territory.

526.name: Accounting voucher
526.desc: A document/message justifying an accounting entry.

527.name: Self billed debit note
527.desc: A document which indicates that the customer is claiming debit in a self billing environment.

528.name: Military Identification Card
528.desc: The official document used for military personnel on travel orders, substituting a passport.

529.name: Re-Entry Permit
529.desc: A permit to re-enter a country.

530.name: Insurance policy
530.desc: Document/message issued by the insurer evidencing an agreement to insure and containing the conditions of the agreement concluded whereby the insurer undertakes for a specific fee to indemnify the insured for the losses arising out of the perils and accidents specified in the contract.

531.name: Refugee Permit
531.desc: Document identifying a refugee recognized by a country.

532.name: ForwarderÆs credit note
532.desc: Document/message for providing credit information to the relevant party.

533.name: Original accounting voucher
533.desc: To indicate that the document/message justifying an accounting entry is original.

534.name: Copy accounting voucher
534.desc: To indicate that the document/message justifying an accounting entry is a copy.

535.name: Pro-forma accounting voucher
535.desc: To indicate that the document/message justifying an accounting entry is pro-forma.

536.name: International Ship Security Certificate
536.desc: A certificate on ship security issued based on the International code for the Security of Ships and of Port facilities (ISPS code).

537.name: Interim International Ship Security Certificate
537.desc: An interim certificate on ship security issued basis under the International code for the Security of Ships and of Port facilities (ISPS code).

538.name: Good Manufacturing Practice (GMP) Certificate
538.desc: Certificate that guarantees quality manufacturing and processing of food products, medications, cosmetics, etc.

539.name: Framework Agreement
539.desc: An agreement between one or more contracting authorities and one or more economic operators, the purpose of which is to establish the terms governing contracts to be awarded during a given period, in particular with regard to price and, where appropriate, the quantity envisaged.

550.name: Insurance declaration sheet (bordereau)
550.desc: A document/message used when an insured reports to his insurer details of individual shipments which are covered by an insurance contract - an open cover or a floating policy - between the parties.

551.name: Transport capacity offer
551.desc: Offering of capacity for the transport of goods for a date and a route.

552.name: Ship Security Plan
552.desc: Ship Security Plan (SSP) is a document prepared in terms of the ISPS Code to contribute to the prevention of illegal acts against the ship and its crew.

553.name: ForwarderÆs invoice discrepancy report
553.desc: Document/message reporting invoice discrepancies indentified by the forwarder.

554.name: Storage capacity offer
554.desc: Offering of capacity to store goods.

575.name: Insurer's invoice
575.desc: Document/message issued by an insurer specifying the cost of an insurance which has been effected and claiming payment therefore.

576.name: Storage capacity request
576.desc: Request for capacity to store goods.

577.name: Transport capacity request
577.desc: Request for capacity for the transport of goods for a date and a route.

578.name: EU Customs declaration for External Community Transit (T1)
578.desc: Customs declaration for goods under the external Community/common transit procedure. This applies to "non-Community goods" ("T1" under EU legislation and EC- EFTA "Transit Convention").

579.name: EU Customs declaration for internal Community Transit (T2)
579.desc: Customs declaration for goods under the internal Community/common transit procedure. This applies to "Community goods" ("T2" under EU legislation and EC-EFTA "Transit Convention").

580.name: Cover note
580.desc: Document/message issued by an insurer (insurance broker, agent, etc.) to notify the insured that his insurance have been carried out.

581.name: EU Customs declaration for non-fiscal area internal Community Transit (T2F)
581.desc: Declaration for goods under the internal Community transit procedure in the context of trade between the "VAT" territory of EU Member States and EU territories where the VAT rules do not apply, such as Canary islands, some French overseas territories, the Channel islands and the Aaland islands, and between those territories. ("T2F" under EU Legislation).

582.name: EU Customs declaration for internal transit to San Marino (T2SM)
582.desc: Customs declaration for goods under the internal Community transit procedure between the Community and San Marino. ("T2SM" under EU Legislation).

583.name: EU Customs declaration for mixed consignments (T)
583.desc: Customs declaration for goods under the Community/common transit procedure for mixed consignments (i.e. consignments that comprise goods of different statuses, like "T1" and "T2") ("T" under EU Legislation).

584.name: EU Document for establishing the Community status of goods (T2L)
584.desc: Form establishing the Community status of goods ("T2L" under EU Legislation).

585.name: EU Document for establishing the Community status of goods for certain fiscal purposes (T2LF)
585.desc: Form establishing the Community status of goods in the context of trade between the "VAT" territory of EU Member States and EU territories where the VAT rules do not apply, such as Canary islands, some French overseas territories, the Channel islands and the Aaland islands, and between those territories ("T2LF" under EU Legislation).

586.name: Document for establishing the Customs Status of goods for San Marino (T2LSM)
586.desc: Form establishing the Community status of goods ("T2L" under European Legislation) in the context of trade between the EU and San Marino. ("T2LSM" under EU Legislation).

587.name: Customs declaration for TIR Carnet goods
587.desc: A Customs declaration in which goods move under cover of TIR Carnets.

588.name: Transport Means Security Report
588.desc: A document reporting the security status and related information of a means of transport.

589.name: Halal Slaughtering Certificate
589.desc: A certificate verifying that meat has been produced from slaughter in accordance with Islamic laws and practices.

610.name: Forwarding instructions
610.desc: Document/message issued to a freight forwarder, giving instructions regarding the action to be taken by the forwarder for the forwarding of goods described therein.

621.name: Forwarder's advice to import agent
621.desc: Document/message issued by a freight forwarder in an exporting country advising his counterpart in an importing country about the forwarding of goods described therein.

622.name: Forwarder's advice to exporter
622.desc: Document/message issued by a freight forwarder informing an exporter of the action taken in fulfillment of instructions received.

623.name: Forwarder's invoice
623.desc: Invoice issued by a freight forwarder specifying services rendered and costs incurred and claiming payment therefore.

624.name: Forwarder's certificate of receipt
624.desc: Non-negotiable document issued by a forwarder to certify that he has assumed control of a specified consignment, with irrevocable instructions to send it to the consignee indicated in the document or to hold it at his disposal. E.g. FIATA-FCR.

625.name: Heat Treatment Certificate
625.desc: A certificate verifying the heat treatment of the product is in conformance with international standards to ensure the productÆs healthiness and/or shows the mode of heat treatment indicating the temperature and the amount of time the product or raw material used in the product was treated (such as milk).

626.name: Convention on International Trade in Endangered Species of Wild Fauna and Flora (CITES) Certificate
626.desc: A certificate used in the trade of endangered species in accordance with the CITES convention.

627.name: Free Sale Certificate in the Country of Origin
627.desc: A certificate confirming that a specified product is free for sale in the country of origin.

628.name: Transit license
628.desc: Document/message issued by the competent body in accordance with transit regulations in force, by which authorization is granted to a party to move articles under customs procedure.

629.name: Veterinary quarantine certificate
629.desc: A certification that livestock or animal products, that are either imported or entering free zones, are kept under health supervision for a time period determined by veterinary quarantine instructions.

630.name: Shipping note
630.desc: (1123) Document/message provided by the shipper or his agent to the carrier, multimodal transport operator, terminal or other receiving authority, giving information about export consignments offered for transport, and providing for the necessary receipts and declarations of liability. Sometimes a multipurpose cargo handling document also fulfilling the functions of document 632, 633, 650 and 655.

631.name: Forwarder's warehouse receipt
631.desc: Document/message issued by a forwarder acting as Warehouse Keeper acknowledging receipt of goods placed in a warehouse, and stating or referring to the conditions which govern the warehousing and the release of goods. The document contains detailed provisions regarding the rights of holders-by-endorsement, transfer of ownership, etc. E.g. FIATA-FWR.

632.name: Goods receipt
632.desc: Document/message to acknowledge the receipt of goods and in addition may indicate receiving conditions.

633.name: Port charges documents
633.desc: Documents/messages specifying services rendered, storage and handling costs, demurrage and other charges due to the owner of goods described therein.

634.name: Certified list of ingredients
634.desc: A document legalized from a competent authority that shows the components of the product (food additive, detergent, disinfectant and sanitizer).

635.name: Warehouse warrant
635.desc: Negotiable receipt document, issued by a Warehouse Keeper to a person placing goods in a warehouse and conferring title to the goods stored.

636.name: Health certificate
636.desc: A document legalized from a competent authority that shows that the product has been tested microbiologically and is free from any pathogens and fit for human consumption and/or declares that the product is in compliance with sanitary and phytosanitary measures.

637.name: Food grade certificate
637.desc: A document that shows that the product (food additive, detergent, disinfectant and sanitizer) is suitable to be used in the food industry.

638.name: Certificate of suitability for transport of grains and legumes
638.desc: Certificate of inspection for the vessel stating its readiness and suitability for transporting grains and legumes.

639.name: Certificate of refrigerated transport equipment inspection
639.desc: Inspection document shows that the container, the cooling devices and measured temperature is in good working condition.

640.name: Delivery order
640.desc: Document/message issued by a party entitled to authorize the release of goods specified therein to a named consignee, to be retained by the custodian of the goods.

641.name: Thermographic reading report
641.desc: A report of temperature readings over a period.

642.name: Certificate of food item transport readiness
642.desc: A certificate to verify readiness of a transport or transport area such as a reservoir or hold to transport food items.

643.name: Food packaging contact certificate
643.desc: A document legalized from a competent authority that shows that the food packaging product is safe to come into contact with food.

644.name: Packaging material composition report
644.desc: A document that shows the main structure that composes the packaging material.

645.name: Export price certificate
645.desc: A certification executed by the competent authority from country of exportation stating the export price of the goods.

646.name: Public price certificate
646.desc: A certification executed by the competent authority from country of production stating the price of the goods to the general public.

647.name: Drug shelf life study report
647.desc: A document containing results from the study which determines the shelf life, namely the time period of storage at a specified condition within which a drug substance or drug product still meets its established specifications; its identity, strength, quality and purity.

648.name: Certificate of compliance with standards of the World Organization for Animal Health (OIE)
648.desc: A certification that the products have been treated in a way consistent with the standards set by the World Organization for Animal Health (OIE).

649.name: Production facility license
649.desc: A license granted by a competent authority to a production facility for manufacturing specific products.

650.name: Handling order
650.desc: Document/message issued by a cargo handling organization (port administration, terminal operator, etc.) for the removal or other handling of goods under their care.

651.name: Manufacturing license
651.desc: A license granted by a competent authority to a manufacturer for production of specific products.

652.name: Low risk country formal letter
652.desc: An official letter issued by an import authority granted to the importer of goods from a low risk country which allows the importer to place its products in the local market with certain favorable considerations.

654.name: Declaration for radioactive material
654.desc: A declaration to be presented to the competent authority when radioactive material moves cross-border.

655.name: Gate pass
655.desc: Document/message authorizing goods specified therein to be brought out of a fenced-in port or terminal area.

656.name: Resale information
656.desc: Document/message providing information on a resale.

657.name: Phytosanitary Re-export Certificate
657.desc: A message/document consistent with the model for re- export phytosanitary certificates of the IPPC, attesting that a consignment meets phytosanitary import requirements.

658.name: Bayplan/stowage plan, full
658.desc: A full bayplan containing all occupied and/or blocked stowage locations.

659.name: Bayplan/stowage plan, partial
659.desc: A partial bayplan. containing only a selected part of the available stowage locations.

700.name: Waybill
700.desc: Non-negotiable document evidencing the contract for the transport of cargo.

701.name: Universal (multipurpose) transport document
701.desc: Document/message evidencing a contract of carriage covering the movement of goods by any mode of transport, or combination of modes, for national as well as international transport, under any applicable international convention or national law and under the conditions of carriage of any carrier or transport operator undertaking or arranging the transport referred to in the document.

702.name: Goods receipt, carriage
702.desc: Document/message issued by a carrier or a carrier's agent, acknowledging receipt for carriage of goods specified therein on conditions stated or referred to in the document, enabling the carrier to issue a transport document.

703.name: House waybill
703.desc: The document made out by an agent/consolidator which evidences the contract between the shipper and the agent/consolidator for the arrangement of carriage of goods.

704.name: Master bill of lading
704.desc: A bill of lading issued by the master of a vessel (in actuality the owner or charterer of the vessel). It could cover a number of house bills.

705.name: Bill of lading
705.desc: Negotiable document/message which evidences a contract of carriage by sea and the taking over or loading of goods by carrier, and by which carrier undertakes to deliver goods against surrender of the document. A provision in the document that goods are to be delivered to the order of a named person, or to order, or to bearer, constitutes such an undertaking.

706.name: Bill of lading original
706.desc: The original of the bill of lading issued by a transport company. When issued by the maritime industry it could signify ownership of the cargo.

707.name: Bill of lading copy
707.desc: A copy of the bill of lading issued by a transport company.

708.name: Empty container bill
708.desc: Bill of lading indicating an empty container.

709.name: Tanker bill of lading
709.desc: Document which evidences a transport of liquid bulk cargo.

710.name: Sea waybill
710.desc: Non-negotiable document which evidences a contract for the carriage of goods by sea and the taking over of the goods by the carrier, and by which the carrier undertakes to deliver the goods to the consignee named in the document.

711.name: Inland waterway bill of lading
711.desc: Negotiable transport document made out to a named person, to order or to bearer, signed by the carrier and handed to the sender after receipt of the goods.

712.name: Non-negotiable maritime transport document (generic)
712.desc: Non-negotiable document which evidences a contract for the carriage of goods by sea and the taking over or loading of the goods by the carrier, and by which the carrier undertakes to deliver the goods to the consignee named in the document. E.g. Sea waybill. Remark: Synonymous with "straight" or "non-negotiable Bill of lading" used in certain countries, e.g. Canada.

713.name: Mate's receipt
713.desc: Document/message issued by a ship's officer to acknowledge that a specified consignment has been received on board a vessel, and the apparent condition of the goods; enabling the carrier to issue a Bill of lading.

714.name: House bill of lading
714.desc: The bill of lading issued not by the carrier but by the freight forwarder/consolidator known by the carrier.

715.name: Letter of indemnity for non-surrender of bill of lading
715.desc: Document/message issued by a commercial party or a bank of an insurance company accepting responsibility to the beneficiary of the indemnity in accordance with the terms thereof.

716.name: Forwarder's bill of lading
716.desc: Non-negotiable document issued by a freight forwarder evidencing a contract for the carriage of goods by sea and the taking over or loading of the goods by the freight forwarder, and by which the freight forwarder undertakes to deliver the goods to the consignee named in the document.

720.name: Rail consignment note (generic term)
720.desc: Transport document constituting a contract for the carriage of goods between the sender and the carrier (the railway). For international rail traffic, this document must conform to the model prescribed by the international conventions concerning carriage of goods by rail, e.g. CIM Convention, SMGS Convention.

722.name: Road list-SMGS
722.desc: Accounting document, one copy of which is drawn up for each consignment note; it accompanies the consignment over the whole route and is a rail transport document.

723.name: Escort official recognition
723.desc: Document/message which gives right to the owner to exert all functions normally transferred to a guard in a train by which an escorted consignment is transported.

724.name: Recharging document
724.desc: Fictitious transport document regarding a previous transport, enabling a carrier's agent to give to another carrier's agent (in a different country) the possibility to collect charges relating to the original transport (rail environment).

730.name: Road consignment note
730.desc: Transport document/message which evidences a contract between a carrier and a sender for the carriage of goods by road (generic term). Remark: For international road traffic, this document must contain at least the particulars prescribed by the convention on the contract for the international carriage of goods by road (CMR).

740.name: Air waybill
740.desc: Document/message made out by or on behalf of the shipper which evidences the contract between the shipper and carrier(s) for carriage of goods over routes of the carrier(s) and which is identified by the airline prefix issuing the document plus a serial (IATA).

741.name: Master air waybill
741.desc: Document/message made out by or on behalf of the agent/consolidator which evidences the contract between the agent/consolidator and carrier(s) for carriage of goods over routes of the carrier(s) for a consignment consisting of goods originated by more than one shipper (IATA).

743.name: Substitute air waybill
743.desc: A temporary air waybill which contains only limited information because of the absence of the original.

744.name: Crew's effects declaration
744.desc: Declaration to Customs regarding the personal effects of crew members aboard the conveyance; equivalent to IMO FAL 4.

745.name: Passenger list
745.desc: Declaration to Customs regarding passengers aboard the conveyance; equivalent to IMO FAL 6.

746.name: Delivery notice (rail transport)
746.desc: Document/message created by the consignor or by the departure station, joined to the transport or sent to the consignee, giving the possibility to the consignee or the arrival station to attest the delivery of the goods. The document must be returned to the consignor or to the departure station.

750.name: Despatch note (post parcels)
750.desc: Document/message which, according to Article 106 of the "Agreement concerning Postal Parcels" under the UPU convention, is to accompany post parcels.

760.name: Multimodal/combined transport document (generic)
760.desc: A transport document used when more than one mode of transportation is involved in the movement of cargo. It is a contract of carriage and receipt of the cargo for a multimodal transport. It indicates the place where the responsible transport company in the move takes responsibility for the cargo, the place where the responsibility of this transport company in the move ends and the conveyances involved.

761.name: Through bill of lading
761.desc: Bill of lading which evidences a contract of carriage from one place to another in separate stages of which at least one stage is a sea transit, and by which the issuing carrier accepts responsibility for the carriage as set forth in the through bill of lading.

763.name: Forwarder's certificate of transport
763.desc: Negotiable document/message issued by a forwarder to certify that he has taken charge of a specified consignment for despatch and delivery in accordance with the consignor's instructions, as indicated in the document, and that he accepts responsibility for delivery of the goods to the holder of the document through the intermediary of a delivery agent of his choice. E.g. FIATA-FCT.

764.name: Combined transport document (generic)
764.desc: Negotiable or non-negotiable document evidencing a contract for the performance and/or procurement of performance of combined transport of goods and bearing on its face either the heading "Negotiable combined transport document issued subject to Uniform Rules for a Combined Transport Document (ICC Brochure No. 298)" or the heading "Non-negotiable Combined Transport Document issued subject to Uniform Rules for a Combined Transport Document (ICC Brochure No. 298)".

765.name: Multimodal transport document (generic)
765.desc: Document/message which evidences a multimodal transport contract, the taking in charge of the goods by the multimodal transport operator, and an undertaking by him to deliver the goods in accordance with the terms of the contract. (International Convention on Multimodal Transport of Goods).

766.name: Combined transport bill of lading/multimodal bill of lading
766.desc: Document which evidences a multimodal transport contract, the taking in charge of the goods by the multimodal transport operator, and an undertaking by him to deliver the goods in accordance with the terms of the contract.

770.name: Booking confirmation
770.desc: Document/message issued by a carrier to confirm that space has been reserved for a consignment in means of transport.

775.name: Calling forward notice
775.desc: Instructions for release or delivery of goods.

780.name: Freight invoice
780.desc: Document/message issued by a transport operation specifying freight costs and charges incurred for a transport operation and stating conditions of payment.

781.name: Arrival notice (goods)
781.desc: Notification from the carrier to the consignee in writing, by telephone or by any other means (express letter, message, telegram, etc.) informing him that a consignment addressed to him is being or will shortly be held at his disposal at a specified point in the place of destination.

782.name: Notice of circumstances preventing delivery (goods)
782.desc: Request made by the carrier to the sender, or, as the case may be, the consignee, for instructions as to the disposal of the consignment when circumstances prevent delivery and the return of the goods has not been requested by the consignor in the transport document.

783.name: Notice of circumstances preventing transport (goods)
783.desc: Request made by the carrier to the sender, or, the consignee as the case may be, for instructions as to the disposal of the goods when circumstances prevent transport before departure or en route, after acceptance of the consignment concerned.

784.name: Delivery notice (goods)
784.desc: Notification in writing, sent by the carrier to the sender, to inform him at his request of the actual date of delivery of the goods.

785.name: Cargo manifest
785.desc: Listing of goods comprising the cargo carried in a means of transport or in a transport-unit. The cargo manifest gives the commercial particulars of the goods, such as transport document numbers, consignors, consignees, shipping marks, number and kind of packages and descriptions and quantities of the goods.

786.name: Freight manifest
786.desc: Document/message containing the same information as a cargo manifest, and additional details on freight amounts, charges, etc.

787.name: Bordereau
787.desc: Document/message used in road transport, listing the cargo carried on a road vehicle, often referring to appended copies of Road consignment note.

788.name: Container manifest (unit packing list)
788.desc: Document/message specifying the contents of particular freight containers or other transport units, prepared by the party responsible for their loading into the container or unit.

789.name: Charges note
789.desc: Document used by the rail organization to indicate freight charges or additional charges in each case where the departure station is not able to calculate the charges for the total voyage (e.g. tariff not yet updated, part of voyage not covered by the tariff). This document must be considered as joined to the transport.

790.name: Advice of collection
790.desc: (1030) Document that is joined to the transport or sent by separate means, giving to the departure rail organization the proof that the cash-on delivery amount has been encashed by the arrival rail organization before reimbursement of the consignor.

791.name: Safety of ship certificate
791.desc: Document certifying a ship's safety to a specified date.

792.name: Safety of radio certificate
792.desc: Document certifying the safety of a ship's radio facilities to a specified date.

793.name: Safety of equipment certificate
793.desc: Document certifying the safety of a ship's equipment to a specified date.

794.name: Civil liability for oil certificate
794.desc: Document declaring a ship owner's liability for oil propelling or carried on a vessel.

795.name: Loadline document
795.desc: Document specifying the limit of a ship's legal submersion under various conditions.

796.name: Derat document
796.desc: Document certifying that a ship is free of rats, valid to a specified date.

797.name: Maritime declaration of health
797.desc: Document certifying the health condition on board a vessel, valid to a specified date.

798.name: Certificate of registry
798.desc: Official certificate stating the vessel's registry.

799.name: Ship's stores declaration
799.desc: Declaration to Customs regarding the contents of the ship's stores (equivalent to IMO FAL 3) i.e. goods intended for consumption by passengers/crew on board vessels, aircraft or trains, whether or not sold or landed; goods necessary for operation/maintenance of conveyance, including fuel/lubricants, excluding spare parts/equipment (IMO).

810.name: Export licence, application for
810.desc: Application for a permit issued by a government authority permitting exportation of a specified commodity subject to specified conditions as quantity, country of destination, etc.

811.name: Export licence
811.desc: Permit issued by a government authority permitting exportation of a specified commodity subject to specified conditions as quantity, country of destination, etc. Synonym: Embargo permit.

812.name: Exchange control declaration, export
812.desc: Document/message completed by an exporter/seller as a means whereby the competent body may control that the amount of foreign exchange accrued from a trade transaction is repatriated in accordance with the conditions of payment and exchange control regulations in force.

821.name: Despatch note model T1
821.desc: Transit declaration for goods circulating under internal community transit procedures (between European Union (EU) countries).

822.name: Despatch note model T2
822.desc: Ascertainment that the declared goods were originally produced in an European Union (EU) country.

823.name: Control document T5
823.desc: Control document (export declaration) used particularly in case of re-sending without use with only VAT collection, refusal, unconformity with contract etc.

824.name: Re-sending consignment note
824.desc: Rail consignment note prepared by the consignor for the facilitation of an eventual return to the origin of the goods.

825.name: Despatch note model T2L
825.desc: Ascertainment that the declared goods were originally produced in an European Union (EU) country. May only be used for goods that are loaded on one single means of transport in one single departure point for one single delivery point.

830.name: Goods declaration for exportation
830.desc: Document/message by which goods are declared for export Customs clearance, conforming to the layout key set out at Appendix I to Annex C.1 concerning outright exportation to the Kyoto convention (CCC). Within a Customs union, "for despatch" may have the same meaning as "for exportation".

833.name: Cargo declaration (departure)
833.desc: Generic term, sometimes referred to as Freight declaration, applied to the documents providing the particulars required by the Customs concerning the cargo (freight) carried by commercial means of transport (CCC).

840.name: Application for goods control certificate
840.desc: Document/message submitted to a competent body by party requesting a Goods control certificate to be issued in accordance with national or international standards, or conforming to legislation in the importing country, or as specified in the contract.

841.name: Goods control certificate
841.desc: Document/message issued by a competent body evidencing the quality of the goods described therein, in accordance with national or international standards, or conforming to legislation in the importing country, or as specified in the contract.

850.name: Application for phytosanitary certificate
850.desc: Document/message submitted to a competent body by party requesting a Phytosanitary certificate to be issued.

851.name: Phytosanitary certificate
851.desc: A message/doucment consistent with the model for certificates of the IPPC, attesting that a consignment meets phytosanitary import requirements.

852.name: Sanitary certificate
852.desc: Document/message issued by the competent authority in the exporting country evidencing that alimentary and animal products, including dead animals, are fit for human consumption, and giving details, when relevant, of controls undertaken.

853.name: Veterinary certificate
853.desc: Document/message issued by the competent authority in the exporting country evidencing that live animals or birds are not infested or infected with disease, and giving details regarding their provenance, and of vaccinations and other treatment to which they have been subjected.

855.name: Application for inspection certificate
855.desc: Document/message submitted to a competent body by a party requesting an Inspection certificate to be issued in accordance with national or international standards, or conforming to legislation in the country in which it is required, or as specified in the contract.

856.name: Inspection certificate
856.desc: Document/message issued by a competent body evidencing that the goods described therein have been inspected in accordance with national or international standards, in conformity with legislation in the country in which the inspection is required, or as specified in the contract.

860.name: Certificate of origin, application for
860.desc: Document/message submitted to a competent body by an interested party requesting a Certificate of origin to be issued in accordance with relevant criteria, and on the basis of evidence of the origin of the goods.

861.name: Certificate of origin
861.desc: Document/message identifying goods, in which the authority or body authorized to issue it certifies expressly that the goods to which the certificate relates originate in a specific country. The word "country" may include a group of countries, a region or a part of a country. This certificate may also include a declaration by the manufacturer, producer, supplier, exporter or other competent person.

862.name: Declaration of origin
862.desc: Appropriate statement as to the origin of the goods, made in connection with their exportation by the manufacturer, producer, supplier, exporter or other competent person on the Commercial invoice or any other document relating to the goods (CCC).

863.name: Regional appellation certificate
863.desc: Certificate drawn up in accordance with the rules laid down by an authority or approved body, certifying that the goods described therein qualify for a designation specific to the given region (e.g. champagne, port wine, Parmesan cheese).

864.name: Preference certificate of origin
864.desc: Document/message describing a certificate of origin meeting the requirements for preferential treatment.

865.name: Certificate of origin form GSP
865.desc: Specific form of certificate of origin for goods qualifying for preferential treatment under the generalized system of preferences (includes a combined declaration of origin and certificate, form A).

870.name: Consular invoice
870.desc: Document/message to be prepared by an exporter in his country and presented to a diplomatic representation of the importing country for endorsement and subsequently to be presented by the importer in connection with the import of the goods described therein.

890.name: Dangerous goods declaration
890.desc: (1115) Document/message issued by a consignor in accordance with applicable conventions or regulations, describing hazardous goods or materials for transport purposes, and stating that the latter have been packed and labelled in accordance with the provisions of the relevant conventions or regulations.

895.name: Statistical document, export
895.desc: Document/message in which an exporter provides information about exported goods required by the body responsible for the collection of international trade statistics.

896.name: INTRASTAT declaration
896.desc: Document/message in which a declarant provides information about goods required by the body responsible for the collection of trade statistics.

901.name: Delivery verification certificate
901.desc: Document/message whereby an official authority (Customs or governmental) certifies that goods have been delivered.

910.name: Import licence, application for
910.desc: Document/message in which an interested party applies to the competent body for authorization to import either a limited quantity of articles subject to import restrictions, or an unlimited quantity of such articles during a limited period, and specifies the kind of articles, their origin and value, etc.

911.name: Import licence
911.desc: Document/message issued by the competent body in accordance with import regulations in force, by which authorization is granted to a named party to import either a limited quantity of designated articles or an unlimited quantity of such articles during a limited period, under conditions specified in the document.

913.name: Customs declaration without commercial detail
913.desc: CUSDEC transmission that does not include data from the commercial detail section of the message.

914.name: Customs declaration with commercial and item detail
914.desc: CUSDEC transmission that includes data from both the commercial detail and item detail sections of the message.

915.name: Customs declaration without item detail
915.desc: CUSDEC transmission that does not include data from the item detail section of the message.

916.name: Related document
916.desc: Document that has a relationship with the stated document/message.

925.name: Application for exchange allocation
925.desc: Document/message whereby an importer/buyer requests the competent body to allocate an amount of foreign exchange to be transferred to an exporter/seller in payment for goods.

926.name: Foreign exchange permit
926.desc: Document/message issued by the competent body authorizing an importer/buyer to transfer an amount of foreign exchange to an exporter/seller in payment for goods.

927.name: Exchange control declaration (import)
927.desc: Document/message completed by an importer/buyer as a means for the competent body to control that a trade transaction for which foreign exchange has been allocated has been executed and that money has been transferred in accordance with the conditions of payment and the exchange control regulations in force.

929.name: Goods declaration for importation
929.desc: Document/message by which goods are declared for import Customs clearance [sister entry of 830].

930.name: Goods declaration for home use
930.desc: Document/message by which goods are declared for import Customs clearance according to Annex B.1 (concerning clearance for home use) to the Kyoto convention (CCC).

931.name: Customs immediate release declaration
931.desc: Document/message issued by an importer notifying Customs that goods have been removed from an importing means of transport to the importer's premises under a Customs- approved arrangement for immediate release, or requesting authorization to do so.

932.name: Customs delivery note
932.desc: Document/message whereby a Customs authority releases goods under its control to be placed at the disposal of the party concerned. Synonym: Customs release note.

933.name: Cargo declaration (arrival)
933.desc: Generic term, sometimes referred to as Freight declaration, applied to the documents providing the particulars required by the Customs concerning the cargo (freight) carried by commercial means of transport (CCC).

934.name: Value declaration
934.desc: Document/message in which a declarant (importer) states the invoice or other price (e.g. selling price, price of identical goods), and specifies costs for freight, insurance and packing, etc., terms of delivery and payment, any relationship with the trading partner, etc., for the purpose of determining the Customs value of goods imported.

935.name: Customs invoice
935.desc: Document/message required by the Customs in an importing country in which an exporter states the invoice or other price (e.g. selling price, price of identical goods), and specifies costs for freight, insurance and packing, etc., terms of delivery and payment, for the purpose of determining the Customs value in the importing country of goods consigned to that country.

936.name: Customs declaration (post parcels)
936.desc: Document/message which, according to Article 106 of the "Agreement concerning Postal Parcels" under the UPU Convention, must accompany post parcels and in which the contents of such parcels are specified.

937.name: Tax declaration (value added tax)
937.desc: Document/message in which an importer states the pertinent information required by the competent body for assessment of value-added tax.

938.name: Tax declaration (general)
938.desc: Document/message containing a general tax declaration.

940.name: Tax demand
940.desc: Document/message containing the demand of tax.

941.name: Embargo permit
941.desc: Document/message giving the permission to export specified goods.

950.name: Goods declaration for Customs transit
950.desc: Document/message by which the sender declares goods for Customs transit according to Annex E.1 (concerning Customs transit) to the Kyoto convention (CCC).

951.name: TIF form
951.desc: International Customs transit document by which the sender declares goods for carriage by rail in accordance with the provisions of the 1952 International Convention to facilitate the crossing of frontiers for goods carried by rail (TIF Convention of UIC).

952.name: TIR carnet
952.desc: International Customs document (International Transit by Road), issued by a guaranteeing association approved by the Customs authorities, under the cover of which goods are carried, in most cases under Customs seal, in road vehicles and/or containers in compliance with the requirements of the Customs TIR Convention of the International Transport of Goods under cover of TIR Carnets (UN/ECE).

953.name: EC carnet
953.desc: EC customs transit document issued by EC customs authorities for transit and/or temporary user of goods within the EC.

954.name: EUR 1 certificate of origin
954.desc: Customs certificate used in preferential goods interchanges between EC countries and EC external countries.

955.name: ATA carnet
955.desc: International Customs document (Admission Temporaire / Temporary Admission) which, issued under the terms of the ATA Convention (1961), incorporates an internationally valid guarantee and may be used, in lieu of national Customs documents and as security for import duties and taxes, to cover the temporary admission of goods and, where appropriate, the transit of goods. If accepted for controlling the temporary export and reimport of goods, international guarantee does not apply (CCC).

960.name: Single administrative document
960.desc: A set of documents, replacing the various (national) forms for Customs declaration within the EC, implemented on 01-01-1988.

961.name: General response (Customs)
961.desc: General response message to permit the transfer of data from Customs to the transmitter of the previous message.

962.name: Document response (Customs)
962.desc: Document response message to permit the transfer of data from Customs to the transmitter of the previous message.

963.name: Error response (Customs)
963.desc: Error response message to permit the transfer of data from Customs to the transmitter of the previous message.

964.name: Package response (Customs)
964.desc: Package response message to permit the transfer of data from Customs to the transmitter of the previous message.

965.name: Tax calculation/confirmation response (Customs)
965.desc: Tax calculation/confirmation response message to permit the transfer of data from Customs to the transmitter of the previous message.

966.name: Quota prior allocation certificate
966.desc: Document/message issued by the competent body for prior allocation of a quota.

970.name: Wagon report
970.desc: Document which contains consignment information concerning the wagons and their lading in a case of a multiple wagon consignment.

971.name: Transit Conveyor Document
971.desc: Document for a course of transit used for a carrier who is neither the carrier at the beginning nor the arrival. The transit carrier can directly invoice the expenses for its part of the transport.

972.name: Rail consignment note forwarder copy
972.desc: Document which is a copy of the rail consignment note printed especially for the need of the forwarder.

974.name: Duty suspended goods
974.desc: Document giving details for the carriage of excisable goods on a duty-suspended basis.

975.name: Proof of transit declaration
975.desc: A document providing proof that a transit declaration has been accepted.

976.name: Container transfer note
976.desc: Document for the carriage of containers. Syn: transfer note.

977.name: NATO transit document
977.desc: Customs transit document for the carriage of shipments of the NATO armed forces under Customs supervision.

978.name: Transfrontier waste shipment authorization
978.desc: Document containing the authorization from the relevant authority for the international carriage of waste. Syn: Transfrontier waste shipment permit.

979.name: Transfrontier waste shipment movement document
979.desc: Document certified by the carriers and the consignee to be used for the international carriage of waste.

990.name: End use authorization
990.desc: Document issued by Customs granting the end-use Customs procedure.

991.name: Government contract
991.desc: Document/message describing a contract with a government authority.

995.name: Statistical document, import
995.desc: Document/message describing an import document that is used for statistical purposes.

996.name: Application for documentary credit
996.desc: Message with application for opening of a documentary credit.

998.name: Previous Customs document/message
998.desc: Indication of the previous Customs document/message concerning the same transaction.

1.name: Heading section
1.desc: The section of the message being referenced is the header.

2.name: Detail section
2.desc: The section of the message being referenced is the detail.

5.name: Multiple sections
5.desc: Multiple sections of the message are being referenced.

6.name: Summary section
6.desc: The section of the message being referenced is the summary.

7.name: Sub-line item
7.desc: The section of the message being referenced refers to the sub-line item.

8.name: Commercial heading section of CUSDEC
8.desc: Group 7 to 14 of CUSDEC message.

9.name: Commercial line detail section of CUSDEC
9.desc: Group 15 to 22 of CUSDEC message.

10.name: Customs item detail section of CUSDEC
10.desc: Group 23 to 33 of CUSDEC message.

11.name: Customs sub-item detail section of CUSDEC
11.desc: Group 34 and 35 of CUSDEC message.

1.name: Included in document/transaction
1.desc: The document line is included in the document/transaction.

2.name: Excluded from document/transaction
2.desc: The document line is excluded from the document/transaction.

AAA.name: Order acknowledgement document identifier
AAA.desc: [1018] Reference number identifying the acknowledgement of an order.

AAB.name: Proforma invoice document identifier
AAB.desc: [1088] Reference number to identify a proforma invoice.

AAC.name: Documentary credit identifier
AAC.desc: [1172] Reference number to identify a documentary credit.

AAD.name: Contract document addendum identifier
AAD.desc: [1318] Reference number to identify an addendum to a contract.

AAE.name: Goods declaration number
AAE.desc: Reference number assigned to a goods declaration.

AAF.name: Debit card number
AAF.desc: A reference number identifying a debit card.

AAG.name: Offer number
AAG.desc: (1332) Reference number assigned by issuing party to an offer.

AAH.name: Bank's batch interbank transaction reference number
AAH.desc: Reference number allocated by the bank to a batch of different underlying interbank transactions.

AAI.name: Bank's individual interbank transaction reference number
AAI.desc: Reference number allocated by the bank to one specific interbank transaction.

AAJ.name: Delivery order number
AAJ.desc: Reference number assigned by issuer to a delivery order.

AAK.name: Despatch advice number
AAK.desc: [1035] Reference number assigned by issuing party to a despatch advice.

AAL.name: Drawing number
AAL.desc: Reference number identifying a specific product drawing.

AAM.name: Waybill number
AAM.desc: Reference number assigned to a waybill, see: 1001 = 700.

AAN.name: Delivery schedule number
AAN.desc: Reference number assigned by buyer to a delivery schedule.

AAO.name: Consignment identifier, consignee assigned
AAO.desc: [1362] Reference number assigned by the consignee to identify a particular consignment.

AAP.name: Partial shipment identifier
AAP.desc: [1310] Identifier of a shipment which is part of an order.

AAQ.name: Transport equipment identifier
AAQ.desc: [8260] To identify a piece if transport equipment e.g. container or unit load device.

AAR.name: Municipality assigned business registry number
AAR.desc: A reference number assigned by a municipality to identify a business.

AAS.name: Transport contract document identifier
AAS.desc: [1188] Reference number to identify a document evidencing a transport contract.

AAT.name: Master label number
AAT.desc: Identifies the master label number of any package type.

AAU.name: Despatch note document identifier
AAU.desc: [1128] Reference number to identify a Despatch Note.

AAV.name: Enquiry number
AAV.desc: Reference number assigned to an enquiry.

AAW.name: Docket number
AAW.desc: A reference number identifying the docket.

AA.name: Civil action number
AA.desc: A reference number identifying the civil action.

AAY.name: Carrier's agent reference number
AAY.desc: Reference number assigned by the carriers agent to a transaction.

AAZ.name: Standard Carrier Alpha Code (SCAC) number
AAZ.desc: For maritime shipments, this code qualifies a Standard Alpha Carrier Code (SCAC) as issued by the United Stated National Motor Traffic Association Inc.

ABA.name: Customs valuation decision number
ABA.desc: Reference by an importing party to a previous decision made by a Customs administration regarding the valuation of goods.

ABB.name: End use authorization number
ABB.desc: Reference issued by a Customs administration authorizing a preferential rate of duty if a product is used for a specified purpose, see: 1001 = 990.

ABC.name: Anti-dumping case number
ABC.desc: Reference issued by a Customs administration pertaining to a past or current investigation of goods "dumped" at a price lower than the exporter's domestic market price.

ABD.name: Customs tariff number
ABD.desc: (7357) Code number of the goods in accordance with the tariff nomenclature system of classification in use where the Customs declaration is made.

ABE.name: Declarant's reference number
ABE.desc: Unique reference number assigned to a document or a message by the declarant for identification purposes.

ABF.name: Repair estimate number
ABF.desc: A number identifying a repair estimate.

ABG.name: Customs decision request number
ABG.desc: Reference issued by Customs pertaining to a pending tariff classification decision requested by an importer or agent.

ABH.name: Sub-house bill of lading number
ABH.desc: Reference assigned to a sub-house bill of lading.

ABI.name: Tax payment identifier
ABI.desc: [1168] Reference number identifying a payment of a duty or tax e.g. under a transit procedure.

ABJ.name: Quota number
ABJ.desc: Reference number allocated by a government authority to identify a quota.

ABK.name: Transit (onward carriage) guarantee (bond) number
ABK.desc: Reference number to identify the guarantee or security provided for Customs transit operation (CCC).

ABL.name: Customs guarantee number
ABL.desc: Reference assigned to a Customs guarantee.

ABM.name: Replacing part number
ABM.desc: New part number which replaces the existing part number.

ABN.name: Seller's catalogue number
ABN.desc: Identification number assigned to a seller's catalogue.

ABO.name: Originator's reference
ABO.desc: A unique reference assigned by the originator.

ABP.name: Declarant's Customs identity number
ABP.desc: Reference to the party whose posted bond or security is being declared in order to accept responsibility for a goods declaration and the applicable duties and taxes.

ABQ.name: Importer reference number
ABQ.desc: Reference number assigned by the importer to identify a particular shipment for his own purposes.

ABR.name: Export clearance instruction reference number
ABR.desc: Reference number of the clearance instructions given by the consignor through different means.

ABS.name: Import clearance instruction reference number
ABS.desc: Reference number of the import clearance instructions given by the consignor/consignee through different means.

ABT.name: Goods declaration document identifier, Customs
ABT.desc: [1426] Reference number, assigned or accepted by Customs, to identify a goods declaration.

ABU.name: Article number
ABU.desc: A number that identifies an article.

ABV.name: Intra-plant routing
ABV.desc: To define routing within a plant.

ABW.name: Stock keeping unit number
ABW.desc: A number that identifies the stock keeping unit.

AB.name: Text Element Identifier deletion reference
AB.desc: The reference used within a given TEI (Text Element Identifier) which is to be deleted.

ABY.name: Allotment identification (Air)
ABY.desc: Reference assigned to guarantied capacity on one or more specific flights on specific date(s) to third parties as agents and other airlines.

ABZ.name: Vehicle licence number
ABZ.desc: Number of the licence issued for a vehicle by an agency of government.

AC.name: Air cargo transfer manifest Banker's acceptance
AC.desc: A number assigned to an air cargo list of goods to be transferred. Reference number for banker's acceptance issued by the accepting financial institution.

ACA.name: Cargo acceptance order reference number
ACA.desc: Reference assigned to the cargo acceptance order.

ACB.name: US government agency number
ACB.desc: A number that identifies a United States Government agency.

ACC.name: Shipping unit identification
ACC.desc: Identifying marks on the outermost unit that is used to transport merchandise.

ACD.name: Additional reference number
ACD.desc: [1010] Reference number provided in addition to another given reference.

ACE.name: Related document number
ACE.desc: Reference number identifying a related document.

ACF.name: Addressee reference
ACF.desc: A reference number of an addressee.

ACG.name: ATA carnet number
ACG.desc: Reference number assigned to an ATA carnet.

ACI.name: Outerpackaging unit identification
ACI.desc: Identifying marks on packing units contained within an outermost shipping unit.

ACJ.name: Customer material specification number
ACJ.desc: Number for a material specification given by customer.

ACK.name: Bank reference
ACK.desc: Cross reference issued by financial institution.

ACL.name: Principal reference number
ACL.desc: A number that identifies the principal reference.

ACN.name: Collection advice document identifier
ACN.desc: [1030] Reference number to identify a collection advice document.

ACO.name: Iron charge number
ACO.desc: Number attributed to the iron charge for the production of steel products.

ACP.name: Hot roll number
ACP.desc: Number attributed to a hot roll coil.

ACQ.name: Cold roll number
ACQ.desc: Number attributed to a cold roll coil.

ACR.name: Railway wagon number
ACR.desc: (8260) Registered identification initials and numbers of railway wagon. Synonym: Rail car number.

ACT.name: Unique claims reference number of the sender
ACT.desc: A number that identifies the unique claims reference of the sender.

ACU.name: Loss/event number
ACU.desc: To reference to the unique number that is assigned to each major loss hitting the reinsurance industry.

ACV.name: Estimate order reference number
ACV.desc: Reference number assigned by the ordering party of the estimate order.

ACW.name: Reference number to previous message
ACW.desc: Reference number assigned to the message which was previously issued (e.g. in the case of a cancellation, the primary reference of the message to be cancelled will be quoted in this element).

ACY.name: Duty memo number
ACY.desc: Reference number assigned by customs to a duty memo.

ACZ.name: Equipment transport charge number
ACZ.desc: Reference assigned to a specific equipment transportation charge.

ADA.name: Buyer's item number
ADA.desc: [7304] Reference number assigned by the buyer to an item.

ADB.name: Matured certificate of deposit
ADB.desc: Reference number for certificate of deposit allocated by issuing financial institution.

ADC.name: Loan
ADC.desc: Reference number for loan allocated by lending financial institution.

ADD.name: Analysis number/test number
ADD.desc: Number given to a specific analysis or test operation.

ADF.name: Treaty number
ADF.desc: A number that identifies a treaty.

ADG.name: Catastrophe number
ADG.desc: A number that identifies a catastrophe.

ADI.name: Bureau signing (statement reference)
ADI.desc: A statement reference that identifies a bureau signing.

ADL.name: Ordering customer consignment reference number
ADL.desc: Reference number assigned to the consignment by the ordering customer.

ADM.name: Shipowner's authorization number
ADM.desc: Reference number assigned by the shipowner as an authorization number to transport certain goods (such as hazardous goods, cool or reefer goods).

ADN.name: Inland transport order number
ADN.desc: Reference number assigned by the principal to the transport order for inland carriage.

ADO.name: Container work order reference number
ADO.desc: Reference number assigned by the principal to the work order for a (set of) container(s).

ADP.name: Statement number
ADP.desc: A reference number identifying a statement.

ADQ.name: Unique market reference
ADQ.desc: A number that identifies a unique market.

ADT.name: Group accounting
ADT.desc: A number that identifies group accounting.

ADW.name: Lloyd's claims office reference
ADW.desc: A number that identifies a Lloyd's claims office.

AD.name: Secure delivery terms and conditions agreement reference
AD.desc: A reference to a secure delivery terms and conditions agreement. A secured delivery agreement is an agreement containing terms and conditions to secure deliveries in case of failure in the production or logistics process of the supplier.

ADY.name: Report number
ADY.desc: Reference to a report to Customs by a carrier at the point of entry, encompassing both conveyance and consignment information.

ADZ.name: Trader account number
ADZ.desc: Number assigned by a Customs authority which uniquely identifies a trader (i.e. importer, exporter or declarant) for Customs purposes.

AE.name: Authorization for expense (AFE) number Non-negotiable maritime transport document number
AE.desc: A number that identifies an authorization for expense (AFE). Reference number assigned to a sea waybill, see: 1001 = 712.

AEA.name: Government agency reference number
AEA.desc: Coded reference number that pertains to the business of a government agency.

AEB.name: Assembly number
AEB.desc: A number that identifies an assembly.

AEC.name: Symbol number
AEC.desc: A number that identifies a symbol.

AED.name: Commodity number
AED.desc: A number that identifies a commodity.

AEE.name: Eur 1 certificate number
AEE.desc: Reference number assigned to a Eur 1 certificate.

AEF.name: Customer process specification number
AEF.desc: Retrieval number for a process specification defined by customer.

AEG.name: Customer specification number
AEG.desc: Retrieval number for a specification defined by customer.

AEH.name: Applicable instructions or standards
AEH.desc: Instructions or standards applicable for the whole message or a message line item. These instructions or standards may be published by a neutral organization or authority or another party concerned.

AEI.name: Registration number of previous Customs declaration
AEI.desc: Registration number of the Customs declaration lodged for the previous Customs procedure.

AEJ.name: Post-entry reference
AEJ.desc: Reference to a message related to a post-entry.

AEK.name: Payment order number
AEK.desc: A number that identifies a payment order.

AEL.name: Delivery number (transport)
AEL.desc: Reference number by which a haulier/carrier will announce himself at the container terminal or depot when delivering equipment.

AEM.name: Transport route
AEM.desc: A predefined and identified sequence of points where goods are collected, agreed between partners, e.g. the party in charge of organizing the transport and the parties where goods will be collected. The same collecting points may be included in different transport routes, but in a different sequence.

AEN.name: Customer's unit inventory number
AEN.desc: Number assigned by customer to a unique unit for inventory purposes.

AEO.name: Product reservation number
AEO.desc: Number assigned by seller to identify reservation of specified products.

AEP.name: Project number
AEP.desc: Reference number assigned to a project.

AEQ.name: Drawing list number
AEQ.desc: Reference number identifying a drawing list.

AER.name: Project specification number
AER.desc: Reference number identifying a project specification.

AES.name: Primary reference
AES.desc: A number that identifies the primary reference.

AET.name: Request for cancellation number
AET.desc: A number that identifies a request for cancellation.

AEU.name: Supplier's control number
AEU.desc: Reference to a file regarding a control of the supplier carried out on departure of the goods.

AEV.name: Shipping note number
AEV.desc: [1123] Reference number assigned to a shipping note.

AEW.name: Empty container bill number
AEW.desc: Reference number assigned to an empty container bill, see: 1001 = 708.

AEY.name: Substitute air waybill number
AEY.desc: Reference number assigned to a substitute air waybill, see: 1001 = 743.

AEZ.name: Despatch note (post parcels) number
AEZ.desc: (1128) Reference number assigned to a despatch note (post parcels), see: 1001 = 750.

AF.name: Airlines flight identification number Bill of quantities number
AF.desc: (8028) Identification of a commercial flight by carrier code and number as assigned by the airline (IATA). Reference number assigned to a bill of quantities.

AFA.name: Through bill of lading number
AFA.desc: Reference number assigned to a through bill of lading, see: 1001 = 761.

AFB.name: Cargo manifest number
AFB.desc: [1037] Reference number assigned to a cargo manifest.

AFC.name: Bordereau number
AFC.desc: Reference number assigned to a bordereau, see: 1001 = 787.

AFD.name: Customs item number
AFD.desc: Number (1496 in CST) assigned by the declarant to an item.

AFE.name: Export Control Commodity number (ECCN)
AFE.desc: Reference number to relevant item within Commodity Control List covering actual products change functionality.

AFF.name: Marking/label reference
AFF.desc: Reference where marking/label information derives from.

AFG.name: Tariff number
AFG.desc: A number that identifies a tariff.

AFH.name: Replenishment purchase order number
AFH.desc: Purchase order number specified by the buyer for the assignment to vendor's replenishment orders in a vendor managed inventory program.

AFI.name: Immediate transportation no. for in bond movement
AFI.desc: A number that identifies immediate transportation for in bond movement.

AFJ.name: Transportation exportation no. for in bond movement
AFJ.desc: A number that identifies the transportation exportation number for an in bond movement.

AFK.name: Immediate exportation no. for in bond movement
AFK.desc: A number that identifies the immediate exportation number for an in bond movement.

AFL.name: Associated invoices
AFL.desc: A number that identifies associated invoices.

AFM.name: Secondary Customs reference
AFM.desc: A number that identifies the secondary customs reference.

AFQ.name: Applicant's bank reference
AFQ.desc: Reference number of the applicant's bank.

AFR.name: Issuing bank's reference
AFR.desc: Reference number of the issuing bank.

AFS.name: Beneficiary's bank reference
AFS.desc: Reference number of the beneficiary's bank.

AFT.name: Direct payment valuation number
AFT.desc: Reference number assigned to a direct payment valuation.

AFU.name: Direct payment valuation request number
AFU.desc: Reference number assigned to a direct payment valuation request.

AFV.name: Quantity valuation number
AFV.desc: Reference number assigned to a quantity valuation.

AFW.name: Quantity valuation request number
AFW.desc: Reference number assigned to a quantity valuation request.

AFY.name: Payment valuation number
AFY.desc: Reference number assigned to a payment valuation.

AFZ.name: Situation number
AFZ.desc: Common reference number given to documents concerning a determined period of works.

AGA.name: Agreement to pay number
AGA.desc: A number that identifies an agreement to pay.

AGB.name: Contract party reference number
AGB.desc: Reference number assigned to a party for a particular contract.

AGC.name: Account party's bank reference
AGC.desc: Reference number of the account party's bank.

AGD.name: Agent's bank reference
AGD.desc: Reference number issued by the agent's bank.

AGG.name: Dispute number
AGG.desc: Reference number to a dispute notice.

AGH.name: Credit rating agency's reference number
AGH.desc: Reference number assigned by a credit rating agency to a debtor.

AGI.name: Request number
AGI.desc: The reference number of a request.

AGJ.name: Single transaction sequence number
AGJ.desc: A number that identifies a single transaction sequence.

AGK.name: Application reference number
AGK.desc: A number that identifies an application reference.

AGL.name: Delivery verification certificate
AGL.desc: Formal identification of delivery verification certificate which is a formal document from Customs etc. confirming that physical goods have been delivered. It may be needed to support a tax reclaim based on an invoice.

AGM.name: Number of temporary importation document
AGM.desc: Number assigned by customs to identify consignment in transit.

AGN.name: Reference number quoted on statement
AGN.desc: Reference number quoted on the statement sent to the beneficiary for information purposes.

AGO.name: Sender's reference to the original message
AGO.desc: The reference provided by the sender of the original message.

AGP.name: Company issued equipment ID
AGP.desc: Owner/operator, non-government issued equipment reference number.

AGQ.name: Domestic flight number

TB.desc: A cargo list/description issued by a motor carrier of freight.

TCR.desc: Reference assigned to a consignment by the terminal operator.

TE.desc: Reference number identifying a telex message.

TI.desc: Reference number assigned to a TIR carnet.

TIN.desc: Reference number identifying a transport instruction.

TN.desc: Reference applied to a transaction between two or more parties over a defined life cycle; e.g. number applied by importer or broker to obtain release from Customs, may then used to control declaration through final accounting (synonyms: declaration, entry number).

TP.desc: Reference number identifying a test report document relevant to the product.

UAR.name: Upper number of range
UAR.desc: Upper number in a range of numbers.

UC.desc: The originator's reference number as forwarded in a sequence of parties involved.

UCN.name: Unique consignment reference number
UCN.desc: [1202] Unique reference identifying a particular consignment of goods. Synonym: UCR, UCRN.

UN.desc: [7124] United Nations Dangerous Goods Identifier (UNDG) is the unique serial number assigned within the United Nations to substances and articles contained in a list of the dangerous goods most commonly carried.

UO.name: Ultimate customer's order number
UO.desc: The originator's order number as forwarded in a sequence of parties involved.

URI.name: Uniform Resource Identifier
URI.desc: A string of characters used to identify a name of a resource on the worldwide web.

VA.desc: Unique number assigned by the relevant tax authority to identify a party for use in relation to Value Added Tax (VAT).

VC.name: Vendor contract number
VC.desc: Number assigned by the vendor to a contract.

VN.name: Order number (vendor)
VN.desc: Reference number assigned by supplier to a buyer's purchase order.

VON.name: Voyage number
VON.desc: (8028) Reference number assigned to the voyage of the vessel.

VP.name: Vendor product number
VP.desc: Number assigned by vendor to another manufacturer's product.

VR.name: Vendor ID number
VR.desc: A number that identifies a vendor's identification.

VS.name: Vendor order number suffix
VS.desc: The suffix for a vendor order number.

VT.desc: (8213) Reference identifying a motor vehicle used for transport. Normally is the vehicle registration number.

WE.desc: Entry number under which imported merchandise was placed in a Customs bonded warehouse.

WM.name: Weight agreement number
WM.desc: A number identifying a weight agreement.

WN.name: Well number
WN.desc: A number assigned to a shaft sunk into the ground.

WR.name: Warehouse receipt number
WR.desc: A number identifying a warehouse receipt.

WS.name: Warehouse storage location number
WS.desc: A number identifying a warehouse storage location.

WY.name: Rail waybill number
WY.desc: The number on a rail waybill.

A.name: Company/place registration number
A.desc: Company registration and place as legally required.

C.desc: Reference used to identify and control a carrier and consignment from initial entry into a country until release of the cargo by Customs.

ZZZ.desc: Number based on party agreement.
