105.desc: Calendar day: Y = Year ; D = Day January the first = Day 001 Always start numbering the days of the year from January 1st through December 31st.

106.name: MMDD
106.desc: Day of a month: M = Month; D = Day. Day's number within a specific year: D = Day. Week's number within a specific year: W = Week. Month's number within a specific year: M = Month. Day's number within is a specific month: D = Day.

201.name: YYMMDDHHMM
201.desc: Calendar date including time without seconds: Y = Year; M = Month; D = Day; H = Hour; M = Minute.

202.name: YYMMDDHHMMSS
202.desc: Calendar date including time with seconds: Y = Year; M = Month; D = Day; H = Hour; m = Minutes = Seconds.

203.name: CCYYMMDDHHMM
203.desc: Calendar date including time with minutes: C=Century; Y=Year; M=Month; D=Day; H=Hour; M=Minutes.

204.name: CCYYMMDDHHMMSS
204.desc: Calendar date including time with seconds: C=Century;Y=Year; M=Month;D=Day;H=Hour;M=Minute;S=Second.

205.name: CCYYMMDDHHMMZHHMM
205.desc: Calendar date including time and time zone expressed in hours and minutes. ZHHMM = time zone given as offset from Coordinated Universal Time (UTC).

206.name: YYMMDDHHMMZHHMM
206.desc: Calendar date including time without seconds, with Time Zone:  Y = Year; M = Month; D = Day; H = Hour; M = Minute,  Z = leading plus/minus sign, HHMM = difference to UTC in Hours and Minutes.

207.name: YYMMDDHHMMSSZHHMM
207.desc: Calendar date including time with seconds, with Time Zone:  Y = Year; M = Month; D = Day; H = Hour; M = Minute, S = Seconds Z = leading plus/minus sign, HHMM = difference to UTC in Hours and Minutes.

208.name: CCYYMMDDHHMMSSZHHMM
208.desc: Calendar date including time with seconds, with Time Zone:  C = Century, Y = Year; M = Month; D = Day; H = Hour; M = Minute, S = Seconds, Z = leading plus/minus sign, HHMM = difference to UTC in Hours and Minutes.

209.name: HHMMSSZHHMM
209.desc: Time with seconds and with Time Zone:  H = Hour; M = Minute, S = Seconds, Z = leading plus/minus sign, HHMM = difference to UTC in Hours and Minutes.

210.name: HHMMSSZHHMM-HHMMSSZHHMM
210.desc: A period of time specified by giving the start time followed by the end time (both expressed by hours, minutes, seconds and time zone leading plus/minus sign and time zone difference in hours and minutes).

305.name: MMDDHHMM
305.desc: Month, day, hours, minutes; M = Month; D = Day; H = Hour; M = Minute.

306.name: DDHHMM
306.desc: Day, hours, minutes; D = Day; H = Hour; M = Minute.

401.name: HHMM
401.desc: Time without seconds: H = Hour; m = Minute.

402.name: HHMMSS
402.desc: Time with seconds: H = Hour; m = Minute; s = Seconds.

406.name: ZHHMM
406.desc: Offset from Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) where Z is plus (+) or minus (-).

501.name: HHMMHHMM
501.desc: Time span without seconds: H = Hour; m = Minute;.

502.name: HHMMSS-HHMMSS
502.desc: A period of time specified by giving the start time followed by the end time (both expressed by hours minutes and seconds). Data is to be transmitted as consecutive characters without hyphen.

503.name: HHMMSSZZZ-HHMMSSZZZ
503.desc: A period of time specified by giving the start time followed by the end time (both expressed by hours minutes, seconds and time zone). Data is to be transmitted as consecutive characters without hyphen. Century. Calendar year: Y = Year.

602.name: CCYY
602.desc: Calendar year including century: C = Century; Y = Year. Semester in a calendar year: Y = Year; S = Semester.

604.name: CCYYS
604.desc: Semester in a calendar year: C = Century; Y = Year; S = Semester.

608.name: CCYYQ
608.desc: Quarter in a calendar year: C = Century; Y = Year; Q = Quarter.

609.name: YYMM
609.desc: Month within a calendar year: Y = Year; M = Month.

610.name: CCYYMM
610.desc: Month within a calendar year: CC = Century; Y = Year; M = Month.

613.name: YYMMA
613.desc: To specifiy a ten-day period within a month of a year (A = ten day period).

614.name: CCYYMMA
614.desc: To specifiy a ten-day period within a month of a year, including century  (A = ten day period).

615.name: YYWW
615.desc: Week within a calendar year: Y = Year; W = Week 1st week of January = week 01.

616.name: CCYYWW
616.desc: Week within a calendar year: CC = Century; Y = Year; W = Week (1st week of January = week 01).

701.name: YY-YY
701.desc: A period of time specified by giving the start year followed by the end year (both without century). Data is to be transmitted as consecutive characters without hyphen.

702.name: CCYY-CCYY
702.desc: A period of time specified by giving the start year followed by the end year (both including century). Data is to be transmitted as consecutive characters without hyphen.

703.name: YYS-YYS
703.desc: A period of time specified by giving the start semester of a year followed by the end semester of a year (both not including century). Data is to be transmitted as consecutive characters without hyphen.

704.name: CCYYS-CCYYS
704.desc: A period of time specified by giving the start semester of a year followed by the end semester of a year (both including century). Data is to be transmitted as consecutive characters without hyphen.

705.name: YYPYYP
705.desc: Format of period to be given without hyphen (P = period of 4 months).

706.name: CCYYP-CCYYP
706.desc: Format of period to be given without hyphen (P = period of 4 months).

707.name: YYQ-YYQ
707.desc: A period of time specified by giving the start quarter of a year followed by the end quarter of year (both not including century). Data is to be transmitted as consecutive characters without hyphen.

708.name: CCYYQ-CCYYQ
708.desc: A period of time specified by giving the start quarter of a year followed by the end quarter of year (both including century). Data is to be transmitted as consecutive characters without hyphen.

709.name: YYMM-YYMM
709.desc: A period of time specified by giving the start month of a year followed by the end month of a year (both not including century). Data is to be transmitted as consecutive characters without hyphen.

710.name: CCYYMM-CCYYMM
710.desc: A period of time specified by giving the start month of a year followed by the end month of a year (both including century). Data is to be transmitted as consecutive characters without hyphen.

713.name: YYMMDDHHMM-YYMMDDHHMM
713.desc: A period of time specified by giving the start time followed by the end time (format year, month, day, hour and minute). Data is to be transmitted as consecutive characters without hyphen.

715.name: YYWW-YYWW
715.desc: A period of time specified by giving the start week of a year followed by the end week of year (both not including century). Data is to be transmitted as consecutive characters without hyphen.

716.name: CCYYWW-CCYYWW
716.desc: A period of time specified by giving the start week of a year followed by the end week of year (both including century). Data is to be transmitted as consecutive characters without hyphen.

717.name: YYMMDD-YYMMDD
717.desc: A period of time specified by giving the start date followed by the end date (both not including century). Data is to be transmitted as consecutive characters without hyphen.

718.name: CCYYMMDD-CCYYMMDD
718.desc: A period of time specified by giving the start date followed by the end date (both including century). Data is to be transmitted as consecutive characters without hyphen.

719.name: CCYYMMDDHHMM-CCYYMMDDHHMM
719.desc: A period of time which includes the century, year, month, day, hour and minute. Format of period to be given in actual message without hyphen.

720.name: DHHMM-DHHMM
720.desc: Format of period to be given without hyphen (D=day of the week, 1=Monday; 2=Tuesday; ... 7=Sunday).

801.name: Year
801.desc: To indicate a quantity of years.

802.name: Month
802.desc: To indicate a quantity of months.

803.name: Week
803.desc: To indicate a quantity of weeks. To indicate a quantity of days.

805.name: Hour
805.desc: To indicate a quantity of hours.

806.name: Minute
806.desc: To indicate a quantity of minutes.

807.name: Second
807.desc: To indicate a quantity of seconds.

808.name: Semester
808.desc: To indicate a quantity of semesters (six months).

809.name: Four months period
809.desc: To indicate a quantity of four months periods.

810.name: Trimester
810.desc: To indicate a quantity of trimesters (three months).

811.name: Half month
811.desc: To indicate a quantity of half months.

812.name: Ten days
812.desc: To indicate a quantity of ten days periods.

1.name: Date of order
1.desc: Payment time reference is date of order.

2.name: Date of confirmation
2.desc: Payment time reference is date of confirmation.

3.name: Date of contract
3.desc: Payment time reference is date of contract.

4.name: Date of signature of contract
4.desc: Payment time reference is date of signature of contract.

5.name: Date of invoice
5.desc: Payment time reference is date of invoice.

6.name: Date of credit note
6.desc: Payment time reference is date of credit note.

7.name: Date of present document
7.desc: Payment time reference is date of present document.

8.name: Date of confirmation of order received
8.desc: Payment time reference is date of confirmation received.

9.name: Date invoice received
9.desc: Payment time reference is date of invoice received.

10.name: Latest date/time for bid reception
10.desc: The date when, at the latest, the bids have to be submitted. This date is required for each call for tender, either in public or private sector.

11.name: Date credit note received
11.desc: Payment time reference is date of credit note received.

12.name: Date present document received
12.desc: Payment time reference is date of present document received.

13.name: Date of resale by buyer
13.desc: Payment time reference is date of resale by the buyer.

14.name: Date proceeds of resale collected by buyer
14.desc: Payment time reference is date of resale proceeds are collected by buyer. "buyer" is a retailer. Retailer will pay his supplier when having sold goods and money received.

21.name: Date goods received by buyer
21.desc: Payment time reference is date when goods are received by buyer.

22.name: Date goods received by buyer's agent
22.desc: Payment time reference is date when goods are received by buyer's agent.

23.name: Date goods received by carrier
23.desc: Payment time reference is date when goods are received by carrier.

24.name: Date ex-works
24.desc: Payment time reference is date when goods are leaving the sellers factory.

25.name: Date goods handed over for shipment by seller or agent
25.desc: Payment time reference is the date when goods are handed over for shipment by the seller or his agent.

26.name: Date of arrival of transport
26.desc: Date the transport arrived at the agreed destination.

27.name: Date of outward frontier crossing
27.desc: Date the goods are crossing the border of the exporters country.

28.name: Date of inward frontier crossing
28.desc: Date the goods are crossing the border of the importers country.

29.name: Date of delivery of goods to establishments/domicile/site
29.desc: Date the goods are delivered at agreed place of destination.

31.name: Stipulated date for payment of documentary credit
31.desc: Date as per agreement when documentary credit is due for payment.

32.name: Stipulated date for acceptance of documentary credit
32.desc: Date as per agreement when documentary credit is accepted.

33.name: Stipulated date for negotiation of documentary credit
33.desc: Date as per agreement when documentary credit is negotiated.

41.name: Date of delivery to buyer of documents representing goods
41.desc: Date when documents representing goods are received by buyer .

42.name: Date of delivery to buyer's agent of documents representing goods
42.desc: Date when documents representing goods are received by buyer's agent.

43.name: Date of delivery to carrier of documents representing goods
43.desc: Date when documents representing goods are received by carrier.

44.name: Date of delivery to intermediary bank of documents representing good
44.desc: Date when documents representing goods are received by intermediary bank.

45.name: Date of bill of lading, consignment note or other transport document
45.desc: The date of issuance of a bill of lading, consignment note or similar transport document.

46.name: Date of receipt for loading (mate's receipt)
46.desc: Date when goods are expedited to a ship confirmed by mate's received.

47.name: Date of negotiable instrument (draft, promissory note, bank)
47.desc: Payment time reference is the date of the negotiable instrument.

48.name: Date of receipt of tool dependent initial samples plus unlimited absolute bank guarantee plus value added tax
48.desc: Payment time reference is date of receipt of tool dependent initial samples and unlimited absolute bank guarantee of a third party, who is liable to the full amount of the tooling (which is owned by the customer).

52.name: Due date of negotiable instrument
52.desc: Date when the negotiable instrument is due for payment.

53.name: Date of presentation of negotiable instrument
53.desc: Date when the negotiable instrument is presented or will be presented to drawee.

54.name: Date of acceptance of negotiable instrument
54.desc: Date when the negotiable instrument is accepted or will be accepted by drawee.

55.name: Date of acceptance of tooling
55.desc: Payment time reference is date of acceptance of tooling or set of tooling.

56.name: Date of receipt of tooling
56.desc: Payment time reference is date of receipt of tooling or set of tooling.

57.name: Date of acceptance of first samples produced under production conditions
57.desc: Payment time reference is date of acceptance of first samples produced under production conditions.

60.name: Date of start of work
60.desc: Payment time reference is the date when work begins.

61.name: Date of end of work
61.desc: Payment time reference is the date when work ends.

62.name: Date of provisional reception of work
62.desc: Date of temporary acceptance of work until final reception will take place.

63.name: Date of final acceptance of work
63.desc: Payment time reference is the date of final acceptance of work.

64.name: Date of certificate of preliminary acceptance
64.desc: Date of certificate of temporary acceptance of work until final reception will take place.

65.name: Date of certificate of final acceptance
65.desc: Payment time reference is the date of the certificate of final acceptance.

66.name: Specified date
66.desc: Date specified elsewhere.

67.name: Anticipated delivery date
67.desc: The date on which delivery is anticipated to take place.

68.name: Effective date
68.desc: The date on which an action or event becomes effective.

69.name: Invoice transmission date
69.desc: Payment time reference is the date of invoice transmission.

70.name: Date of issue of transport document(s)
70.desc: The date on which a transport document(s) is issued.

71.name: Date of presentation of documents
71.desc: Payment time reference is the date when documents are presented.

72.name: Payment date
72.desc: Date when a payment was made.

73.name: Draft(s) at ... days sight
73.desc: Draft(s) is/are due after a specific number of days after sight.

74.name: Draft(s) at ... days date
74.desc: Draft(s) is/are due after a specific number of days after date.

75.name: Draft(s) at ... days after date of issuance of transport document(s)
75.desc: Draft(s) is/are due after a specific number of days after date of issuance of transport document(s).

76.name: Draft(s) at ... days after date of presentation of documents
76.desc: Draft(s) is/are due after a specific number of days after date of presentation of documents.

77.name: Specified draft date
77.desc: Draft at specified date.

78.name: Customs clearance date (import)
78.desc: Date when goods clear Customs in the importing country.

79.name: Customs clearance date (export)
79.desc: Date when goods clear Customs in the exporting country.

80.name: Date of salary payment
80.desc: Date when a salary payment was made.

81.name: Date of shipment as evidenced by the transport document(s)
81.desc: Date of shipment as evidenced by the transport document(s).

82.name: Payment due date
82.desc: Date on which a payment is due.

83.name: Requested date of delivery
83.desc: Payment terms apply from the requested date of delivery.

ZZZ.name: Other reference date agreed upon between the parties
ZZZ.desc: A code assigned within a code list to be used on an interim basis and as defined among trading partners until a precise code can be assigned to the code list.

AA.name: Party to be billed (AAR Accounting rule 11)
AA.desc: Party to be billed in accordance with AAR Accounting rule 11.

AB.name: Buyer's agent/representative
AB.desc: Third party who arranged the purchase of merchandise on behalf of the actual buyer.

AE.name: Declarant's agent/representative
AE.desc: Any natural or legal person who makes a declaration to an official body on behalf of another natural or legal person, where legally permitted (CCC).

AF.name: Transit principal
AF.desc: Natural or legal person responsible for the satisfactory performance of a Customs transit operation. Source: CCC.

AG.name: Agent
AG.desc: (3196) Party authorized to act on behalf of another party. Synonym: Representative.

AH.name: Transit principal's agent/representative
AH.desc: Agent acting on behalf of the transit principal (CCC).

AI.name: Successful job applicant
AI.desc: Person who has been chosen for a job.

AJ.name: Party issuing mutually agreed codes
AJ.desc: The party which has issued all mutually agreed codes used in the message.

AK.name: Acknowledgement recipient
AK.desc: Party to whom acknowledgement should be sent.

AL.name: Principal responsible party
AL.desc: (3340) Party accepting liability for goods held or moving (e.g. transit) under a Customs authorization and - when applicable - a guarantee.

AM.name: Authorized official
AM.desc: Employee of a company or firm authorized to act on behalf of that company or firm e.g. to make a Customs declaration.

AN.name: Approved importer
AN.desc: Person or company which is authorised by the relevant Customs authority to import goods without payment all taxes or specific taxes at the point of entry into the country.

AP.name: Accepting party
AP.desc: (3336) Party accepting goods, products, services, etc.

AQ.name: Approved consignor
AQ.desc: Person or company approved by the relevant authority in the country to pack and export specific goods under Customs supervision.

AR.name: Authorized exporter
AR.desc: Exporter authorized/approved by Customs for special Customs procedures e.g. simplified procedure.

AS.name: Account servicing financial institution
AS.desc: Identifies the financial institution servicing the account(s).

AT.name: Authorized importer
AT.desc: Importer authorized/approved by Customs for special Customs procedures e.g. simplified procedure.

AU.name: Authorized trader (transit)
AU.desc: Trader authorized/approved by Customs for special transit procedures e.g. simplified procedure.

AV.name: Authorizing official
AV.desc: Party that has delegated the authority to take a certain action on behalf of a company or agency.

AW.name: Applicant's bank
AW.desc: (3234) Financial institution which is requested to issue the documentary credit.

A.name: Authenticating party
A.desc: Party which certifies that a document is authentic.

AZ.name: Issuing bank
AZ.desc: [3320] Financial institution which issues the documentary credit, if the applicant's bank is not acting as the issuing bank.

B1.name: Contact bank 1
B1.desc: Identifies an additional bank which must be informed of certain aspects of the message.

B2.name: Contact bank 2
B2.desc: Identifies an additional bank which must be informed of certain aspects of the message.

BA.name: Booking agent
BA.desc: Party acting as a booking office for transport and forwarding services.

BB.name: Buyer bank identification
BB.desc: [3421]To identify a bank employed by the buyer to make a payment.

BC.name: Negotiating bank
BC.desc: Financial institution to whom a negotiable documentary credit is directed.

BD.name: Documentary credit reimbursing bank
BD.desc: [3350] A financial institution which reimburses documentary credit.

BE.name: Beneficiary
BE.desc: (3260) The ultimate recipient of the funds. Normally the account owner who is reimbursed by the payer.

BF.name: Beneficiary's bank
BF.desc: (3422) Identifies the account servicer for the beneficiary or the payee.

BG.name: Employer
BG.desc: A party that keeps a person in service for payment.

BI.name: Buyer's financial institution
BI.desc: Financial institution designated by buyer to make payment.

BJ.name: Release to party
BJ.desc: Party to which the goods or container(s) is (are) to be released.

BM.name: Insured
BM.desc: [3136] Party which is the object of an insurance contract.

BN.name: Insurance beneficiary
BN.desc: Party which benefits from insurance coverage.

BO.name: Broker or sales office
BO.desc: Party acting in the name of the seller as broker or as sales office.

BP.name: Building site purchaser
BP.desc: Party at the building site responsible for the purchasing of goods and services for that particular site.

BQ.name: Cheque drawn bank
BQ.desc: Identifies the bank on which the cheque should be drawn, as instructed by the ordering customer.

BS.name: Bill and ship to
BS.desc: Party receiving goods and relevant invoice.

BT.name: Party to be billed for other than freight (bill to)
BT.desc: Party receiving invoice excluding freight costs.

BU.name: Service bureau
BU.desc: Party carrying out service bureau processing work, (e.g. a payroll bureau).

BV.name: Member
BV.desc: Member of a group (e.g. of a group of persons or a service scheme).

BW.name: Borrower
BW.desc: A person who acquires something temporarily with the promise or intention of returning.

B.name: Building site engineer
B.desc: Party at the building site responsible for engineering matters for that particular site.

BY.name: Buyer
BY.desc: [3002] Party to which merchandise or services are sold.

BZ.name: Building site forwarder
BZ.desc: Party at the building site responsible for forwarding the received goods on that particular site.

C1.name: In care of party no. 1
C1.desc: A person taking responsibility on behalf of party no. 1.

C2.name: In care of party no. 2
C2.desc: A person taking responsibility on behalf of party no. 2.

CA.name: Carrier
CA.desc: [3126] Party undertaking or arranging transport of goods between named points.

CB.name: Customs broker
CB.desc: Agent or representative or a professional Customs clearing agent who deals directly with Customs on behalf of the importer or exporter (CCC).

CC.name: Claimant
CC.desc: Party who claims goods or insurance.

CE.name: Ceding company
CE.desc: Company which cedes something to someone.

CF.name: Container operator/lessee
CF.desc: Party to whom the possession of specified property (e.g. container) has been conveyed for a period of time in return for rental payments.

CG.name: Carrier's agent
CG.desc: [3052] Party authorized to act for or on behalf of carrier.

CH.name: Connecting carrier
CH.desc: Owner or operator of a transportation conveyance to which goods in a given transaction will be transferred.

CI.name: Commission processor
CI.desc: Party who provides extra treatment to goods on commission base.

CJ.name: Previous member
CJ.desc: Previous member of a group of persons or a service scheme.

CK.name: Empty equipment despatch party
CK.desc: Party from whose premises empty equipment will be or has been despatched.

CL.name: Container location party
CL.desc: Party from whose premises container will be or has been despatched.

CM.name: Customs
CM.desc: Identification of customs authority relevant to the transaction or shipment.

CN.name: Consignee Cash pool top account servicing financial institution
CN.desc: [3132] Party to which goods are consigned. Identification of a financial institution servicing the top account of a cash pool.

CNY.name: Cash pool level account servicing financial institution
CNY.desc: Identification of a financial institution servicing the level account of a cash pool.

CNZ.name: Cash pool sub-account servicing financial institution
CNZ.desc: Identification of a financial institution servicing the sub-account of a cash pool.

CO.name: Corporate office Freight payer on behalf of the consignee
CO.desc: Identification of the Head Office within a company. (3470) Freight payer is a third party acting on behalf of the consignee.

COA.name: Entity in which a financial interest is held
COA.desc: Business in which a financial interest is held.

COD.name: Quotation requesting party
COD.desc: Party sending a request for a quotation.

COE.name: Party maintaining the codes used in the message
COE.desc: The party which maintains the codes used in the message.

COF.name: Party maintaining the identifiers used in the message
COF.desc: The party which maintains the identifiers used in the message.

COG.name: Dispatcher
COG.desc: An individual responsible for sending something to a destination.

COH.name: Submitter of sample
COH.desc: An entity responsible for the submission of a sample.

COJ.name: Primary health care provider
COJ.desc: Health care provider that has primary responsibility for patient.

COL.name: Admitting health care provider
COL.desc: Health care provider that admitted the patient.

COM.name: Referring health care provider
COM.desc: Health care provider that referred patient to current provider of services.

CON.name: Supervising health care provider
CON.desc: Health care provider that supervised the rendering of a service.

COO.name: Party providing financing
COO.desc: Identifies the party providing the financing.

COP.name: Convoying party
COP.desc: Party designated to escort the transported goods.

COS.name: Co-participant
COS.desc: Identifies another party who participates in an activity.

COT.name: Involved party
COT.desc: Party which is involved in an activity.

COV.name: Registered principal
COV.desc: An individual who is registered as a principal for an entity.

COW.name: Freight payer on behalf of the consignor
COW.desc: (3470) Freight payer is a third party acting on behalf of the consignor.

COY.name: Party responsible for disinfection
COY.desc: Party responsible for performing disinfection operations.

COZ.name: Party responsible for refueling
COZ.desc: Party responsible for performing refueling operations.

CP.name: Party to receive certificate of compliance
CP.desc: Party acting for or on behalf of seller in matters concerning compliance.

CPA.name: Advising bank
CPA.desc: [3190] Identifies the financial institution used by the issuing bank to advise the documentary credit.

CPB.name: Reimbursing bank
CPB.desc: Identifies the financial institution through which the reimbursement is to be effected.

CPC.name: Advise through bank
CPC.desc: Identifies the financial institution through which the advising bank is to advise.

CPD.name: Charges payer at destination
CPD.desc: Party, other than the ordering party, which has to pay the charges concerning the destination operations.

CPE.name: Transport means master name
CPE.desc: [3408] Name of the Master of a means of transport such as vessel.

CPF.name: Means of transport charterer
CPF.desc: Charterer of the means of transport.

CPG.name: Excise party
CPG.desc: Party to whom excise must be paid.

CPH.name: Copy report to
CPH.desc: Party receiving a copy of a report.

CPI.name: Related healthcare party
CPI.desc: A healthcare party related to the subject.

CPM.name: Patient discharged to
CPM.desc: The party who receives the discharged patient.

CQ.name: Cheque order
CQ.desc: Party to which the cheque will be ordered, when different from the beneficiary.

CR.name: Empty equipment return party
CR.desc: Party to whose premises empty equipment will be or has been returned.

CS.name: Consolidator
CS.desc: Party consolidating various consignments, payments etc.

CT.name: Consignee to be specified
CT.desc: The party to be identified at a later time as the consignee.

CU.name: Container return company
CU.desc: The company to which containers have to be returned.

CV.name: Consignee of vessel
CV.desc: Party to which the vessel shall be delivered.

C.name: Consignee's agent
C.desc: Party authorized to act on behalf of the consignee.

CY.name: Commissionable agent
CY.desc: IATA cargo agent entitled to commission.

CZ.name: Consignor
CZ.desc: [3336] Party which, by contract with a carrier, consigns or sends goods with the carrier, or has them conveyed by him. Synonym: shipper, sender.

DA.name: Available with bank (documentary credits)
DA.desc: Financial institution with whom the documentary credit is available.

DB.name: Distributor branch
DB.desc: The affiliate of a retailer or distributor.

DC.name: Deconsolidator Party to receive refund
DC.desc: Party that splits up a large consignment composed of separate consignments of goods. The smaller consignments of goods were grouped together into that large consignment for carriage as a larger unit in order to obtain a reduced rate. Party to whom a refund is given.

DCP.name: Despatch charge payer
DCP.desc: Party, other than the ordering party, which has to pay the charges concerning the despatch operations.

DCQ.name: Prescription database owner
DCQ.desc: Organisation or person owning a prescription database.

DCR.name: Original prescriber
DCR.desc: The doctor who issued the original prescription.

DCS.name: Temporary employee
DCS.desc: A person employed on a temporary basis.

DCU.name: Quotation delivered to
DCU.desc: Party to whom the quotation is to be or has been delivered.

DCY.name: Authorised issuer of prescription
DCY.desc: Party authorised to issue a prescription.

DCZ.name: Authorised dispenser of medicine
DCZ.desc: Organisation or person authorised to dispense medicine.

DD.name: Documentary credit account party's bank Imbalance settlement responsible party
DD.desc: Bank of the documentary credit account party. A party that is responsible for settlement of the difference between planned and realised quantities.

DDA.name: Report responsible party
DDA.desc: The party or person taking responsibility for a report.

DDB.name: Initial sender
DDB.desc: The party who does the initial sending.

DDC.name: The party authorising the original prescription
DDC.desc: The party authorising the issuer of the original prescription.

DDD.name: Applicant
DDD.desc: A party who applies for something.

DDE.name: Meter reader
DDE.desc: A party physically reading the meter.

DDF.name: Primary electronic business contact
DDF.desc: Code specifying a party who serves as a business entity's primary contact for matters related to electronic business.

DDG.name: Alternate electronic business contact
DDG.desc: Code specifying a party who serves as a business entity's alternate contact for matters related to electronic business.

DDH.name: Primary government business contact
DDH.desc: Code specifying a party who serves as a business entity's primary contact for matters related to doing business with the government.

DDI.name: Alternate government business contact
DDI.desc: Code specifying a party who serves as a business entity's alternate contact for matters related to doing business with the government.

DDJ.name: Past performance contact
DDJ.desc: Code specifying a party who serves as a business entity's contact for matters related to the past performance of that entity.

DDK.name: Balance responsible party
DDK.desc: A party responsible for balancing supply and consumption.

DDL.name: Group of passengers
DDL.desc: A group of persons conveyed by a means of transport, other than the crew.

DDN.name: First financial institution in the transaction chain
DDN.desc: Identifies the financial institution that is the point of entry into the interbank transaction chain.

DDO.name: Location manager
DDO.desc: Party responsible for the management of the location.

DDP.name: Group leader
DDP.desc: Party responsible for leading the group.

DDR.name: Consignor's freight forwarder
DDR.desc: Identification of freight forwarder giving services to the consignor.

DDS.name: Consignee's freight forwarder
DDS.desc: Identification of freight forwarder giving services to the consignee.

DDT.name: In transit crew member
DDT.desc: The movement of a crew member from one country to another via the territory of an intermediate country for which no entry is intended.

DDU.name: In transit passenger
DDU.desc: The movement of a passenger from one country to another via the territory of an intermediate country for which no entry is intended.

DDV.name: Energy consumption imbalance responsible party
DDV.desc: A party who can be brought to rights, legally and financially, for any imbalance between energy bought and consumed for all associated metering points.

DDW.name: Energy production imbalance responsible party
DDW.desc: A party who can be brought to rights, legally and financially, for any imbalance between energy sold and produced for all associated metering points.

DDY.name: Transmission capacity allocator
DDY.desc: A party managing the allocation of transmission capacity.

DDZ.name: Metering point administrator
DDZ.desc: A party responsible for registering the technical specifications of metering points and the parties linked to them.

DE.name: Depositor Pilots seated outside cockpit
DE.desc: Party depositing goods, financial payments or documents. Pilots currently not in charge of flying the aircraft and not present in the cockpit.

DEA.name: Metered data aggregator
DEA.desc: A party responsible for aggregation of metered data.

DEB.name: Meter operator
DEB.desc: A party responsible for the operation of a meter,  including installing  maintaining, testing, certifying and decommissioning.

DEC.name: Party connected to grid
DEC.desc: A party that contracts for the right to consume or produce electricity at a metering point.

DEE.name: Stowaway
DEE.desc: A person who hides on a conveyance in order to obtain free passage.

DEF.name: Meat cutter
DEF.desc: Person whose job is to cut up and/or mince meat.

DEG.name: Consortium Carrier (maritime)
DEG.desc: A marine carrier that transports goods for more than one shipping line between named points.

DEH.name: Non-vessel operating carrier
DEH.desc: A carrier that does not operate the vessel.

DEI.name: Means of transport operator
DEI.desc: The operator of a means of transport, e.g. the captain of a vessel.

DEJ.name: Stuffing address
DEJ.desc: Address where cargo is loaded into the transport equipment e.g. container. Synonyms; vanning address / place of vanning.

DEK.name: Mooring service provider
DEK.desc: Party responsible for mooring the vessel at the berth in the port. Synonym: Boatmen.

DEL.name: Pilotage service provider
DEL.desc: Party responsible for the pilotage of the vessel.

DEM.name: Berth towage service provider
DEM.desc: Party responsible for towing the vessel to/from the berth in the port.

DEN.name: Agent/representative, direct representation
DEN.desc: Party authorised to act in the name and on behalf of another person.

DEO.name: Agent/representative, indirect representation
DEO.desc: Party authorised to act in its own name but on behalf of another person.

DEP.name: Stevedore
DEP.desc: A party which handles the loading and unloading of marine vessels from several terminals.

DEQ.name: Shipper
DEQ.desc: Party responsible for the shipment of goods.

DER.name: Source data pool
DER.desc: A data pool that supports the functionality required by a data source such as data loading, publication, notification, registration, etc.

DET.name: Cockpit crew
DET.desc: Cockpit crew and personnel inside cockpit.

DEU.name: Cabin crew
DEU.desc: Crew members operating in passenger cabin.

DEV.name: Airline operations management, not in cockpit
DEV.desc: Personnel of the airline operations management department positioned outside the cockpit.

DEW.name: Cargo non-cockpit crew and/or non-crew personnel
DEW.desc: Employees of the carrier, cargo groomers, or special cargo handlers, that are not authorized to ride in the cockpit.

DEY.name: Commercial verifier
DEY.desc: A party recognized under relevant legislation to undertake official verification.

DEZ.name: Authorized issuer
DEZ.desc: A person authorized under relevant legislation for the purpose of issuing official assurances.

DF.name: Documentary credit applicant
DF.desc: [3198] Party at whose request the applicant's bank/issuing bank is to issue a documentary credit.

DFA.name: Bank for deposit of duties/taxes/fees
DFA.desc: Bank that is authorized to receive the deposit for duties, taxes, and fees.

DFB.name: Company security officer (IMO Circular MSC 1130)
DFB.desc: The company security officer as described in IMO Circular MSC 1130.

DFD.name: Drayman/lighterman
DFD.desc: The bonded (insured) party that moves goods within port limits.

DFE.name: Exhibitor
DFE.desc: The party who offers items for exhibit or show.

DFF.name: Feedlot
DFF.desc: A commercial establishment that feeds livestock.

DFG.name: Government official
DFG.desc: A person appointed to some position of responsibility or authority in the government.

DFH.name: Government service requestor
DFH.desc: The party requesting inspection, grading, or other government service.

DFJ.name: ISPS Responsible Party
DFJ.desc: The responsible party as identified and defined in the International Ship and Port Facility Security Code (ISPS).

DFK.name: LPCO authorized party
DFK.desc: The party to whom the License, Permit, Certificate, or Other required document (LPCO) is issued.

DFL.name: Operator of property, registered
DFL.desc: The registered operator of the property.

DFM.name: Organic growth certifier, accredited
DFM.desc: An organization that is accredited to certify organic growth processes.

DFN.name: Party holding Certificate of Financial Responsibility
DFN.desc: The party holding the Certificate of Financial Responsibility (COFR).

DFO.name: Port facility security officer
DFO.desc: The individual (person) designated as the port facility security officer responsible for port security requirements.

DFQ.name: Security certificate issuer, recognized
DFQ.desc: Organization recogized for issuing security certificates.

DFR.name: Ship Security Officer
DFR.desc: The person who is appointed as Ship Security Officer (SSO).

DFS.name: Certificate issuer, veterinary
DFS.desc: The person who issues veterinary certificates.

DFT.name: Assembler
DFT.desc: The party putting together various components or parts into a product or commodity.

DFV.name: Right holder
DFV.desc: Party holding exclusive rights to a protected intellectual property.

DFW.name: Authorised Economic Operator (AEO)
DFW.desc: Party approved by Customs as complying with WCO or equivalent supply-chain security standards.

DG.name: Documentary credit beneficiary
DG.desc: Party in whose favour the documentary credit is to be issued and the party that must comply with the credit's terms and conditions.

DH.name: Documentary credit account party
DH.desc: Party which is responsible for the payment settlement of the documentary credit with the applicant's bank/issuing bank, if different from the documentary credit applicant.

DI.name: Documentary credit second beneficiary
DI.desc: Party to whom the documentary credit can be transferred.

DJ.name: Party according to documentary credit transaction
DJ.desc: Party related to documentary credit transaction.

DK.name: Documentary credit beneficiary's bank
DK.desc: Financial institution with which the beneficiary of the documentary credit maintains an account.

DL.name: Factor
DL.desc: Company offering a financial service whereby a firm sells or transfers title to its accounts receivable to the factoring company.

DM.name: Party to whom documents are to be presented
DM.desc: Party to whom documents are to be presented.

DO.name: Document recipient
DO.desc: [1370] Party which should receive a specified document.

DP.name: Delivery party
DP.desc: [3144] Party to which goods should be delivered, if not identical with consignee, such as the place where a container is to be, or has been, positioned.

DQ.name: Owner's agent
DQ.desc: Person acting on delegation of powers of the owner.

DR.name: Driver
DR.desc: Person who drives a means of transport.

DS.name: Distributor
DS.desc: Party distributing goods, financial payments or documents.

DT.name: Declarant
DT.desc: [3140] Party which makes a declaration to an official body or - where legally permitted - in whose name, or on whose behalf, a declaration to an official body is made.

DU.name: Owner's representative
DU.desc: Person commissioned by the owner to represent him in certain circumstances.

DV.name: Project management office
DV.desc: Party commissioned by the owner to follow through the execution of all works.

DW.name: Drawee
DW.desc: (3290) Party on whom drafts must be drawn.

D.name: Engineer (construction)
D.desc: Party representing the contractor to advise and supervise engineering aspects of the works.

DY.name: Engineer, resident (construction)
DY.desc: Party commissioned by the owner to advise and supervise engineering aspects of the works.

DZ.name: Architect
DZ.desc: A designer who prepares plans for buildings, ships, etc. and supervises their construction.

EB.name: Building inspectorate
EB.desc: Party controlling the conformity of works to legal and regulation rules.

EE.name: Location of goods for customs examination before clearance
EE.desc: The location where the goods are examined by customs before clearance.

EF.name: Project coordination office
EF.desc: Party responsible for technical coordination of works.

EI.name: Controller, quality
EI.desc: Party controlling the quality of goods and workmanship for the project.

EJ.name: Surveyor, quantity
EJ.desc: Party responsible for the quantification and valuation of the works on behalf of the contractor.

EK.name: Surveyor (professional), quantity
EK.desc: Party responsible to the owner for the quantification and valuation of the works.

EL.name: Project
EL.desc: Party responsible for a project, e.g. a construction project.

EM.name: Party to receive electronic memo of invoice
EM.desc: Party being informed about invoice issue (via EDI).

EN.name: Tenderer
EN.desc: Firm answering an invitation to tender.

EP.name: Equipment drop-off party
EP.desc: The party which drops off equipment.

EQ.name: Empty container responsible party
EQ.desc: Party responsible for the empty container.

ER.name: Empty container return agent
ER.desc: Party, designated by owner of containers, responsible for their collection as agreed between the owner and customer/ consignee.

ES.name: Contractor, lead
ES.desc: Leader representing a grouping of co-contractors.

ET.name: Co-contractor
ET.desc: Member of a grouping of co-contractors.

EU.name: Contractor, general
EU.desc: Single contractor for the whole construction project, working by his own or with subcontractors.

EV.name: Subcontractor
EV.desc: Firm carrying out a part of the works for a contractor.

E.name: Exporter
E.desc: [3030] Party who makes, or on whose behalf the export declaration is made, and who is the owner of the goods or has similar rights of disposal over them at the time when the declaration is accepted.

EY.name: Subcontractor, nominated
EY.desc: Subcontractor authorized by the owner after having been proposed.

EZ.name: Operator, essential services
EZ.desc: Operator of essential services e.g. water, sewerage system, power.

FB.name: Nominated freight company
FB.desc: Party nominated to act as transport company or carrier for the goods.

FC.name: Contractor, main
FC.desc: Firm or grouping of co-contractors which has been awarded the contract.

FE.name: Credit rating agency
FE.desc: A party which evaluates another party for credit rating.

FF.name: Factor, correspondent
FF.desc: Factoring company engaged by another factoring company to assist the letter with the services provided to the clients (sellers).

FG.name: Buyer as officially registered
FG.desc: Buying party as officially registered with government.

FH.name: Seller as officially registered
FH.desc: Selling party as officially registered with government.

FI.name: Copy message to
FI.desc: Party that is to receive a copy of a message.

FK.name: Previous Trade Union
FK.desc: Employee organisation who previously represented an employee .

FL.name: Passenger
FL.desc: A person conveyed by a means of transport, other than the crew.

FM.name: Crew member
FM.desc: A person manning a means of transport.

FN.name: Tariff issuer
FN.desc: [3363] The issuer of a tariff, e.g. a freight tariff.

FP.name: Freight/charges payer
FP.desc: Party responsible for the payment of freight.

FQ.name: Container survey agent
FQ.desc: The container survey agency that will survey the containers.

FR.name: Message from
FR.desc: Party where the message comes from.

FS.name: Party authorized to make definite a contract action
FS.desc: Party who has the authority to make definite a contract action.

FT.name: Financial settlement party
FT.desc: [3450] Party responsible for either the transfer or repatriation of the funds relating to a transaction.

FU.name: Hazardous material office
FU.desc: The office responsible for providing information regarding hazardous material.

FV.name: Party providing government furnished property
FV.desc: The party responsible for providing government furnished property.

F.name: Current receiver
F.desc: Current receiver of the goods in a multi-step transportation process (indirect flow) involving at least one grouping centre.

FY.name: Current sender
FY.desc: Current sender of the goods in a multi-step transportation process (indirect flow) involving at least one grouping centre.

FZ.name: Grouping centre
FZ.desc: A party in charge of groupage, including degroupage and regroupage.

GB.name: Chamber of commerce
GB.desc: Name of the Chamber of Commerce of the town where the company is registered.

GC.name: Goods custodian
GC.desc: [3024] Party responsible for the keeping of goods.

GD.name: Producer
GD.desc: Party or person who has produced the produce.

GE.name: Registration tribunal
GE.desc: Name of the tribunal where the company is registered.

GF.name: Slot charter party
GF.desc: An identification code of a participant or user that books slots (space) on a ship, more likely on a long term basis on a series of sailings. He pays for the space whether he uses it or not.

GH.name: Applicant for job
GH.desc: A person who applied for a job.

GL.name: Socially insured person
GL.desc: A person who is registered in a social security scheme.

GM.name: Inventory controller
GM.desc: To specifically identify the party in charge of inventory control.

GN.name: Processor
GN.desc: Party or person who has or will apply a process.

GO.name: Goods owner
GO.desc: The party which owns the goods.

GP.name: Packer
GP.desc: Party or person who has undertaken or will undertake packing.

GQ.name: Slaughterer
GQ.desc: Party or person who has undertaken or will undertake a slaughter.

GR.name: Goods releasing party
GR.desc: [3026] Party entitled to authorize release of goods from custodian.

GS.name: Consignor's representative
GS.desc: Party authorised to represent the consignor.

GT.name: Rail carrier
GT.desc: A carrier moving cargo, including containers, via rail.

GU.name: Originator of article number
GU.desc: A code identifying the party which created a specific article number.

GV.name: Procurement responsibility for order
GV.desc: A code used to identify the organization which is responsible for the procurement.

GW.name: Party fulfilling all operations
GW.desc: Code indicating the fact that the party identified carries out all operations within that company's activities.

GZ.name: Substitute supplier
GZ.desc: Party which may be in a position to supply products or services should the main usual supplier be unable to do so.

HA.name: Party which delivers consignments to the terminal
HA.desc: Party which delivers consignments to a terminal.

HB.name: Party which picks up consignments from the terminal
HB.desc: Party which picks up consignments from a terminal.

HC.name: Transit freight forwarder
HC.desc: Freight forwarder to whom transit consignments are addressed, and from whom they are to be on-forwarded.

HD.name: Inspection and acceptance party
HD.desc: The party who will perform inspection and acceptance.

HE.name: Transportation office
HE.desc: The office that provides transportation information.

HF.name: Contract administration office
HF.desc: The office responsible for the administration of a contract.

HH.name: Audit office
HH.desc: The office responsible for conducting audits.

HJ.name: Foreign disclosure information office
HJ.desc: The office that reviews sensitive information for foreign disclosure.

HK.name: Mark-for party
HK.desc: The party within an organization for whom the material is marked to be delivered.

HL.name: Party to receive reports
HL.desc: The party to whom reports are to be submitted.

HM.name: Alternative manufacturer
HM.desc: Party identification of an alternative manufacturer for a product.

HN.name: Service performer
HN.desc: The party who is performing a service.

HP.name: Final message recipient
HP.desc: To identify the final recipient of the message.

HQ.name: Account owner
HQ.desc: Identifies the owner of the account.

HR.name: Shipping line service
HR.desc: Identifies the shipping line service organization.

HS.name: Creditor
HS.desc: Party to whom payment is due.

HT.name: Clearing house
HT.desc: Institution through which funds will be paid.

HU.name: Ordering bank
HU.desc: Bank which instructed the sender to act on the transaction(s).

HV.name: Receiver of funds
HV.desc: Identifies the financial party that receives the funds.

HW.name: Sender of funds
HW.desc: Identifies the party that sends the funds.

H.name: Debtor
H.desc: Party from whom payment is due.

HY.name: Presenting bank
HY.desc: The bank which presents documents to the drawee.

I1.name: Intermediary bank 1
I1.desc: A financial institution between the ordered bank and the beneficiary's bank.

I2.name: Intermediary bank 2
I2.desc: A financial institution between the ordered bank and the beneficiary's bank.

IB.name: Intermediary/broker
IB.desc: A person intervening between parties to produce agreement or reconciliation.

ID.name: Replacing manufacturer
ID.desc: A code used to identify a party who replaces the previous party for the manufacture of an article.

IE.name: Non-resident third party company with whom financial account is held
IE.desc: Identifies the non-resident third party company with whom the financial account is held.

IF.name: Non-resident group company with whom financial account is held
IF.desc: Identifies the non-resident group company with whom the financial account is held.

IG.name: Non-resident beneficiary
IG.desc: The ultimate non-resident recipient of the funds. Normally the account owner who is reimbursed by the payer.

IH.name: Resident beneficiary
IH.desc: The ultimate resident recipient of the funds. Normally the account owner who is reimbursed by the payer.

IJ.name: Non-resident instructing party
IJ.desc: Identifies the non-resident party originating the instruction.

IL.name: Resident instructing party
IL.desc: Identifies the resident party originating the instruction.

IM.name: Importer
IM.desc: [3020] Party who makes - or on whose behalf a Customs clearing agent or other authorized person makes - an import declaration. This may include a person who has possession of the goods or to whom the goods are consigned.

IN.name: Insurer
IN.desc: [3070] A person or company offering insurance policies for premiums.

IO.name: Insurance company
IO.desc: A company engaged in the business of insurance.

IP.name: Insurance claim adjuster
IP.desc: [3360] A party which adjusts losses on behalf of an insurer.

IQ.name: Domestic financial institution
IQ.desc: Domestic party acting as financial institution.

IR.name: Non-domestic financial institution
IR.desc: Non-domestic party acting as financial institution.

IS.name: Party to receive certified inspection report
IS.desc: Party (at buyer) to receive certified inspection report.

IT.name: Installation on site
IT.desc: A party who possesses the site on which an installation shall be made.

IU.name: Non-resident debtor
IU.desc: Non-resident party who makes the payment or against whom a claim exists.

IV.name: Invoicee
IV.desc: [3006] Party to whom an invoice is issued.

IW.name: Non-resident creditor
IW.desc: Non-resident party receiving the payment or against whom a liability exists.

I.name: Supplier work team
I.desc: The supplier's team responsible for performing the work.

IY.name: Tenant manager
IY.desc: A code to identify the party who rents the rights to use the goodwill and facilities of an enterprise.

IZ.name: Party mandated to liquidate an enterprise
IZ.desc: A code to identify the party who has been legally mandated to sell off an enterprise.

JA.name: Certified accountant
JA.desc: Code identifying the party as a certified accountant.

JB.name: Goods collection party
JB.desc: Party that will collect or has collected the goods.

JC.name: Party at final place of positioning
JC.desc: Identifies the party at the final place of positioning.

JD.name: Customs office of clearance
JD.desc: Identifies the office where customs clearance procedures take place.

JE.name: Party from whom customs documents are to be picked up
JE.desc: Identification of the party from whom customs documents are to be picked up.

JF.name: Party from whom non-customs documents are to be picked up
JF.desc: Identification of the party from whom non-customs documents are to be picked up.

JG.name: Party to receive customs documents
JG.desc: Identification of the party to whom customs documents are to be delivered.

JH.name: Party to receive non-customs documents
JH.desc: Identification of the party to whom non-customs documents are to be delivered.

LA.name: Party designated to provide living animal care
LA.desc: Party responsible to take care of transported living animals.

LB.name: Co-producer
LB.desc: A code used to identify a party who participates in production.

LC.name: Party declaring the Value Added Tax (VAT)
LC.desc: A code to identify the party who is responsible for declaring the Value Added Tax (VAT) on the sale of goods or services.

LD.name: Party recovering the Value Added Tax (VAT)
LD.desc: A code to identify the party who is eligible to recover the Value Added Tax (VAT) on the sale of goods or services.

LE.name: Person on claim
LE.desc: To identify the person who is the subject of the claim.

LF.name: Buyer's corporate office
LF.desc: The identification of the buyer's corporate office.

LG.name: Supplier's corporate office
LG.desc: The identification of the supplier's corporate office.

LH.name: Liquidator
LH.desc: The party responsible for settling or paying a debt.

LI.name: Account coordinator
LI.desc: An individual with coordination responsibilities for a specific account.

LJ.name: Inspection leader
LJ.desc: An individual responsible for an inspection team.

LK.name: Patient
LK.desc: A person receiving or registered to receive medical treatment.

LM.name: Medical treatment executant
LM.desc: The party who executes a medical treatment.

LO.name: Medical treatment prescriber
LO.desc: The party who prescribes a medical treatment.

LP.name: Loading party
LP.desc: Party responsible for the loading when other than carrier.

LQ.name: Debt payment authorisation party
LQ.desc: A party which authorises the payment of a debt.

LS.name: Product services and repairs centre
LS.desc: A centre which services and repairs products.

LU.name: Entry point technical assessment group
LU.desc: Party acts as an entry point for technical assessment.

LV.name: Party assigning a status
LV.desc: Party responsible for assigning a status.

MA.name: Party for whom item is ultimately intended
MA.desc: Party for whom item is ultimately intended.

MAD.name: Meter administrator
MAD.desc: A party responsible for keeping a register of meters and related characteristics.

MDR.name: Metered data responsible
MDR.desc: A party responsible for the establishment and validation of metered data received from the Metered Data Collector.

MG.name: Party designated to execute re-icing
MG.desc: Party designated to execute re-icing, selected in the official list of mandatories competent for this kind of operation.

MI.name: Planning schedule/material release issuer
MI.desc: A party issuing a planning schedule/material release.

MP.name: Manufacturing unit
MP.desc: A party acting as a particular production unit of a manufacturer.

MR.name: Message recipient
MR.desc: A party to receive a message or messages.

MS.name: Document/message issuer/sender
MS.desc: [3522] Issuer of a document and/or sender of a message.

MT.name: Party designated to execute sanitary procedures
MT.desc: A party which is designated to execute sanitary procedures.

N2.name: Notify party no. 2
N2.desc: [3376] The second party which is to be notified.

NI.name: Notify party
NI.desc: [3180] Party to be notified. Synonym: Notify party No. 1.

OA.name: Break bulk berth operator
OA.desc: Party who offers facilities for berthing of vessels, handling and storage of break bulk cargo.

OC.name: Party data responsible party
OC.desc: The party responsible for all party data.

OD.name: Equipment repair party
OD.desc: A party making repairs to equipment.

OF.name: On behalf of
OF.desc: Party on behalf of which an action is executed.

OG.name: Owner or lessor's surveyor
OG.desc: Surveyor hired by the owner or lessor of the item.

OH.name: Lessee's surveyor
OH.desc: Surveyor hired by the lessee of the item.

OI.name: Outside inspection agency
OI.desc: Third party inspecting goods or equipment.

OJ.name: Third party
OJ.desc: Another party besides the two principals.

OK.name: Receiver's sub-entity
OK.desc: Identifies a sub-entity within the receiver's organization.

OL.name: Case of need party
OL.desc: Party to be approached in case of difficulty.

OM.name: Collecting bank
OM.desc: Any bank, other than the remitting bank, involved in processing the collection.

ON.name: Remitting bank
ON.desc: The bank to which the principal has entrusted the handling of a collection.

OO.name: Order of the shipper party
OO.desc: The owner of goods under consignment which are moving under a negotiable transport document and will only be released upon receipt of the original transport document.

OP.name: Operator of property or equipment
OP.desc: (3174) The party which operates property or a unit of equipment.

OQ.name: Collection principal
OQ.desc: The party entrusting the handling of a collection to a bank.

OR.name: Ordered bank
OR.desc: Identifies the bank servicing the account for the ordering customer or payer.

OS.name: Original shipper
OS.desc: The original supplier of the goods.

OT.name: Outside test agency
OT.desc: Third party testing goods, equipment or services.

OU.name: Account owner's servicing bank on the sending side
OU.desc: Identifies the financial institution on the sending side which services the account owner's bank account(s).

OV.name: Transport means owner
OV.desc: Party owning the means of transport. No synonym of carrier (= CA).

OW.name: Account owner's servicing bank on the receiving side
OW.desc: Identifies the financial institution on the receiving side which services the account owner's bank account(s).

O.name: Sender's correspondent bank
O.desc: The account, or branch of the sender, or another financial institution, through which the sender will reimburse the receiver.

OY.name: Ordering customer
OY.desc: Identifies the originator of the instruction.

OZ.name: Receiver's correspondent bank
OZ.desc: The branch of the receiver, or another financial institution, at which the funds will be made available to the receiver.

PA.name: Party to receive inspection report
PA.desc: Party to whom the inspection report should be sent.

PB.name: Paying financial institution
PB.desc: Financial institution designated to make payment.

PC.name: Actual purchaser's customer
PC.desc: Party the purchaser within the actual message is selling the ordered goods or services to.

PE.name: Payee
PE.desc: Identifies the credit party when other than the beneficiary.

PF.name: Party to receive freight bill
PF.desc: Party to whom the freight bill should be sent.

PG.name: Prime contractor
PG.desc: Party responsible for the whole project if other than the buyer.

PH.name: Payer's financial institution
PH.desc: Institution chosen by the payer to execute financial transactions on his behalf.

1.name: Place of terms of delivery
