FN.desc: Reference number assigned by issuing party to a freight bill.

FO.name: Foreign exchange
FO.desc: Exchange of two currencies at an agreed rate.

FS.name: Final sequence number
FS.desc: A number that identifies the final sequence.

FT.name: Free zone identifier
FT.desc: Identifier to specify the territory of a State where any goods introduced are generally regarded, insofar as import duties and taxes are concerned, as being outside the Customs territory and are not subject to usual Customs control (CCC).

FV.name: File version number
FV.desc: Number given to a version of an identified file.

F.name: Foreign exchange contract number
F.desc: Reference number identifying a foreign exchange contract.

GA.name: Standard's number
GA.desc: Number to identify a standardization description (e.g. ISO 9375).

GC.name: Government contract number
GC.desc: Number assigned to a specific government/public contract.

GD.name: Standard's code number
GD.desc: Number to identify a specific parameter within a standardization description (e.g. M5 for screws or DIN A4 for paper).

GDN.name: General declaration number
GDN.desc: Number of the declaration of incoming goods out of a vessel.

GN.name: Government reference number
GN.desc: A number that identifies a government reference.

HS.name: Harmonised system number
HS.desc: Number specifying the goods classification under the Harmonised Commodity Description and Coding System of the Customs Co-operation Council (CCC).

HWB.name: House waybill number
HWB.desc: Reference number assigned to a house waybill, see: 1001 = 703.

IA.name: Internal vendor number
IA.desc: Number identifying the company-internal vending department/unit.

IB.name: In bond number
IB.desc: Customs assigned number that is used to control the movement of imported cargo prior to its formal Customs clearing.

ICA.name: IATA cargo agent code number
ICA.desc: Code issued by IATA identify each IATA Cargo Agent whose name is entered on the Cargo Agency List.

ICE.name: Insurance certificate reference number
ICE.desc: A number that identifies an insurance certificate reference.

ICO.name: Insurance contract reference number
ICO.desc: A number that identifies an insurance contract reference.

II.name: Initial sample inspection report number
II.desc: Inspection report number given to the initial sample inspection.

IL.name: Internal order number
IL.desc: Number assigned to an order for internal handling/follow up.

INB.name: Intermediary broker
INB.desc: A number that identifies an intermediary broker.

INN.name: Interchange number new
INN.desc: Number assigned by the interchange sender to identify one specific interchange. This number points to the actual interchange.

INO.name: Interchange number old
INO.desc: Number assigned by the interchange sender to identify one specific interchange. This number points to the previous interchange.

IP.name: Import permit identifier
IP.desc: [1107] Reference number to identify an import licence or permit.

IS.name: Invoice number suffix
IS.desc: A number added at the end of an invoice number.

IT.name: Internal customer number
IT.desc: Number assigned by a seller, supplier etc. to identify a customer within his enterprise.

IV.name: Invoice document identifier
IV.desc: [1334] Reference number to identify an invoice.

JE.name: Ending job sequence number
JE.desc: A number that identifies the ending job sequence.

LA.name: Shipping label serial number
LA.desc: The serial number on a shipping label.

LAN.name: Loading authorisation identifier
LAN.desc: [4092] Identifier assigned to the loading authorisation granted by the forwarding location e.g. railway or airport, when the consignment is subject to traffic limitations.

LAR.name: Lower number in range
LAR.desc: Lower number in a range of numbers.

LB.name: Lockbox
LB.desc: Type of cash management system offered by financial institutions to provide for collection of customers 'receivables'.

LC.name: Letter of credit number
LC.desc: Reference number identifying the letter of credit document.

LI.name: Document line identifier
LI.desc: [1156] To identify a line of a document.

LO.name: Load planning number
LO.desc: The reference that identifies the load planning number.

LRC.name: Reservation office identifier
LRC.desc: Reference to the office where a reservation was made.

LS.name: Bar coded label serial number
LS.desc: The serial number on a bar code label.

MA.name: Ship notice/manifest number
MA.desc: The number assigned to a ship notice or manifest.

MB.name: Master bill of lading number
MB.desc: Reference number assigned to a master bill of lading, see: 1001 = 704.

MF.name: Manufacturer's part number
MF.desc: Reference number assigned by the manufacturer to his product or part.

MG.name: Meter unit number
MG.desc: Number identifying a unique meter unit.

MH.name: Manufacturing order number
MH.desc: Reference number assigned by manufacturer for a given production quantity of products.

MR.name: Message recipient
MR.desc: A number that identifies the message recipient.

MRN.name: Mailing reference number
MRN.desc: Identifies the party designated by the importer to receive certain customs correspondence in lieu of its being mailed directly to the importer.

MS.name: Message sender
MS.desc: A number that identifies the message sender.

MSS.name: Manufacturer's material safety data sheet number
MSS.desc: A number that identifies a manufacturer's material safety data sheet.

MWB.name: Master air waybill number
MWB.desc: Reference number assigned to a master air waybill, see: 1001 = 741.

NA.name: North American hazardous goods classification number
NA.desc: Reference to materials designated as hazardous for purposes of transportation in North American commerce.

NF.name: Nota Fiscal
NF.desc: Nota Fiscal is a registration number for shipments / deliveries within Brazil, issued by the local tax authorities and mandated for each shipment.

OH.name: Current invoice number
OH.desc: Reference number identifying the current invoice.

OI.name: Previous invoice number
OI.desc: Reference number identifying a previously issued invoice.

ON.name: Order document identifier, buyer assigned
ON.desc: [1022] Identifier assigned by the buyer to an order.

OP.name: Original purchase order
OP.desc: Reference to the order previously sent.

OR.name: General order number
OR.desc: Customs number assigned to imported merchandise that has been left unclaimed and subsequently moved to a Customs bonded warehouse for storage.

PB.name: Payer's financial institution account number
PB.desc: Originated company account number (ACH transfer), check, draft or wire.

PC.name: Production code
PC.desc: Number assigned by the manufacturer to a specified article or batch to identify the manufacturing date etc. for subsequent reference.

PD.name: Promotion deal number
PD.desc: Number assigned by a vendor to a special promotion activity.

PE.name: Plant number
PE.desc: A number that identifies a plant.

PF.name: Prime contractor contract number
PF.desc: Reference number assigned by the client to the contract of the prime contractor.

PI.name: Price list version number
PI.desc: A number that identifies the version of a price list.

PK.name: Packing list number
PK.desc: [1014] Reference number assigned to a packing list.

PL.name: Price list number
PL.desc: Reference number assigned to a price list.

POR.name: Purchase order response number
POR.desc: Reference number assigned by the seller to an order response.

PP.name: Purchase order change number
PP.desc: Reference number assigned by a buyer for a revision of a purchase order.

PQ.name: Payment reference
PQ.desc: Reference number assigned to a payment.

PR.name: Price quote number
PR.desc: Reference number assigned by the seller to a quote.

PS.name: Purchase order number suffix
PS.desc: A number added at the end of a purchase order number.

PW.name: Prior purchase order number
PW.desc: Reference number of a purchase order previously sent to the supplier.

PY.name: Payee's financial institution account number
PY.desc: Receiving company account number (ACH transfer), check, draft or wire.

RA.name: Remittance advice number
RA.desc: A number that identifies a remittance advice.

RC.name: Rail/road routing code
RC.desc: International Western and Eastern European route code used in all rail organizations and specified in the international tariffs (rail tariffs) known by the customers.

RCN.name: Railway consignment note number
RCN.desc: Reference number assigned to a rail consignment note, see: 1001 = 720.

RE.name: Release number
RE.desc: Reference number assigned to identify a release of a set of rules, conventions, conditions, etc.

REN.name: Consignment receipt identifier
REN.desc: [1150] Reference number assigned to identify a consignment upon its arrival at its destination.

RF.name: Export reference number
RF.desc: Reference number given to an export shipment.

RR.name: Payer's financial institution transit routing No.(ACH transfers)

RT.name: Payee's financial institution transit routing No.

SA.name: Sales person number
SA.desc: Identification number of a sales person.

SB.name: Sales region number
SB.desc: A number that identifies a sales region.

SD.name: Sales department number
SD.desc: A number that identifies a sales department.

SE.name: Serial number
SE.desc: Identification number of an item which distinguishes this specific item out of an number of identical items.

SEA.name: Allocated seat
SEA.desc: Reference to a seat allocated to a passenger.

SF.name: Ship from
SF.desc: A number that identifies a ship from location.

SH.name: Previous highest schedule number
SH.desc: Number of the latest schedule of a previous period (ODETTE DELINS).

SI.name: SID (Shipper's identifying number for shipment)
SI.desc: A number that identifies the SID (shipper's identification) number for a shipment.

SM.name: Sales office number
SM.desc: A number that identifies a sales office.

SN.name: Transport equipment seal identifier
SN.desc: [9308] The identification number of a seal affixed to a piece of transport equipment.

SP.name: Scan line
SP.desc: A number that identifies a scan line.

SQ.name: Equipment sequence number
SQ.desc: (1492) A temporary reference number identifying a particular piece of equipment within a series of pieces of equipment.

SRN.name: Shipment reference number
SRN.desc: [1065] Reference number assigned to a shipment.

SS.name: Sellers reference number
SS.desc: Reference number assigned to a transaction by the seller.

STA.name: Station reference number
STA.desc: International UIC code assigned to every European rail station (CIM convention).

SW.name: Swap order number
SW.desc: Number assigned by the seller to a swap order (see definition of DE 1001, code 229).

SZ.name: Specification number
SZ.desc: Number assigned by the issuer to his specification.

TB.name: Trucker's bill of lading
TB.desc: A cargo list/description issued by a motor carrier of freight.

TCR.name: Terminal operator's consignment reference
TCR.desc: Reference assigned to a consignment by the terminal operator.

TE.name: Telex message number
TE.desc: Reference number identifying a telex message.

TF.name: Transfer number
TF.desc: An extra number assigned to goods or a container which functions as a reference number or as an authorization number to get the goods or container released from a certain party.

TI.name: TIR carnet number
TI.desc: Reference number assigned to a TIR carnet.

TIN.name: Transport instruction number
TIN.desc: Reference number identifying a transport instruction.

TL.name: Tax exemption licence number
TL.desc: Number assigned by the tax authorities to a party indicating its tax exemption authorization. This number could relate to a specified business type, a specified local area or a class of products.

TN.name: Transaction reference number
TN.desc: Reference applied to a transaction between two or more parties over a defined life cycle; e.g. number applied by importer or broker to obtain release from Customs, may then used to control declaration through final accounting (synonyms: declaration, entry number).

TP.name: Test report number
TP.desc: Reference number identifying a test report document relevant to the product.

UAR.name: Upper number of range
UAR.desc: Upper number in a range of numbers.

UC.name: Ultimate customer's reference number
UC.desc: The originator's reference number as forwarded in a sequence of parties involved.

UCN.name: Unique consignment reference number
UCN.desc: [1202] Unique reference identifying a particular consignment of goods. Synonym: UCR, UCRN.

UN.name: United Nations Dangerous Goods identifier
UN.desc: [7124] United Nations Dangerous Goods Identifier (UNDG) is the unique serial number assigned within the United Nations to substances and articles contained in a list of the dangerous goods most commonly carried.

UO.name: Ultimate customer's order number
UO.desc: The originator's order number as forwarded in a sequence of parties involved.

URI.name: Uniform Resource Identifier
URI.desc: A string of characters used to identify a name of a resource on the worldwide web.

VA.name: VAT registration number
VA.desc: Unique number assigned by the relevant tax authority to identify a party for use in relation to Value Added Tax (VAT).

VC.name: Vendor contract number
VC.desc: Number assigned by the vendor to a contract.

VGR.name: Transport equipment gross mass verification reference number
VGR.desc: Reference number identifying the documentation of a transport equipment gross mass (weight) verification.

VN.name: Order number (vendor)
VN.desc: Reference number assigned by supplier to a buyer's purchase order.

VON.name: Voyage number
VON.desc: (8028) Reference number assigned to the voyage of the vessel.

VOR.name: Transport equipment gross mass verification order reference
VOR.desc: Reference number identifying the order for obtaining a Verified Gross Mass (weight) of a packed transport equipment as per SOLAS Chapter VI, Regulation 2, paragraphs 4-6.

VP.name: Vendor product number
VP.desc: Number assigned by vendor to another manufacturer's product.

VR.name: Vendor ID number
VR.desc: A number that identifies a vendor's identification.

VS.name: Vendor order number suffix
VS.desc: The suffix for a vendor order number.

VT.name: Motor vehicle identification number
VT.desc: (8213) Reference identifying a motor vehicle used for transport. Normally is the vehicle registration number.

WE.name: Warehouse entry number
WE.desc: Entry number under which imported merchandise was placed in a Customs bonded warehouse.

WM.name: Weight agreement number
WM.desc: A number identifying a weight agreement.

WN.name: Well number
WN.desc: A number assigned to a shaft sunk into the ground.

WR.name: Warehouse receipt number
WR.desc: A number identifying a warehouse receipt.

WS.name: Warehouse storage location number
WS.desc: A number identifying a warehouse storage location.

WY.name: Rail waybill number
WY.desc: The number on a rail waybill.

A.name: Company/place registration number
A.desc: Company registration and place as legally required.

C.name: Cargo control number
C.desc: Reference used to identify and control a carrier and consignment from initial entry into a country until release of the cargo by Customs.

P.name: Previous cargo control number
P.desc: Where a consignment is deconsolidated and/or transferred to the control of another carrier or freight forwarder (e.g. housebill, abstract) this references the previous (e.g. master) cargo control number.

ZZZ.name: Mutually defined reference number
ZZZ.desc: Number based on party agreement.

2.name: Broadcast 2
2.desc: Report from workstation 2.

3.name: Manufacturer sequence number
3.desc: The manufacturer's plant requesting the delivery of the item has allocated the sequence number.

4.name: Manufacturer production sequence number
4.desc: The plant requesting the delivery of an item assigns a number indicating the sequence of the finished article.

5.name: Transmission sequence
5.desc: The positional sequence when transmitted.

6.name: Structure sequence
6.desc: The positional sequence in a message structure as published in a particular UN directory.

2.desc: Message containing items to be added.

3.desc: Message containing items to be deleted.

4.name: Change
4.desc: Message containing items to be changed.

5.desc: Message replacing a previous message.

6.desc: Message confirming the details of a previous transmission where such confirmation is required or recommended under the terms of a trading partner agreement.

7.name: Duplicate
7.desc: The message is a duplicate of a previously generated message.

8.name: Status
8.desc: Code indicating that the referenced message is a status.

9.name: Original
9.desc: Initial transmission related to a given transaction.

10.name: Not found
10.desc: Message whose reference number is not filed.

11.name: Response
11.desc: Message responding to a previous message or document.

12.desc: Message indicating that the referenced message was received but not yet processed.

13.desc: Code indicating that the referenced message is a request.

14.desc: Code indicating that the information contained in the message is an advance notification of information to follow.

15.desc: Repeated message transmission for reminding purposes.

16.name: Proposal
16.desc: Message content is a proposal.

17.name: Cancel, to be reissued
17.desc: Referenced transaction cancelled, reissued message will follow.

18.desc: New issue of a previous message (maybe cancelled).

19.name: Seller initiated change
19.desc: Change information submitted by buyer but initiated by seller.

20.desc: Message to replace the heading of a previous message.

23.desc: Message not to be processed until further release information.

24.desc: Delivery schedule message only used to transmit short- term delivery instructions.

25.desc: Delivery schedule message only used to transmit long- term schedule information.

26.desc: Combination of codes '24' and '25'.

27.desc: Message to inform that the referenced message is not accepted by the recipient.

29.desc: Referenced message is entirely accepted.

30.name: Accepted, with amendment in detail section
30.desc: Referenced message is accepted but amended in detail section.

32.desc: A message releasing an existing referenced message for action to the receiver.

33.name: Change in heading section
33.desc: Message changing the referenced message heading section.

34.name: Accepted with amendment
34.desc: The referenced message is accepted but amended.

35.name: Retransmission
35.desc: Change-free transmission of a message previously sent.

36.name: Change in detail section
36.desc: Message changing referenced detail section.

37.desc: Reversal of a previously posted debit.

38.name: Reversal of a credit
38.desc: Reversal of a previously posted credit.

39.desc: Code indicating that the referenced message is reversing a cancellation of a previous transmission for a given transaction.

40.desc: The message is given to inform the recipient to delete the referenced transaction.

41.desc: Last of series of call-offs.

42.desc: Message confirming a transaction previously agreed via other means (e.g. phone).

44.desc: Message accepted without reserves.

45.desc: Message accepted with reserves.

46.desc: Message content is provisional.

47.desc: Message content is definitive.

52.desc: A code used to indicate an amendment suggested by the sender.

53.desc: Code indicating the message is to be considered as a test.

54.desc: A subset of the original.

55.desc: The receiver may use the notification information for analysis only.

57.desc: An advice that items are pending to be booked in the ledger.

58.desc: A pre-advice that items require further information.

59.name: Pre-adviced items
59.desc: A pre-advice of items.

60.desc: Code indicating the fact that no action has taken place since the last message.

61.name: Complete schedule
61.desc: The message function is a complete schedule.

62.name: Update schedule
62.desc: The message function is an update to a schedule.

63.name: Not accepted, provisional
63.desc: Not accepted, subject to confirmation.

64.name: Verification
64.desc: The message is transmitted to verify information.

65.name: Unsettled dispute
65.desc: To report an unsettled dispute.

66.desc: A message related to a guarantee containing information about the discharge of an operation.

67.desc: A message related to a guarantee containing information about the termination of an operation.

68.desc: A message related to a guarantee containing information about the start of an operation.

69.desc: A message related to a guarantee containing advanced cargo information.
