EI.name: EDI transmission
EI.desc: Number identifying the service and service user.

EM.name: Electronic mail
EM.desc: Exchange of mail by electronic means.

E.name: Extension
E.desc: Telephone extension.

F.name: Telefax X.400
F.desc: Device used for transmitting and reproducing fixed graphic material (as printing) by means of signals over telephone lines or other electronic transmission media. CCITT Message handling system.

GM.name: GEIS (General Electric Information Service) mailbox
GM.desc: GEIS mailbox system is used as communication medium.

IE.name: IBM information exchange
IE.desc: IBM IE is used as communication medium.

PB.name: Postbox no.
PB.desc: Postbox system is used as communication medium.

PS.name: Packet switching
PS.desc: The process of routing and transferring data by means of addressed packets so that a channel is occupied only during the transmission; upon completion of the transmission the channel is made available for the transfer of other packets (ISO).

SW.name: S.W.I.F.T.
SW.desc: Communications address assigned by Society for Worldwide Interbank Financial Telecommunications s.c.

TT.name: Teletext
TT.desc: Transmission of text/data via teletext. Communication service involving Teletypewriter machines connected by wire or electronic transmission media. Teletypewriter machines are the devices used to send and receive signals and produce hardcopy from them.

AA.name: Circuit switching
AA.desc: A process that, on demand, connects two or more data terminal equipments and permits the exclusive use of a data circuit between them until the connection is released (ISO).

AB.name: SITA
AB.desc: Communications number assigned by Societe Internationale de Telecommunications Aeronautiques (SITA).

AC.name: ARINC
AC.desc: Communications number assigned by Aeronautical Radio Inc.

AD.name: AT&T mailbox
AD.desc: AT&T mailbox identifier.

AE.name: Peripheral device
AE.desc: Peripheral device identification.

AF.name: U.S. Defense Switched Network
AF.desc: The switched telecommunications network of the United States Department of Defense.

AG.name: U.S. federal telecommunications system
AG.desc: The switched telecommunications network of the United States government.

AH.name: World Wide Web
AH.desc: Data exchange via the World Wide Web.

AI.name: International calling country code
AI.desc: Identifies that portion of an international telephone number representing the country code to be used when calling internationally.

AJ.name: Alternate telephone
AJ.desc: Identifies the alternate telephone number.

AK.name: Videotex number
AK.desc: Code that identifies the communications number for the online videotex service.

AL.name: Cellular phone
AL.desc: Identifies the cellular phone number.

AM.name: International telephone direct line
AM.desc: The international telephone direct line number.

AN.name: O.F.T.P. (ODETTE File Transfer Protocol)
AN.desc: ODETTE File Transfer Protocol.

AO.name: Uniform Resource Location (URL)
AO.desc: Identification of the Uniform Resource Location (URL) Synonym: World wide web address.

AP.name: Very High Frequency (VHF) radio telephone
AP.desc: VHF radio telephone.

AQ.name: X.400 address for mail text
AQ.desc: The X.400 address accepting information in the body text of a message.

AR.name: AS1 address
AR.desc: Address capable of receiving messages in accordance with the EDIINT/AS1 protocol for MIME based EDI .

AS.name: AS2 address
AS.desc: Address capable of receiving messages in accordance with the EDIINT/AS2 protocol.

AT.name: AS3 address
AT.desc: Address capable of receiving messages in accordance with the EDIINT/AS3 protocol.

AU.name: File Transfer Protocol
AU.desc: Address capable for receiving message in accordance with the File Transfer Protocol (IETF RFC 959 et. al.).

AW.name: Radio communication call sign
AW.desc: Contact number for radio communication based on call sign.

CA.name: Cable address
CA.desc: The communication number identifies a cable address.

EI.name: EDI transmission
EI.desc: Number identifying the service and service user.

EM.name: Electronic mail
EM.desc: Exchange of mail by electronic means.

E.name: Extension
E.desc: Telephone extension.

F.name: Telefax X.400 address
F.desc: Device used for transmitting and reproducing fixed graphic material (as printing) by means of signals over telephone lines or other electronic transmission media. The X.400 address.

GM.name: GEIS (General Electric Information Service) mailbox
GM.desc: The communication number identifies a GEIS mailbox.

IE.name: IBM information exchange
IE.desc: The communication number identifies an IBM IE mailbox.

PB.name: Postbox number
PB.desc: The communication number identifies a postbox.

PS.name: Packet switching
PS.desc: The process of routing and transferring data by means of addressed packets so that a channel is occupied only during the transmission; upon completion of the transmission the channel is made available for the transfer of other packets (ISO).

SW.name: S.W.I.F.T.
SW.desc: Communications address assigned by Society for Worldwide Interbank Financial Telecommunications s.c.

TT.name: Teletext
TT.desc: Transmission of text/data via teletext. Communication service involving Teletypewriter machines connected by wire or electronic transmission media. Teletypewriter machines are the devices used to send and receive signals and produce hardcopy from them.

G.name: Pager
G.desc: Identifies that the communication number is for a pager.

I.name: National telephone direct line
I.desc: The national telephone direct line number.

1.name: Place of terms of delivery
1.desc: (3018) Point or port of departure, shipment or destination, as required under the applicable terms of delivery, e.g. Incoterms.

2.name: Payment location
2.desc: [3109] To identify the place where the payment has been or should be made.

3.name: Tare check place
3.desc: Place where equipment tare has been or must be checked for official assessment.

4.name: Goods receipt place
4.desc: [3160] Place at which the goods have been received.

5.name: Place of departure
5.desc: (3214) Port, airport or other location from which a means of transport or transport equipment is scheduled to depart or has departed.

6.name: Ward bed
6.desc: A bed in a ward.

7.name: Place of delivery
7.desc: (3246) Place to which the goods are to be finally delivered under transport contract terms (operational term).

8.name: Place of destination
8.desc: (3258) Port, airport or other location to which a means of transport or transport equipment is destined.

9.name: Place of loading
9.desc: [3334] Seaport, airport, freight terminal, rail station or other place at which the goods (cargo) are loaded on to the means of transport being used for their carriage.

10.name: Place of acceptance
10.desc: [3348] Place where the goods are taken over by the carrier.

11.name: Place of discharge
11.desc: [3392] Seaport, airport, freight terminal, rail station or other place at which goods are unloaded from the means of transport having been used for their carriage.

12.name: Port of discharge
12.desc: Port at which the goods are discharged from the vessel used for their transport.

13.name: Place of transhipment
13.desc: [3424] Place where goods are to be or have been transferred from one means of transport to another during the course of one transport operation.

14.name: Goods item storage location
14.desc: [3385] To identify the place where a goods item is located.

15.name: Place of transfer responsibility
15.desc: Place where the responsibility is transferred.

16.name: Place of transfer of ownership
16.desc: Place where the ownership of the goods is transferred.

17.name: Border crossing place
17.desc: Place where goods are transported across a country border.

18.name: Warehouse
18.desc: [3156] Warehouse where a particular consignment is to be or has been stored.

19.name: Factory/plant
19.desc: Factory/plant relevant for a particular consignment.

20.name: Place of ultimate destination of goods
20.desc: Place where goods will ultimately be delivered.

21.name: Terms of sale place
21.desc: Place of departure, shipment or destination as specified in the terms of sale agreed between the parties.

22.name: Customs clearance location
22.desc: [3080] Place at which Customs clearance should or has taken place.

23.name: Port of release
23.desc: Port where goods are released from Customs custody.

24.name: Port of entry
24.desc: Port where final documentation is filed for Customs Entry processing.

25.name: Country
25.desc: Country relevant for a particular transaction.

26.name: City
26.desc: City or town relevant for a particular transaction or consignment.

27.name: Country of origin
27.desc: [3239] To identify the country in which the goods have been produced or manufactured, according to criteria laid down for the application of the Customs tariff or quantitative restrictions, or any measure related to trade.

28.name: Country of destination of goods
28.desc: Country to which the goods are to be delivered.

29.name: Railway station
29.desc: Name or identification of a railway station/yard relevant to a particular consignment.

30.name: Country of source
30.desc: Country in which raw material or components were originally produced prior to manufacture or assembly in another country.

31.name: Building
31.desc: A building or part thereof relevant to a particular consignment or transaction.

32.name: Beginning of chargeable section
32.desc: First rail station in a predefined section of the chargeable voyage. A complete voyage may be divided in sections, even within one country, that are separately chargeable using different tariff rules (split tariffs).

33.name: Baseport of discharge
33.desc: [3356] Place at which the cargo is discharged or unloaded from a means of transport according to the transport contract. The goods may or may not be discharged from the main means of transport at this place or port.

34.name: Baseport of loading
34.desc: [3322] Place at which the cargo is loaded on a means of transport according to the transport contract. The goods may or may not be loaded on the main means of transport at this place or port.

35.name: Exportation country
35.desc: [3220] Country from which the goods were initially exported to the importing country without any commercial transaction taking place in intermediate countries. Synonym: Country whence consigned. Country of despatch: Country from which goods are despatched between countries of a Customs union.

36.name: Country of ultimate destination
36.desc: (3216) Country known to the consignor or his agent at the time of despatch to be the final country to which the goods are to be delivered.

37.name: Consignment final exportation country
37.desc: [3331] To identify the country from which goods have been or will be consigned prior to final importation.

38.name: Consignment first destination country
38.desc: [3219] To identify the country where a consignment is off-loaded from the means of transport used for the original exportation.

39.name: Country of production
39.desc: Country where item has been or will be produced.

40.name: Country of trading
40.desc: Country where item has been or will be traded.

41.name: Consignment entry customs office location
41.desc: [3089] To identify the customs office at which the goods enter the customs territory of destination.

42.name: Consignment exit customs office location
42.desc: [3097] To identify the customs office at which the goods leave or are intended to leave the customs territory of despatch.

43.name: Place of Customs examination
43.desc: Place where Customs undertakes a physical inspection of goods to satisfy themselves that the goods' nature, origin, condition, quantity and value are in accordance with the particulars furnished on the goods declaration (CCC).

44.name: Place of authentication of document
44.desc: (3410) Place where document is signed or otherwise authenticated. Synonym: Place of issue of document.

45.name: Customs office of destination (transit)
45.desc: (3086) Customs office at which a transit operation is terminated. Synonym: Customs office of transit termination.

46.name: Region of despatch
46.desc: Region from which goods are despatched between countries of a Customs union.

47.name: Region of destination
47.desc: Region known to the consignor or his agent at the time of despatch to be the final region to which the goods are to be delivered.

48.name: Region of production
48.desc: Region where item has been or will be produced.

49.name: Transit country
49.desc: [3263] Country through which a goods or passengers are routed between the country of original departure and final destination.

50.name: Transit customs office location
50.desc: [3107] To identify the customs office which is responsible for transit formalities en-route.

51.name: Country of invalid transit guarantee
51.desc: Country in which the security or guarantee for the movement of goods under a transit procedure is not valid.

52.name: Country of destination (transit)
52.desc: Country at which a Customs transit operation is terminated. Synonym: Country of transit termination.

53.name: Charge and freight due from
53.desc: Place or point from which charges and freight are charged.

54.name: Manufacturing department
54.desc: A department within the manufacturing area (e.g. lacquering, assembly).

55.name: Freight charge payable to location
55.desc: [3102] Name of a place to which a transport charges tariff applies or where freight and other related charges are to be or have been incurred.

56.name: End of chargeable section
56.desc: Last rail station in a predefined section of the chargeable voyage. A complete voyage may be divided in sections, even within one country, that are separately chargeable using different tariff rules (split tariffs).

57.name: Place of payment
57.desc: Name of the location at which freight and charges for main transport are payable.

58.name: Full track loading or unloading
58.desc: Identification of the station proceeding to the loading or unloading of a rail wagon on a full track site. (Used only when a rail station is obliged to transfer the load on another wagon for technical reasons - e.g. damage).

59.name: Place of loss
59.desc: To identify the location where the loss occurred.

60.name: Place of arrival
60.desc: Place at which the transport means arrives.

61.name: Next port of call
61.desc: (3095) Next port which the vessel is going to call upon.

62.name: On-carriage port
62.desc: Port of discharge at which the cargo is discharged from the vessel, used for transport after the main transport (transit port).

63.name: Sub-project location
63.desc: A place at which works occur referring to a sub-project.

64.name: First optional place of discharge
64.desc: The first optional place or port of discharge as mentioned on the transport document where cargo can be discharged at the option of the shipper.

65.name: Final port or place of discharge
65.desc: Name of the seaport, airport, freight terminal, rail station or other place at which the goods (cargo) are finally (to be) unloaded from the means of transport used for their carriage according to the transport contract.

66.name: Express railway station
66.desc: Railway station offering express transportation services.

67.name: Mixed cargo railway station
67.desc: Railway station offering mixed cargo transportation services .

68.name: Second optional place of discharge
68.desc: The second optional place or port of discharge as mentioned on the transport document where cargo can be discharged at the option of shipper.

69.name: Next non-discharge port of call
69.desc: A code to identify the next port of call for a vessel where no cargo will be discharged.

70.name: Third optional place of discharge
70.desc: The third optional place or port of discharge as mentioned on the transport document where cargo can be discharged at the option of the shipper.

71.name: Reconsolidation point
71.desc: A place where cargo is reconsolidated.

72.name: Fourth optional place of discharge
72.desc: The fourth optional place or port of discharge as mentioned on the transport document where cargo can be discharged at the option of the shipper.

73.name: Bill of lading release office
73.desc: A location where bills of lading are released to customers.

74.name: Transhipment excluding this place
74.desc: Place/location where a transhipment from a means of transport to another means of transport is not authorised.

75.name: Transhipment limited to this place
75.desc: Only place/location where a transhipment from a means of transport to another means of transport is authorised.

76.name: Original port of loading
76.desc: (3099) The port where the goods were first loaded on a vessel.

77.name: First port of call - non-discharging
77.desc: Port in the country of destination where the conveyance initially arrives from the 'last place/port of call of conveyance' and where a conveyance will not be discharging cargoes.

78.name: First port of call - discharging
78.desc: Port in the country of destination where the conveyance initially arrives from the 'last place/port of call of conveyance' and where a conveyance will be discharging cargoes.

79.name: Place/port of first entry
79.desc: Place or port where final documentation is filed for Customs entry processing.

80.name: Place of despatch
80.desc: Place at which the goods are taken over for carriage (operational term), if different from the transport contract place of acceptance (see: 10). Synonym: Place of origin of carriage.

81.name: Fifth optional place of discharge
81.desc: The fifth optional place or port of discharge as mentioned on the transport document where cargo can be discharged at the option of the shipper.

82.name: Pre-carriage port
82.desc: Port of loading at which the cargo is loaded on the pre- carriage vessel used for the transport prior to the main transport.

83.name: Place of delivery (by on carriage)
83.desc: [3358] Place to which the goods are to be finally delivered.

84.name: Transport contract place of acceptance
84.desc: Place at which the goods are taken over by the carrier according to the contract of carriage.

85.name: Transport contract place of destination
85.desc: Place to which the goods are destined.

86.name: Country of valid transit guarantee
86.desc: Country in which the security or guarantee for the movement of goods under a transit procedure is valid.

87.name: Place/port of conveyance initial arrival
87.desc: Place/port in the country of destination where the conveyance initially arrives from the "Last place/port of call of conveyance" (125).

88.name: Place of receipt
88.desc: Identification of the location at which the cargo is actually received.

89.name: Place of registration
89.desc: (3105) Place where the registration occurs.

90.name: Special treatment place
90.desc: Place where one or more special treatments have happened or must happen.

91.name: Place of document issue
91.desc: The place or location where a document is issued.

92.name: Routing
92.desc: Indication of a routing place.

93.name: Station of application of additional costs
93.desc: Rail station where, according to the transport contract, some chargeable operations must happen (re-weighting, re-fixing of the load, control on equipment and on consignment, etc.).

94.name: Previous port of call
94.desc: Previous port which the vessel has called upon.

95.name: Sailing destination area
95.desc: Geographical area to which the vessel's trip is destined.

96.name: Place of lodgement of documents
96.desc: Customs station where, required documents for Customs declarations, have been lodged.

97.name: Optional place of discharge
97.desc: The optional place or port of discharge as mentioned on the bill of lading where cargo is discharged at the option of the shipper.

98.name: Place of empty equipment despatch
98.desc: The location from which empty equipment is despatched.

99.name: Place of empty equipment return
99.desc: The location to which empty equipment is returned.

100.name: Place/port of warehouse entry
100.desc: Location (e.g. district) within a Customs territory where a warehouse entry was filed to enter merchandise into a Customs bonded warehouse.

101.name: Country of first sale
101.desc: Name of country where firstly a sale took place.

103.name: Place of transfer
103.desc: Place at which goods are transferred from one carrier to another (contractual term).

104.name: Place of deconsolidation
104.desc: Place where a large consignment is de-grouped into smaller consignments.

105.name: Place of consumption
105.desc: Place/location where goods enter the marketplace (commerce) of the importing country.

106.name: Region of origin
106.desc: Region in which the goods have been produced or manufactured according to the criteria laid down for the purposes of the application of the Customs tariff, of quantitative restrictions or of any other measures related to trade (see: 3238).

107.name: Place of consolidation
107.desc: Place where smaller consignments of goods are grouped together into a large consignment to be transported as a larger unit.

108.name: Rate combination point
108.desc: [3369] Point over which sector rates are combined.

109.name: Place of prolongation decision of delivery delay
109.desc: Place where it has been decided to prolong the delivery delay.

110.name: Recharging place/location
110.desc: Place/location where a consignment has been changed of destination and is subject to a recharge note. (Complementary orders to modify the routing of the transport may be given, upon which a new charge calculation may be applied by the carrier).

111.name: Customs office of despatch
111.desc: Customs office from which goods are despatched between countries of a Customs union.

112.name: Region of equipment availability
112.desc: Region in which a piece of equipment is requested to be made available for on-hire.

113.name: Country of despatch
113.desc: Country from which goods are despatched within a Customs union.

114.name: Customs office of export
114.desc: Customs office from which goods are taken out of the Customs territory (CCC).

115.name: Free zone of export
115.desc: Foreign free zone (desc: see 1131 = 131) from which goods are exported to the country of importation.

116.name: Region of export/despatch
116.desc: Region from which the goods were initially exported to the importing country without any commercial transaction taking place in intermediate countries. Region of despatch: region from which goods are despatched between countries of a Customs union.

117.name: Place of collection
117.desc: Place where goods are to be or could be picked up (collected).

118.name: Customs office of departure
118.desc: Customs office at which a Customs transit operation commences (CCC).

119.name: Transit guarantee customs office location
119.desc: [3111] To identify the Customs office at which a security or guarantee for the movement of goods under a transit procedure is lodged.

120.name: Country of transhipment
120.desc: Country where goods are transferred under Customs control from the importing means of transport to the exporting means of transport within the area of one Customs office which is the office of both importation and exportation (CCC).

122.name: Customs office of destination
122.desc: Customs office where the goods are to be cleared (CCC).

123.name: Wagon-load railway station
123.desc: A railway station where rail wagons are loaded.

124.name: Siding
124.desc: A short railway track for loading or unloading rail wagons, or bypassing of trains, connected with a main track by switch.

125.name: Last place/port of call of conveyance
125.desc: Conveyance departed from this last foreign place/port of call to go to "Place/port of conveyance initial arrival" (87).

126.name: Country of previous Customs procedure
126.desc: Country in which the Customs declaration for the previous Customs procedure has been lodged.

127.name: Customs office of registration of previous Customs declaration
127.desc: Customs office where the previous Customs declaration has been lodged.

128.name: Participant sender location
128.desc: Place where a participant in the movement of goods is located and can be contacted.

129.name: Wage negotiation district
129.desc: The district to which workers belong for the purposes of union wage negotiation.

130.name: Place of ultimate destination of conveyance
130.desc: Seaport, airport, freight terminal, rail station or other place to which a means of transport is ultimately destined.

131.name: Place of loading of empty equipment
131.desc: Seaport, airport, freight terminal, rail station or other place where empty equipment (e.g. containers) was loaded onto means of transport.

132.name: Place of discharge of empty equipment
132.desc: Seaport, airport, freight terminal, rail station or other place where empty equipment (e.g. containers) was unloaded from means of transport.

133.name: Region of delivery
133.desc: (3246) Region to which the goods are to be finally delivered under transport contract terms (operational term).

134.name: Petroleum warehouse
134.desc: Bonded petroleum warehouse or the supplier source.

135.name: Place of entry (Customs)
135.desc: Place at which the goods enter the Customs territory.

136.name: Living animals care place
136.desc: Place where living animal cares are provided.

137.name: Re-icing place
137.desc: Place where re-icing must be executed.

138.name: Weighting place
138.desc: Place where weight can be ascertained.

139.name: Marshalling yard
139.desc: Station where the wagons are disconnected and reconnected to form a new train.

140.name: Stopping station
140.desc: Station where the train must stop or is stopped for unexpected handling.

141.name: Loading dock
141.desc: Platform specially equipped for loading and unloading of rail wagons.

142.name: Port connection
142.desc: Track connecting a rail station to a dock.

143.name: Place of expiry
143.desc: [3212] Place where the documentary credit expires for presentation of required documents.

144.name: Place of negotiation
144.desc: Place where the documentary credit is to be presented for negotiation.

145.name: Claims payable place
145.desc: Place where insurance claims are payable.

146.name: Documentary credit available in
146.desc: Place where the documentary credit is available with any bank.

147.name: Transport means stowage location
147.desc: [8043] To identify a location on board a means of transport where specified goods or transport equipment has been or are to be stowed.

148.name: For transportation to
148.desc: Place/country where goods are to be transported to.

149.name: Loading on board/despatch/taking in charge at/from
149.desc: Place/country where goods have to be loaded on board, despatched or taken in charge.

150.name: Container stack position
150.desc: Stack position of a container at a terminal, depot or freight station.

151.name: Private box
151.desc: A private box used for pick-up and delivery of packages, e.g. of express packages.

152.name: Next port of discharge
152.desc: Next port at which goods are discharged from the vessel used for their transport.

153.name: Port of call
153.desc: Port where a vessel has called upon or will call upon.

154.name: Place/location of on-hire
154.desc: Place/location where an object is contracted for use.

155.name: Place/location of off-hire
155.desc: Place/location where an object's contract for use ends.

156.name: Other carriers terminal
156.desc: A carrier terminal belonging to a carrier other than the original carrier.

157.name: Country of Value Added Tax (VAT) jurisdiction
157.desc: The country governing the VAT regulation to which the transaction is subject.

158.name: Contact location
158.desc: The site where a contact is located.

159.name: Additional internal destination
159.desc: Any location within the consignee's premises where the goods are moved to.

160.name: Foreign port of call
160.desc: A code to identify the foreign port where the vessel calls at or will call at.

161.name: Maintenance location
161.desc: A location where maintenance has been or will be performed.

162.name: Place or location of sale
162.desc: Place or location at which the sale takes place.

163.name: Direct investment country
163.desc: Country in which a direct investment is made or withdrawn.

164.name: Berth
164.desc: [3416] Location in port where the vessel is berthed or moored.

165.name: Construction country
165.desc: Country in which the construction work is made.

166.name: Donation acting country
166.desc: Country acting in the donation of aid.

167.name: Payment transaction country
167.desc: Country of the foreign counterpart of the payment transaction.

168.name: Physical place of return of item
168.desc: Physical place at which the item is returned, i.e. the location where the supplier receives the item form the customer.

169.name: Relay port
169.desc: A location where cargo is transferred from one means of transport to another means of transport owned or operated by the same carrier under the same bill of lading.

170.name: Final port of discharge
170.desc: Last port at which cargo is unloaded from a vessel before the cargo is moved to a place of delivery or destination.

171.name: Place of destination for pre-stacking prior to stowage
171.desc: The destination location for which items are to be pre- stacked prior to being stowed together on a means of transport.

172.name: Reporting location
172.desc: The location to which the information being reported is applicable.

173.name: Transport contract place of despatch
173.desc: A place from which goods are despatched as per transport contract.

174.name: Place of residence
174.desc: A place where a party lives.

175.name: Activity location
175.desc: A place at which the activity occurs.

177.name: Construction site
177.desc: A place at which construction works occur.

178.name: Place of embarkation
178.desc: (3488) Place where the object is put, or goes, on board the conveyance.

179.name: Place of disembarkation
179.desc: (3490) Place where the object or person disembarks from the conveyance.

180.name: Person birth location
180.desc: [3486] Name of the place where a person was born.

181.name: Registered office
181.desc: Identifies the place or location of a registered office.

183.name: Place of business
183.desc: Identifies the place or location of a business.

185.name: Location to send mail
185.desc: Identifies the location to which mail is sent.

186.name: Foreign registration location
186.desc: Identifies the place or location of foreign registration.

187.name: Tax filed from location
187.desc: Identifies the location from which taxes are filed.

188.name: Filing location
188.desc: Identifies the location of the filing entity.

189.name: Former location
189.desc: Identifies an earlier or previous place or location.

190.name: Head office
190.desc: Identifies the place or location of a head office.

191.name: Property
191.desc: Identifies the place or location of property.

192.name: Correct location
192.desc: Identifies the correct place or location.

193.name: Branch location
193.desc: Identifies the place or location of a branch.

194.name: Former registered location
194.desc: Identifies the former registered location of an entity.

195.name: Future location
195.desc: Location to be used in the future.

197.name: Place of inquiry
197.desc: Place to which an inquiry is made.

199.name: Country of last source
199.desc: The country where a product or service was last sourced.

200.name: Place of handling
200.desc: Place where a handling operation is to be, or has been, performed.

201.name: Country of origin as defined by transportation agency
201.desc: Country of origin as defined by the transportation agency.

203.name: Sample location
203.desc: Code identifying the location from which a sample is taken.

185.name: CH, compliant with General Food law

186.name: CH, non-compliant with General Food law
186.desc: An indication that a product does not comply with the Swiss general food law.

188.name: Distribution centre may not order

190.desc: A declaration of a trade item's net content is not on the product label.

192.name: Batch or lot number not allocated

193.name: Unsold trade item not returnable
193.desc: A trade item that is not sold cannot be returned.

194.name: Ingredient irradiated

195.name: Ingredients not irradiated
195.desc: Radiation has not been applied to any trade item's ingredient.

196.name: Raw material irradiated

197.name: Raw material not irradiated
197.desc: Radiation has not been applied to any trade item's raw material.

199.name: Receipt advice, fully detailed
199.desc: Includes qualitative and/or quantitative details regarding everything received (all line items) whether or not there were exceptions between what was received and what was advised as being sent.

200.name: Receipt advice, only exceptions
200.desc: Includes only qualitative and/or quantitative exceptions between what was received and what was advised as being sent.

201.name: Ingredient is irradiated not applicable
201.desc: The indication that an ingredient of a trade item is irradiated is not applicable.

202.name: Raw material is irradiated not applicable

203.name: Trade item is genetically modified not applicable
203.desc: The indication that a product has not been genetically modified is not applicable.

204.name: Trade item is irradiated not applicable

206.name: Size independent pricing
206.desc: An item price is independent of the size.

207.name: Only accepted products

ZZZ.name: Mutually defined

A.name: Account
A.desc: The charges are to be charged to an account.

AA.name: Cash on delivery service charge paid by consignor
AA.desc: An indication that the consignor is responsible for the payment of the cash on delivery service charge.

AB.name: Cash on delivery service charge paid by consignee
AB.desc: An indication that the consignee is responsible for the payment of the cash on delivery service charge.

AC.name: Insurance costs paid by consignor
AC.desc: An indication that the consignor is responsible for the payment of the insurance costs.

AD.name: Insurance costs paid by consignee
AD.desc: An indication that the consignee is responsible for the payment of the insurance costs.

AE.name: Goods collected from store
AE.desc: Customer collects goods from the store.

CC.name: Collect
CC.desc: A shipment on which freight charges will be paid by consignee.

CF.name: Collect, freight credited to payment customer
CF.desc: The freight is collect but has been paid by the shipper and will be credited to that party.

DF.name: Defined by buyer and seller
DF.desc: The payment method for transport charges have been defined by the buyer and seller.

FO.name: FOB port of call
FO.desc: Title and control of goods pass to the buyer at port of call. Responsibility for export taxes and cost of documents for overseas shipments have not been specified.

IC.name: Information copy, no payment due
IC.desc: Transaction set has been provided for information only.

M.name: Mixed
M.desc: The consignment is partially collect and partially prepaid.

NC.name: Service freight, no charge
NC.desc: The consignment is shipped on a service basis and there is no freight charge.

NS.name: Not specified
NS.desc: The payment method for transport charges have not been specified.

PA.name: Advance prepaid
PA.desc: Costs have been paid in advance.

PB.name: Customer pick-up/backhaul
PB.desc: Buyer's private carriage picks up the goods as a return load to the buyer's facility.

PC.name: Prepaid but charged to customer
PC.desc: shipping charges have been paid in advance of shipment but are charged back to consignee usually as line item on invoice for the purchased goods.

PE.name: Payable elsewhere
PE.desc: Place of payment not known at the begin of conveyance.

PO.name: Prepaid only
PO.desc: Payment in advance of freight and/or other charges prior to delivery of shipment at destination, usually by shipper at point of origin.

PP.name: Prepaid (by seller)
PP.desc: Seller of goods makes payment to carrier for freight charges prior to shipment.

PU.name: Pickup
PU.desc: Customer is responsible for payment of pickup charges at shipping point.

RC.name: Return container freight paid by customer
RC.desc: The freight for returning the container is paid by the customer.

RF.name: Return container freight free
RF.desc: There is no freight charge for returning the container.

RS.name: Return container freight paid by supplier
RS.desc: The freight charge for returning the container is paid by the supplier.

TP.name: Third party pay
TP.desc: A third party, someone other than buyer or seller, is identified as responsible for payment of shipping charges.

WC.name: Weight condition
WC.desc: The payment method for transport charges are due to the weight.

WD.name: Paid by supplier
WD.desc: Transport charges will be paid by the supplier.

WE.name: Paid by buyer
WE.desc: Transport charges will be paid by the buyer.

ZZZ.name: Mutually defined
ZZZ.desc: A code assigned within a code list to be used on an interim basis and as defined among trading partners until a precise code can be assigned to the code list.

1.name: Express
1.desc: Express treatment (if by rail, legal express regime for parcels transport).

2.name: High speed
2.desc: Transport under legal international rail convention (CIM) concluded between rail organizations and based on fast routing and specified timetables.

3.name: Normal speed
3.desc: Transport under legal international rail convention (CIM) concluded between rail organizations.

4.name: Post service
4.desc: Transport under conditions specified by UPU (Universal Postal Union) and Rail organizations (parcels transport only).

AA.name: Item discontinued by wholesaler
AA.desc: The wholesaler no longer offers the ordered product.

AB.name: Item no longer produced
AB.desc: The item ordered has been discontinued and is no longer in production.

AC.name: Over-shipped

AD.name: Item out of stock at manufacturer
AD.desc: The item is out of stock at manufacturer.

AE.name: Delivered but not advised

AF.name: Goods delivered damaged

AS.name: Available now - scheduled to ship (date)

CC.name: Shipment complete

CE.desc: The quantity dispatched exceeds the order quantity to accommodate a quantity of scale price model opportunity.

CK.name: Cancelled from previous order
CK.desc: Amount deleted from the earlier schedule.

CM.name: Shipment complete with additional quantity
CM.desc: The quantity dispatched exceeds the ordered quantity.

CO.name: Customer inquiry - unshipped items only
CO.desc: The response includes information addressing only the items that have not been dispatched, that were included in the prior inquiry.

CP.name: Shipment partial - considered complete, no backorder
CP.desc: The quantity shipped is less than the amount authorized and there is no plan to ship the remaining amount.

CS.name: Shipment complete with substitution
CS.desc: The quantity and product shipped, though not exactly matching the original order, is compliant with and fulfils the expectation.

IC.name: Item cancelled
IC.desc: The material previously ordered is no longer needed.

IS.name: Item represents substitution from original order

LS.name: Last shipment (date)

NF.name: Not yet published
NF.desc: The product requested is not publicly available at this time.

NN.name: Not in process - no shipping schedule
NN.desc: The product requested is neither available nor in process, as there is not an authorization to manufacture product.

NS.name: Not in process - schedule to ship (date)
NS.desc: The product requested is neither available nor in process. A planned dispatch date has been provided.

OF.name: Order sent to factory for production (date)

OM.name: Item sent to factory for production (date)

OS.name: Item out of stock because of strike or force majeure

OW.name: Item out of stock at wholesaler
OW.desc: Item is not available at the distribution point.

PA.desc: The response includes information concerning all of the articles included in the prior inquiry that had been requested by the contact initiator.

PD.name: Purchase order complete
PD.desc: The amount fulfilling the requirements of the contract.

PI.name: Purchase order inquiry - shipped items only
PI.desc: The response includes information concerning all of the articles that were dispatched and included in the prior inquiry that had been requested by the contact initiator.

PK.name: Packed-to-date (date)
PK.desc: Quantity represents the amount processed and ready for shipment at this date.

PN.name: In process - no shipping schedule
PN.desc: This amount is being manufactured in anticipation for a possible authorization for shipment.

PO.name: Purchase order inquiry - unshipped items only
PO.desc: The response includes information concerning all of the articles that were not dispatched and included in the prior inquiry that had been requested by the contact initiator.

PP.name: Purchase order inquiry - specific items
PP.desc: The response includes information concerning a unique sub-set of the total list of articles that the contract initiator had requested information on.

PS.name: In process - scheduled to ship (date)
PS.desc: This amount is being manufactured in anticipation for a possible authorization for shipment.

RA.name: Item rationed
RA.desc: Product is restricted because of limited availability.

SL.name: Shipped-to-date (date)
SL.desc: Cumulative amount shipped through this date.

SP.name: Scheduled for production at factory
SP.desc: Product is anticipated for manufacture on this date.

SS.name: Split shipment
SS.desc: Shipment is only part of the ordered quantity.

TW.name: Item temporary discontinued by wholesaler

UR.name: Unsolicited report

US.name: Pack to closest complete logistic packaging quantity

UT.name: Pack to next lower complete logistic quantity

15.desc: Packaging should be marked with the supplier number.

20.desc: Markings as specified by industry.

43.desc: Indication that the expiry date has been marked on a package.

45.name: Marked with net weight

46.name: Marked with packaging date

47.name: Marked with GS1 Global Returnable Asset Identifier (GRAI)
47.desc: Indication that the GS1 Global Returnable Asset Identifier (GRAI) has been marked on the package.

A.name: Payable elsewhere

C.name: Collect

P.name: Prepaid

1.name: Draft(s) drawn on issuing bank

3.name: Draft(s) drawn on reimbursing bank
3.desc: Draft(s) must be drawn on the reimbursing bank.

4.name: Draft(s) drawn on applicant
4.desc: Draft(s) must be drawn on the applicant.

5.name: Draft(s) drawn on any other drawee
5.desc: Draft(s) must be drawn on any other drawee.

6.name: No drafts
6.desc: No drafts required.

7.name: Payment means specified in commercial account summary
7.desc: An indication that the payment means are specified in a commercial account summary.

1.name: Basic
1.desc: Payment conditions normally applied.

2.name: End of month
2.desc: Payments are due at end of month.

3.name: Fixed date
3.desc: Payments are due on the fixed date specified.

4.name: Deferred
4.desc: Payments are deferred beyond the normal due date.

5.name: Discount not applicable
5.desc: Payment terms on which discounts are not applicable.

6.name: Mixed
6.desc: Different payment terms negotiated under a documentary credit.

7.name: Extended
7.desc: Payment is extended beyond the normal due date.

8.name: Basic discount offered
8.desc: Payment terms reflect the basic offered discount.

9.name: Proximo
9.desc: Occurring in the next month after present.

10.name: Instant
10.desc: Payment is due on receipt of invoice.

11.name: Elective
11.desc: Payment terms to be chosen by buyer (from options separately advised).

12.name: 10 days after end of month
12.desc: Payment due ten days after end of a calendar month.

13.name: Seller to advise buyer
13.desc: Seller will advise buyer of payment terms by separate transaction.

14.name: Paid against statement
14.desc: Payments are to be made against statement.

15.name: No charge
15.desc: Payment terms have no charge.

16.name: Not yet defined
16.desc: Payment terms are not yet defined.

17.name: Ultimo
17.desc: Payment is due the end of the current or specified month.

18.name: Previously agreed upon
18.desc: Payment terms have been previously agreed upon.

19.name: United States funds
19.desc: The payment terms require the use of United States funds.

20.name: Penalty terms
20.desc: Payment terms on which penalties apply.

21.name: Payment by instalment
21.desc: Payment terms are based on instalment payments.

22.name: Discount
22.desc: Payment terms on which discounts are applicable.

23.name: Available by sight payment
23.desc: Payment made at sight.

24.name: Available by deferred payment
24.desc: Payment made at deferred date.

25.name: Available by acceptance
25.desc: Payment on acceptance.

26.name: Available by negotiation with any bank
26.desc: Payment made by negotiation with any bank.

27.name: Available by negotiation with any bank in ...
27.desc: Payment made by negotiation with any bank in a specified location.

28.name: Available by negotiation by named bank
28.desc: Payment made by negotiation with a specified financial institution.

29.name: Available by negotiation
29.desc: Payment made by negotiation.

30.name: Adjustment payment
30.desc: Payment adjusted for outstanding credits or debits.

31.name: Late payment
31.desc: Payment after due date.

32.name: Advanced payment
32.desc: Payment in advance of due date.

33.name: Payment by instalments according to progress (as agreed)
33.desc: Payment by instalments according to progress (as agreed).

34.name: Payment by instalments according to progress (to be agreed)
34.desc: Payment by instalments according to progress (to be agreed).

35.name: Nonstandard
35.desc: Terms of payment differ from the normal terms.

36.name: Tenor payment terms
36.desc: Payment to be made according to bilaterally agreed conditions between buyer and seller.

37.name: Complete payment
37.desc: Payment must be made for complete value and may not be paid in instalments.

38.name: Payment terms defined in consolidated invoice
38.desc: Payment terms are specified in a consolidated invoice.

39.name: Payment upon completion
39.desc: The payment terms require payment upon completion.

40.name: Partial advance
40.desc: The payment terms require a partial payment in advance of completion.

41.name: Consignment
41.desc: The payment terms are that the goods will be paid for when they are sold or consumed.

42.name: Inter-company account
42.desc: The payment terms involve the use of an inter-company account.

43.name: Sell by note
43.desc: The payment terms involve a debtor who promises to pay a definite sum of money on demand or at a definite time in the future.

44.name: Supplier floor plan
44.desc: The payment terms involve payment for merchandise owned by a third party.

45.name: Contract basis
45.desc: The payment terms are based on a contract with a vendor.

46.name: Credit controlled
46.desc: The payment terms involve the monitoring of credit by the grantor.

47.name: Dating given
47.desc: The payment terms in which suppliers may extend seasonal dating.

48.name: Trade acceptance
48.desc: A trade acceptance is a written acknowledgement of the sale of goods and promise to pay at a definite date and place.

49.name: Cost plus
49.desc: The payment terms permit reimbursement of costs plus other authorised changes.

50.name: Letter of credit
50.desc: The payment terms require the use of a letter of credit.

51.name: Lease agreement
51.desc: The payment terms are included in the lease agreement.

52.name: Cash On Delivery (COD)
52.desc: The payment terms are cash is due on delivery of merchandise.

53.name: Cash by state law
53.desc: The payment terms are dictated by state law requiring payment of cash.

54.name: Bank transfer
54.desc: The payment terms require the use of bank transfer.

55.name: Cash on arrival
55.desc: The payment terms require payment by cash on arrival of the goods or services.

56.name: Cash
56.desc: The payment terms are that payments are made in cash.

57.name: Cash discount terms apply
57.desc: The payment terms are that a discount is applicable if the payment is made in cash.

58.name: Cash with order
58.desc: The payment terms require the payment in cash with placement of the order.

59.name: Cash per vendor request
59.desc: The payment terms involve a vendor request for payment by cash.

60.name: Irrevocable letter of credit
60.desc: The payment terms require the use of an irrevocable letter of credit.

61.name: Documents against acceptance
61.desc: The payment terms require acceptance of liability before document transfer.

62.name: Charge card
62.desc: The payment terms permit the use of a charge card to effect payment.

63.name: Documents against payment
63.desc: The payment terms require payment before document transfer.

64.name: Usance bill
64.desc: The payment terms are based on the time allowed by commercial usage for the payment of foreign bills of exchange.

65.name: Letter of credit at sight
65.desc: The payment terms require the presentation of a letter of credit.

66.name: Secured account
66.desc: The payment terms call for the use of a secured account.

67.name: Basic commission terms
67.desc: The payment terms call for the use of basic commission terms.

68.name: Deposit required
68.desc: The payment terms require a deposit be provided.

69.name: Discount with prompt pay
69.desc: The payment terms include a discount when payment is made within a time frame designated as prompt pay.

70.name: Discount with advance payment
70.desc: The payment terms include a discount when payment is made in advance.

71.name: Certified cheque
71.desc: The payment terms require the use of a certified cheque.

72.name: Cash against documents
72.desc: The payment terms require cash payment before document transfer.

73.name: Bill of exchange
73.desc: The payment terms require the use of bill of exchange.

74.name: Progressive discount
74.desc: The payment terms include a progressive discount based on the amount and speed with which payments are made.

75.name: Lump sum
75.desc: The payment term requires a lump sum payment.

76.name: Fixed fee
76.desc: The payment term requires a fixed fee payment.

77.name: Promissory note
77.desc: The payment term requires the use of a promissory note as a means of payment.

This type of collection involves financial and commercial documents. International Chamber of Commerce (ICC) term.

6.name: ACH demand credit
6.desc: A credit transaction made through the ACH system to a demand deposit account.

7.name: ACH demand debit
7.desc: A debit transaction made through the ACH system to a demand deposit account.

8.name: Hold
8.desc: Indicates that the bank should hold the payment for collection by the beneficiary or other instructions.

9.name: National or regional clearing
9.desc: Indicates that the payment should be made using the national or regional clearing.

10.name: In cash
10.desc: Payment by currency (including bills and coins) in circulation, including checking account deposits.

11.desc: A request to reverse an ACH credit transaction to a savings account.

12.name: ACH savings debit reversal

13.desc: A credit transaction made through the ACH system to a savings account.

14.name: ACH savings debit
14.desc: A debit transaction made through the ACH system to a savings account.

16.name: Bookentry debit
16.desc: A debit entry between two accounts at the same bank branch. Synonym: house debit.

17.name: ACH demand cash concentration/disbursement (CCD) credit

18.name: ACH demand cash concentration/disbursement (CCD) debit
18.desc: A debit transaction made through the ACH system to a demand deposit account using the CCD payment format.

19.name: ACH demand corporate trade payment (CTP) credit

21.name: Banker's draft
21.desc: Issue of a banker's draft in payment of the funds.

22.name: Certified banker's draft

25.name: Certified cheque
25.desc: Payment by a pre-printed form stamped with the paying bank's certification on which instructions are given to an account holder (a bank or building society) to pay a stated sum to a named recipient .

27.name: ACH demand corporate trade payment (CTP) debit
27.desc: A debit transaction made through the ACH system to a demand deposit account using the CTP payment format.

28.name: ACH demand corporate trade exchange (CTX) credit

29.name: ACH demand corporate trade exchange (CTX) debit
29.desc: A debit transaction made through the ACH system to a demand account using the CTX payment format.

30.desc: Payment by credit movement of funds from one account to another.

31.name: Debit transfer

33.name: ACH demand cash concentration/disbursement plus (CCD+) debit
33.desc: A debit transaction made through the ACH system to a demand deposit account using the CCD+ payment format.

34.name: ACH prearranged payment and deposit (PPD)

35.name: ACH savings cash concentration/disbursement (CCD) credit

36.name: ACH savings cash concentration/disbursement (CCD) debit
36.desc: A debit transaction made through the ACH system to a savings account using the CCD payment format.

37.name: ACH savings corporate trade payment (CTP) credit
37.desc: A credit transaction made through the ACH system to a savings account using the CTP payment format.

38.name: ACH savings corporate trade payment (CTP) debit
38.desc: A debit transaction made through the ACH system to a savings account using the CTP payment format.

39.name: ACH savings corporate trade exchange (CTX) credit
39.desc: A credit transaction made through the ACH system to a savings account using the CTX payment format.

40.name: ACH savings corporate trade exchange (CTX) debit
40.desc: A debit transaction made through the ACH system to a savings account using the CTX payment format.

41.name: ACH savings cash concentration/disbursement plus (CCD+) credit
41.desc: A credit transaction made through the ACH system to a savings account using the CCD+ payment format.

42.name: Payment to bank account
42.desc: Payment by an arrangement for settling debts that is operated by the Post Office.

43.name: ACH savings cash concentration/disbursement plus (CCD+) debit
43.desc: A debit transaction made through the ACH system to a savings account using the CCD+ payment format.

44.name: Accepted bill of exchange
44.desc: Bill drawn by the creditor on the debtor and accepted by the debtor.

45.name: Referenced home-banking credit transfer

46.name: Interbank debit transfer
46.desc: A debit transfer via interbank means.

47.name: Home-banking debit transfer
47.desc: A debit transfer initiated through home-banking.

48.name: Bank card
48.desc: Payment by means of a card issued by a bank or other financial institution.

49.name: Direct debit
49.desc: The amount is to be, or has been, directly debited to the customer's bank account.

53.name: Urgent Treasury Payment
53.desc: Payment order or transfer which must be executed, by the most appropriate means, as urgently as possible and before urgent commercial payments.

54.name: Credit card
54.desc: Payment made by means of credit card.

55.name: Debit card
55.desc: Payment made by means of debit card.

56.name: Bankgiro
56.desc: Payment will be, or has been, made by bankgiro.

57.name: Standing agreement
57.desc: The payment means have been previously agreed between seller and buyer and thus are not stated again.

58.name: SEPA credit transfer
58.desc: Credit transfer inside the Single Euro Payment Area (SEPA) system.

59.name: SEPA direct debit
59.desc: Direct debit inside the Single Euro Payment Area (SEPA) system.

65.desc: Payment by an unconditional promise in writing made by the bank to another person, signed by the bank and endorsed by another bank, engaging to pay on demand or at a fixed or determinable future time a sum certain in money, to order or to bearer.

67.name: Promissory note signed by a third party and endorsed by a bank
67.desc: Payment by an unconditional promise in writing made by a third party to another person, signed by the third party and endorsed by a bank, engaging to pay on demand or at a fixed or determinable future time a sum certain in money, to order or to bearer.

70.name: Bill drawn by the creditor on the debtor

74.desc: Bill drawn by the creditor on a bank.
