10.name: Irrevocable and transferable standby letter of credit
10.desc: Irrevocable and transferable standby letter of credit.

11.name: Revocable standby letter of credit
11.desc: Revocable standby letter of credit.

12.name: Irrevocable standby letter of credit
12.desc: Irrevocable standby letter of credit.

13.name: Pre-advised direct debit
13.desc: The transaction is a direct debit about which the debtor has advised his bank prior to the creditor raising the direct debit, giving his bank permission to debit his account.

14.name: Non pre-advised direct debit
14.desc: The transaction is a direct debit about which the debtor has not advised his bank prior to the creditor raising the direct debit.

15.name: Irrevocable reimbursement of cash withdrawal
15.desc: The transaction is an irrevocable direct debit, from bank A to bank B, which reimburses bank A that has by agreement provided cash to a customer of bank B.

AA.name: Ship on authorization
AA.desc: A delivery requirement indicating the items should not be shipped without specific authorization.

BK.name: Ship partial - balance back order
BK.desc: Partial shipping is allowed. The rest of the order should be delivered as soon as possible.

CD.name: Cancel if not delivered by date
CD.desc: An order or the rest of an order should be cancelled if not delivered at specified date.

DA.name: Do not deliver after
DA.desc: A requirement that an order should not be delivered after a specified date/time.

DB.name: Do not deliver before
DB.desc: A requirement that an order should not be delivered before a specified date/time.

DD.name: Deliver on date
DD.desc: An order should be delivered exactly on specified date.

IS.name: Substitute item
IS.desc: A substitute item may be delivered, if the ordered item is not available.

P2.name: Ship as soon as possible
P2.desc: The order should be delivered as soon as possible.

SC.name: Ship complete order
SC.desc: The order should be delivered only complete, not partial.

SF.name: Ship partial, if no freight rate increase
SF.desc: Partial shipping of an order is allowed, if the total freight rate do not increase.

SP.name: Ship partial - balance cancel
SP.desc: Partial shipping is allowed. The rest of the order should be cancelled.

1.name: Reception
1.desc: Goods received at warehouse from another party or warehouse.

2.name: Delivery
2.desc: Goods which have been delivered from the inventory to another party or warehouse.

3.name: Scrapped parts
3.desc: Adjustment due to scrapped parts.

4.name: Difference
4.desc: The difference between the inventory, as physically counted, and the inventory recorded by the system.

5.name: Property transfer within warehouse
5.desc: An inventory movement issued when goods are moved (physically or logically) from one owner to another, whenever inventories are held in account of several owners of the same product within the same warehouse.

6.name: Inventory recycling
6.desc: This inventory movement is due to recycling of goods. For instance, defective goods have been repaired and are put back to the available inventory.

7.name: Reversal of previous movement
7.desc: This inventory movement is issued to cancel a previously processed movement.

8.name: Defects (technical)
8.desc: This inventory movement corresponds to parts with technical defect.

9.name: Commercial
9.desc: The inventory movement has been issued for commercial reasons.

10.name: Conversion
10.desc: The inventory movement is due to conversion of goods.

11.name: Consumption
11.desc: The inventory movement corresponds to goods taken out of consigned inventory for consumption.

1.name: Movement out of inventory
1.desc: Outgoing goods.

2.name: Movement into inventory
2.desc: Incoming goods.

1.name: Book-keeping inventory balance
1.desc: An inventory balance resulting from the book-keeping.

2.name: Formal inventory balance
2.desc: An inventory balance in accordance with the formal inventory procedure.

3.name: Interim inventory balance
3.desc: An inventory balance resulting from an interim counting.

1.name: Multi-currency credit cover
1.desc: Invoices in currencies other than the currency of the credit cover are expected.

2.name: Request new limit
2.desc: Seller requests new limit.

3.name: Request increased limit
3.desc: Seller requests increase of existing limit.

4.name: Request for preliminary assessment
4.desc: Request for information to be used during negotiation with prospective clients (sellers).

5.name: Request for new account only
5.desc: Request for opening new account only.

6.name: Cancellation
6.desc: Request to cancel an existing credit cover.

7.name: Reduction
7.desc: Request to reduce an existing credit cover.

8.name: Prolongation of credit cover
8.desc: Request to prolong an existing credit cover.

1.name: Preliminary assessment
1.desc: A preliminary assessment without formal approval or commitment.

2.name: Approved
2.desc: The limit request has been approved.

3.name: Not approved
3.desc: The limit request has not been approved.

4.name: Conditional approval
4.desc: Approval subject to conditions as specified.

5.name: Partly approved
5.desc: Partly approved as specified.

6.name: Still investigating
6.desc: The limit request is still under investigation.

7.name: Open new account only
7.desc: Buyer account has been opened without an approved limit.

8.name: Cancellation
8.desc: The existing limit has been cancelled.

9.name: Reduction
9.desc: Credit limit is reduced.

10.name: Change of name and/or address
10.desc: The name and/or address of the buyer has changed.

11.name: Close buyer's account
11.desc: The buyer's account is to be closed.

1.name: Requested financial information not provided
1.desc: Party requested has not provided financial information.

2.name: No financial information available
2.desc: No financial information is available on buyer.

3.name: Debtor is out of business
3.desc: Debtor ceased trading activities.

4.name: Debtor is new company
4.desc: Debtor is newly incorporated.

5.name: Debtor is not registered
5.desc: Debtor is not formally registered as legal entity.

6.name: Debtor is non-trading company
6.desc: Debtor without trading, e.g. holding company.

7.name: No comment
7.desc: No information can be disclosed.

8.name: Only insolvency risk covered
8.desc: Only the risk of insolvency is covered.

9.name: Subject to acceptance of bill of exchange
9.desc: Limit cover conditional to buyer's acceptance of bill of exchange.

10.name: Document against acceptance
10.desc: Limit given on documents against acceptance terms.

11.name: Document against payment
11.desc: Limit given on documents against payment terms.

12.name: Adverse information is publicly available
12.desc: Adverse information on buyer is publicly available.

13.name: Credit limit full
13.desc: No approval or increase in credit possible.

14.name: Lack of turnover
14.desc: Limit reduced. E.g. cancelled due to absence of activity.

15.name: Other
15.desc: Reasons not otherwise specified here.

1.name: Article price composition
1.desc: A breakdown of the item price is requested.

2.name: Article price
2.desc: The item price is requested.

3.name: Constituent material
3.desc: Information about constituent material, such as copper and plastics, is requested.

4.name: Carrier
4.desc: Suggested carrier is requested.

5.name: Conditions of sale
5.desc: General conditions of sale are requested.

6.name: Delivery party
6.desc: Suggested grouping centre is requested.

7.name: Economics dates
7.desc: Material, labour and overheads economic dates are requested.

8.name: Lead time
8.desc: Item lead time is requested.

9.name: Packaging price composition
9.desc: A breakdown of the package price is requested.

10.name: Packaging details
10.desc: Details about packaging is requested.

11.name: Production location
11.desc: Information about which production site is going to be used is requested.

12.name: Packaging price
12.desc: The packaging price is requested.

13.name: Payment terms
13.desc: Payment terms are requested.

14.name: Shipment from location
14.desc: Information from where the items are shipped is requested.

15.name: Tooling price composition
15.desc: A breakdown of the tooling price is requested.

16.name: Tooling items details
16.desc: Details about the tooling items are requested.

17.name: Tooling total details
17.desc: Details about the total tooling is requested.

18.name: Validity dates
18.desc: The quotations validity dates are requested.

19.name: Working pattern
19.desc: Information about working week, day and shift is requested.

20.name: Assigned log numbers
20.desc: Assigned log numbers are requested.

21.name: Cycle start date
21.desc: The start date for the cycle is requested.

22.name: Technical assessment status
22.desc: Technical assessment status information is requested.

23.name: Structure tag assignment
23.desc: The assigned structure tag is requested.

24.name: All available status information
24.desc: All available status information is requested.

25.name: Delivery status of all back order articles
25.desc: Information on the delivery status of all articles on back order.

26.name: General status of all back order articles
26.desc: Information on the general status of all articles on back order.

27.name: Delivery status of all outstanding orders
27.desc: Information on the delivery status of all outstanding orders.

28.name: General status of all outstanding orders
28.desc: Information on the general status of all outstanding orders.

29.name: Delivery status of the specified order(s) or order line(s)
29.desc: Delivery status of each order(s) or order line(s) specified.

30.name: General status of the specified order(s) or order line(s)
30.desc: General status of each order(s) or order line(s) specified.

2.name: Add and replace
2.desc: The data contains new objects, which are to be added, and existing objects, which are to replace objects which have the same identifier.

3.name: Replace
3.desc: The data is to replace existing data which has the same identifier.

4.name: Delete
4.desc: The data identified is to be deleted.

5.name: None
5.desc: The data is not to be maintained.

6.name: Addition
6.desc: Maintenance operation involves addition.

7.name: Change
7.desc: Maintenance operation involves change.

8.name: Marked for deletion
8.desc: The item is marked for deletion in a future release.

9.name: Repair
9.desc: Maintenance operation involves repair.

10.name: Cleaning
10.desc: Maintenance operation involves cleaning.

11.name: Waste disposal
11.desc: Maintenance operation involves waste disposal.

12.name: Return of empty packages
12.desc: Maintenance operation involves return of empty packages.

1.name: In right condition
1.desc: The seal is in right condition.

2.name: Damaged
2.desc: The seal is damaged.

3.name: Missing
3.desc: A seal that is missing.

4.name: Broken
4.desc: Used to specify that the seal is broken.

5.name: Faulty electronic seal
5.desc: The electronic seal is faulty.

1.name: Mechanical seal
1.desc: The seal is mechanical.

2.name: Electronic seal
2.desc: The seal is electronic.

3.name: Air fresh vent seal
3.desc: The seal is for sealing an air fresh vent.

1.name: Destination charge totals
1.desc: Code to indicate total charges levied at destination.

2.name: Alternative currency amount
2.desc: The amount is expressed in alternate currency.

3.name: Total message amount
3.desc: The total amount of the message.

4.name: Invoices total amount summary
4.desc: The summary of a number of invoices' total amounts.

5.name: Amount for Customs purposes
5.desc: Number of monetary units expressed in a specified currency for Customs purposes (see: 5004).

7.name: Financial transaction amount
7.desc: Amount refers to financial transaction.

8.name: Total(s) of deferred items
8.desc: To specify the total(s) of all deferred items from one reinsurance account.

9.name: Total(s) of open cash claims
9.desc: To specify the total(s) of all open cash claims from one reinsurance account.

10.name: Reinsurance account balance
10.desc: To specify the result(s) of the reinsurance account calculation.

11.name: Prepaid totals
11.desc: Totals of prepaid freight and charges.

12.name: Collect totals
12.desc: Totals of collect freight and charges.

14.name: Valuation amounts
14.desc: Code to indicate valuation amounts.

15.name: Prepayment amount
15.desc: The amount paid or to be paid before a business transaction occurs.

16.name: Alternative currency total amount
16.desc: The total amount expressed in an alternate currency.

17.name: Documentary credit amount
17.desc: Value expressed in monetary terms of the documentary credit.

18.name: Additional amounts covered: freight costs
18.desc: Freight costs are also covered under the documentary credit.

19.name: Additional amounts covered: insurance costs
19.desc: Insurance costs are also covered under the documentary credit.

20.name: Additional amounts covered: interest
20.desc: Interest on delayed or deferred payment is also covered under the documentary credit.

21.name: Additional amounts covered: inspection costs
21.desc: Goods inspection costs are also covered under the documentary credit.

22.name: Part of documentary credit amount
22.desc: Part of documentary credit subject to sight, deferred or acceptance payment when the documentary credit is available by mixed payment.

23.name: Amount of note
23.desc: Amount of debit or credit note.

24.name: Hash total
24.desc: Total sum of amounts specified for control purposes.

25.name: Cumulative total, this period
25.desc: Totals to date.

26.name: Period total
26.desc: Totals this measurement period.

27.name: Cumulative total, preceding period
27.desc: Total to the end of last measurement period.

28.name: Total balance credit risk covered
28.desc: The total balance of factored invoices which are covered for credit risk.

29.name: Labour costs
29.desc: Identifying costs related to labour resource.

30.name: Business credit amount
30.desc: Monetary amount(s) associated with business credit information.

1.name: Project
1.desc: Indicates that the index relates to the whole project.

2.name: Group
2.desc: Indicates that the index relates to a group of work items.

3.name: Alternative
3.desc: Indicates that the index is an alternative.

1.name: VAT, 1st value
1.desc: First VAT value if, for the same rate of VAT, there are 1 to 3 different ways to set this value.

2.name: VAT, 2nd value
2.desc: Second VAT value if, for the same rate of VAT, there are 2 or 3 different ways to set this value.

3.name: VAT, 3rd value
3.desc: Third VAT value if, for the same rate of VAT, there are 3 different ways to set this value.

4.name: Additional royalties (Customs)
4.desc: Royalties relating to the imported goods that the buyer must pay, either directly or indirectly, as a condition of sale, to the extent that they are not included in the price actually paid or payable.

5.name: Adjusted amount
5.desc: The amount specified is the adjusted amount.

6.name: Amount reference currency
6.desc: The owing amount in the currency used as reference in the transaction.

7.name: Agreed charge
7.desc: Charges which parties agreed upon.

8.name: Allowance or charge amount
8.desc: Total amount of allowance or charge.

9.name: Amount due/amount payable
9.desc: Amount to be paid.

10.name: Amount in charge currency
10.desc: Indicates that the amount is based on the charged currency.

11.name: Amount paid
11.desc: Amount that has been paid.

12.name: Amount remitted
12.desc: Amount which was remitted (see remittance advice).

13.name: Amount subject to total monetary discount
13.desc: The amount is subject to a total monetary discount.

14.name: Amount target currency
14.desc: The amount in the currency in which the amount is paid or has to be paid.

15.name: Average ledger balance
15.desc: The addition of the balance all accounts divided by the number of accounts.

16.name: Bank release fee
16.desc: The fee that a bank charges for releasing monies.

17.name: Batch total
17.desc: The complete quantity of anything needed for or made in one operation or lot.

18.name: Brokerage
18.desc: Fee charged by a broker for acting on behalf of a third party.

19.name: Buying commission
19.desc: Commission paid by the importer to his/her agent for the service of representing him/her in the purchase.

20.name: Data value on carrier media (Customs)
20.desc: Value of data contained on the carrier media (e.g. magnetic tape).

21.name: Cash discount
21.desc: Cash discount given by the seller to the buyer.

22.name: Consignment cash on delivery amount
22.desc: [5017] Monetary amount to be paid at time of delivery.

23.name: Charge amount
23.desc: [5034] The amount of money charged for the provision of a service or product.

24.name: Charge summary total
24.desc: Code to indicate the total charges relating to a consignment.

25.name: Charge/allowance basis
25.desc: The amount specified is the basis for calculation of charges/allowance.

26.name: Charges collect fee
26.desc: The fee a party charges for collecting charges.

27.name: Charges in destination currency
27.desc: Collect charges payable in the currency of the country of destination.

28.name: Collect charge summary total
28.desc: A summary total of collection charges.

29.name: Collect charges in destination currency
29.desc: Collect charges payable in the currency of the country of destination.

30.name: Collect freight charge including VAT
30.desc: This is the total amount that has to be collected from the consignee or other intermediary intervening party - Including VAT-.

31.name: Collect freight charge without VAT
31.desc: For legal accounting reasons the amount without VAT has to be announced, together with the amount of VAT.

32.name: Collect other charges due agent total
32.desc: The total of other charges that are due to the agent.

33.name: Collect taxes total
33.desc: [5294] The total amount of taxes to be collected.

34.name: Collected balance required
34.desc: A certain sum of money that must be kept in an account.

35.name: Container cost
35.desc: The cost of providing a container.

36.name: Converted amount
36.desc: The amount is converted from another currency.

37.name: Credit on consignment
37.desc: Credit deducted from the total invoice amount for the value of goods not included in a consignment but included in the invoice.

39.name: Invoice total amount
39.desc: [5214] Amount, debited by the seller and being the total of related article item amounts in a commercial invoice.

40.name: Goods item for customs declared value amount
40.desc: [5032] Amount declared for customs purposes of those goods in a consignment which are subject to the same customs procedure, and have the same tariff/statistical heading, country information and duty regime.

41.name: Assigned Customs value
41.desc: Goods value assigned by Customs.

42.name: Total cash payments received by factor
42.desc: Total allocated amount of cash payments received by a factor.

43.name: Consignment for customs total amount
43.desc: [5070] Total amount for customs purposes of all goods in a consignment, whether or not they are subject to the same customs procedure, and have the same tariff/statistical heading, country information and duty regime.

44.name: Goods item for carriage declared value amount
44.desc: [5036] Value, declared by the shipper or his agent solely for the purpose of varying the carrier's level of liability from that provided in the contract of carriage, in case of loss or damage to goods or delayed delivery.

45.name: Deductible after importation charges (Customs)
45.desc: Charges (e.g. construction, assembly, erection, maintenance or technical assistance) after importation, which are included in the total invoice price, that may be deducted to arrive at a Customs value.

46.name: Customs allowable deduction basis amount
46.desc: [5020] Allowable deductions from the price payable for calculating Customs value.

47.name: Delivery fee
47.desc: Fees incurred by delivery.

48.name: Deposit total
48.desc: The whole amount of money that one entrusts for safekeeping.

49.name: Development necessary for production of imported goods (Customs)
49.desc: Value of engineering, development, artwork, design work and plans and sketches carried out elsewhere than in the Customs territory and necessary for the production of the imported goods.

50.name: Disbursements
50.desc: [5416] Amount of disbursements to be collected by the carrier according to the order given by the shipper.

51.name: Disbursements fee
51.desc: Fee charged for the collection of disbursements.

52.name: Discount amount
52.desc: An amount deducted in advance, usually calculated based on a percentage.

53.name: Discount amount due
53.desc: The amount of discount that is due.

54.name: Distribution service fee
54.desc: The fee charged for the provision of distribution services.

55.name: Duty amount
55.desc: The amount of duty.

56.name: Duty/tax/fee basis amount
56.desc: The amount specified is the basis for duty/tax or fee.

57.name: Equivalent amount
57.desc: This amount is equivalent to the amount to be transferred, but in another currency.

58.name: Fee amount
58.desc: The amount of a fee.

59.name: Fees paid year to date
59.desc: Payments made for goods thus far.

60.name: Final (posted) amount
60.desc: The amount posted to an account, finally, after charges/allowances.

61.name: Float (e.g. "cash float")
61.desc: The status of funds in the process of collection.

62.name: Total payments on account received by a factor
62.desc: Total unallocated amount of payments received by a factor.

63.name: FOB value
63.desc: Identifies the value of the shipment free on board, named port of shipment (see FOB Incoterm of ICC).

64.name: Freight charge
64.desc: Amount to be paid for moving goods, by whatever means, from one place to another, inclusive discounts, allowances, rebates, adjustment factors and additional cost relating to freight costs (UN/ECE Recommendation no 23).

65.name: Total indirect amount payments made to a seller or his agent instead of to a factor
65.desc: Total indirect amount of payments made to a seller or his agent instead of to a factor.

66.name: Goods item total
66.desc: Net price x quantity for the line item.

67.name: Insurance amount
67.desc: (5486) Amount of insurance.

68.name: Insurance and transport charges (Customs)
68.desc: (5488)+(5290) Sum total of transport and insurance charges (CCC).

69.name: Insurance and transport charges incurred outside Customs territory
69.desc: (5488)+(5290) Insurance and transport charges incurred outside a Customs territory (or a Customs union).

70.name: Consignment to importation location insurance amount
70.desc: [5488] Amount of premium payable to the insurance company to insure the goods to the port or place of importation.

71.name: Insurance charges incurred outside of Customs territory
71.desc: (5488) Insurance charges incurred outside a Customs territory (or a Customs union).

72.name: Internal charges (Customs)
72.desc: Charges incurred within a Customs territory (or a Customs union).

73.name: Total amount of payments booked to the collateral account
73.desc: Total amount of payments booked to the collateral account.

74.name: Amount to be paid in advance
74.desc: Amount which is to be paid before goods are delivered or the service is rendered.

75.name: Registered capital
75.desc: Registered amount of equity of a company.

76.name: Investable balance
76.desc: To put left over money in something offering profitable returns.

77.name: Invoice line item amount
77.desc: [5068] Total sum charged with respect to a single line item of an invoice.

78.name: Landing charges
78.desc: The charges incurred in landing the goods into store in the country of importation, excluding Customs duties and taxes.

79.name: Total line items amount
79.desc: The sum of all the line item amounts.

80.name: Licence fees related to imported goods (Customs)
80.desc: Licence fees relating to the imported goods that the buyer must pay, either directly or indirectly, as a condition of sale, to the extent that they are not included in the price actually paid or payable.

81.name: Loading and handling cost
81.desc: Cost incurred by loading and handling.

82.name: Lock box total
82.desc: The complete amount of funds that customers mailed in to a specific location. Often times funds are sent to a post-office lock box in their city.

83.name: Lumpsum
83.desc: An agreed sum of money, which is paid in full at one time. This term is often used in connection with charter parties.

84.name: Material consumed in production of imported goods (Customs)
84.desc: Value of materials consumed in the production of the imported goods.

85.name: Maximum charge
85.desc: The maximum amount that can be charged for a service or product.

86.name: Message total monetary amount
86.desc: The total of all monetary amounts contained within the message.

87.name: Minimum charge
87.desc: The minimum amount that can be charged for a service or product.

88.name: National preference basis amount
88.desc: Amount giving the basis for national preference calculation.

89.name: Negative collected balance
89.desc: Having a quantity of less than zero in an account.

90.name: Negative ledger balance
90.desc: For an asset account, this would be when the account had a credit balance. For liability and owner's equity accounts, it would be when the account had a debit balance.

91.name: Net adjustment
91.desc: The end-of-the-period total amount which is left after recording appropriate adjusting entries.

92.name: Net fee position
92.desc: The payments left over after deductions or allowances have been made.

93.name: Net year to date excess (deficit)
93.desc: A negative amount of an item.

94.name: No amount of insurance
94.desc: No amount of insurance has been declared for a consignment.

95.name: No declared value for carriage
95.desc: No value has been declared for purposes of carriage.

96.name: No declared value for Customs
96.desc: No value has been declared for Customs purposes.

97.name: Quotation total amount
97.desc: [5210] Total monetary amount of a quotation.

98.name: Original amount
98.desc: Original amount, without charges, allowances or adjustment.

99.name: Other charges at destination
99.desc: (5436) Code to indicate charges levied at destination.

100.name: Other charges due agent
100.desc: Code to indicate that certain charges accrue to an agent.

101.name: Other charges due carrier
101.desc: (5322) Code to indicate that certain charges accrue to a carrier.

102.name: Other commissions
102.desc: Other commissions paid by the importer to his/her agent in relation to the goods being imported.

103.name: Other deductible charges
103.desc: Other charges deducted from the total invoice value.

104.name: Other transport charges
104.desc: (5290) Other charges paid for transport.

105.name: Other valuation charges (Customs)
105.desc: Other valuation charges which are payable by reason of the importation or sale of the goods in the Customs territory.

106.name: Packing cost
106.desc: Cost for packing concerning labour and/or material.

107.name: Transport equipment total for customs packing cost amount
107.desc: [5448] Costs incurred for all containers and coverings of whatever nature which are considered as being one for Customs purposes with the goods, and the cost of packing whether for labour or material.

108.name: Parts incorporated in imported goods (Customs)
108.desc: Materials, components, parts and similar items incorporated in the imported goods.

109.name: Payment discount amount
109.desc: Discount for paying early.

110.name: Pick-up fee
110.desc: Fee incurring if item has been or will be picked up.

111.name: Positive collected balance
111.desc: Having a quantity of greater than zero in an account.

112.name: Positive ledger balance
112.desc: For an asset account, this would be when the account had a debit balance. For liability and owner's equity accounts, it would be when the account had a credit balance.

113.name: Prepaid amount
113.desc: (5302) Amount which has been prepaid in advance.

114.name: Prepaid charge summary total
114.desc: Total of all prepaid charges.

115.name: Prepaid taxes total
115.desc: [5480] Total of all prepaid taxes.

116.name: Purchase amount
116.desc: The cost of buying goods or services.

117.name: Quantity discount
117.desc: Discount given for purchase of goods in bulk.

118.name: Quota value
118.desc: The monetary value of a quota.

119.name: Received amount
119.desc: The amount is what the bank received, and the one before charges/allowances.

120.name: Sales tax
120.desc: Identifies the amount of sales tax payable.

121.name: Shipment value in domestic currency
121.desc: The cost of transportation in domestic currency.

122.name: Specific amount payable
122.desc: Amount that the consignor agrees to be invoiced or to pay. This amount is part of the total charges applied to the consignment.

123.name: Goods item for statistics declared value amount
123.desc: [5218] Value declared for statistical purposes of those goods in a consignment which have the same statistical heading.

124.name: Tax amount
124.desc: Tax imposed by government or other official authority related to the weight/volume charge or valuation charge.

125.name: Taxable amount
125.desc: Amount on which a tax has to be applied.

126.name: To collect
126.desc: Amount that has to be collected.

127.name: Tools used in production of imported goods (Customs)
127.desc: Tools, dies, moulds and similar items used in the production of the imported goods.

128.name: Total amount
128.desc: The amount specified is the total amount.

129.name: Total amount subject to payment discount
129.desc: Part of the invoice amount which is subject to payment discount.

130.name: Total charge due
130.desc: Total amount of charges payable to the carrier.

131.name: Total charges/allowances
131.desc: The amount specified is the total of all charges/allowances.

132.name: Total collect charges
132.desc: [5398] Total charges to be collected.

133.name: Total collect charges at destination
133.desc: Total charges to be collected at destination.

445.name: Contract termination costs, estimated

449.name: Contract funds carried forward
449.desc: Amount of contract funds carried forward.

451.desc: The cost difference between budget at completion and estimate at completion.

452.name: Harmonized tariff schedule mixture, composite or set value

456.desc: Total debit related charges, included in debit amount.

457.desc: Total debit related allowances, included in debit amount.

469.desc: The variable contribution required to be paid by the insured person.

479.name: Schedule variance amount, cumulative to date

481.desc: Total credit-related allowances, not yet included in credit amount.

483.desc: Total credit-related allowances, already included in credit amount.

487.name: Total credit allowances, not included in credit amount, to be booked separately from credit amount

488.desc: Total charges which are not included in the transaction amount.

492.name: Debt financing allowance

493.name: Cancellation charge
493.desc: The amount charged because of a cancellation.

494.name: Incurred cost

497.desc: Total amount of goods and services excluding deposits for returnable goods.

498.name: Waiting time indemnity amount
498.desc: The monetary amount which is used as an indemnity for waiting.

499.name: Total net amount excluding Value Added Tax (VAT)
499.desc: The total net monetary amount excluding Value Added Tax (VAT).

500.desc: Interest to pay because payment date of contribution solidarity fund was exceeded.

501.name: Interest on late payment of employee's additional contribution to solidarity fund
501.desc: Interest to pay because payment date of employee's additional contribution is exceeded.

502.desc: Amount of disbursement on which tax must be applied.

504.name: Daily contribution

505.desc: The amount to be paid for the right to use a place, product or service.

506.name: Gross progress payment amount

507.name: Net progress payment amount
507.desc: Net monetary amount paid or to be paid at intervals.

508.name: Value of returned product
508.desc: Value of product returned by the customer.

509.name: Unit allowance amount
509.desc: The monetary amount of an allowance for each unit.

510.name: Remaining available overdraft
510.desc: The amount still available within the limit of the overdraft.

511.name: Unit charge amount
511.desc: The monetary amount of a charge for each unit.

512.name: Agreed monetary amount credit line limit
512.desc: Limit of the agreed monetary amount credit line.

514.name: Amount for pre-advising
514.desc: The amount is for pre-advising only.

515.name: Supplement
515.desc: The monetary amount represents the price of extra cost to pay in addition to the normal price.

516.name: Debit balance at closing date of accounting period under review
516.desc: The monetary amonunt is the debit balance at the closing date of the accounting period under review.

517.name: Credit balance at closing date of accounting period under review

518.name: Debit balance at starting date of accounting period under review

519.name: Credit balance at starting date of accounting period under review

521.name: Total of credit balances at closing date of accounting period under review

522.name: Total of debit balances at starting date of accounting period under review

523.name: Total of credit balances at starting date of accounting period under review
523.desc: The monetary amount is the total of credit balances at the starting date of the accounting period under review.

524.name: Cost accounting entry amount

525.name: Tariff
525.desc: The monetary amount represents the tariff.

526.name: Volume discount

527.name: Product range discount
527.desc: Discount for the purchase of a whole range of products.

528.name: Calculation basis excluding all taxes
528.desc: The amount used as the basis for calculation excludes all taxes.

529.name: Calculation basis which includes all taxes except VAT
529.desc: The amount, used as the basis for calculation, which includes all taxes except Value Added Tax (VAT).

531.name: Total returnable packaging rental amount
531.desc: Total rental amount for returnable packaging.

532.name: Total Marine Diesel Oil on board amount, on arrival

533.name: Total Marine Diesel Oil amount, loaded

534.name: Total Intermediate Fuel Oil on board amount, on arrival
534.desc: Total amount of Intermediate Fuel Oil (IFO) on board when vessel arrives in port.

535.name: Total Intermediate Fuel Oil amount, loaded
535.desc: Total amount of Intermediate Fuel Oil (IFO) taken on in the port.

536.name: Total Bunker C oil on board amount, on arrival
536.desc: Total amount of Bunker C, or Number 6 fuel oil on board when vessel arrives in port.

537.name: Total Bunker C oil amount, loaded

538.name: Government agency valuation commodity value
538.desc: The value of the commodity for the purposes of a government agency valuation.

539.name: Valuation adjustment amount
539.desc: [5514] Amount of adjustments to the valuation, e.g. price influence, royalties, assists, proceeds and commissions.

540.name: Damage allowance
540.desc: An allowance made in the value to the extent of the damage or defect.

541.name: Air transport freight cost
541.desc: Charges relating to the air transport of the goods which represent the freight charges only (i.e. not including the handling charges, agency fees etc.).

542.name: Unloading and handling cost
542.desc: Cost incurred by unloading and handling.

543.name: Commission and brokerage, except buying commission
543.desc: A monetary amount representing commissions and brokerage paid by or on behalf of the purchaser of goods excluding buying commission.

544.name: Taxable amount - excluding payment discount amount
544.desc: Indication of the total taxable amount before deducting payment discount amount.

545.name: Must buy product in multi-buy promotion value
545.desc: The value of a product which must be bought in order to qualify for a multi-buy promotion.

546.name: Additional voluntary contribution amount

547.name: Interest amount over employee's obligatory contribution

549.name: Amount to be compensated between social security entities
549.desc: Amount which needs to be compensated between social security entities.

550.name: Bank check amount
550.desc: Amount to be paid by bank check.

ZZZ.name: Mutually defined

1.name: Percentage
1.desc: The index value is represented in a proportion.

1.name: Normal

2.name: Special
2.desc: A contribution not usually made.

3.name: Reversal
3.desc: Reversing a previous contribution.

4.name: Back payment
4.desc: Payment is a period prior to the normal period.

5.name: Advanced payment
5.desc: Payment is for a period post the normal period.

6.name: Ceasing contributions
6.desc: Payment is irregular as contributions ceased from the specified date.

ZZZ.name: Mutually defined
ZZZ.desc: Mutually defined contribution qualifier.

1.name: Company

2.name: Company award
2.desc: Company payment as per an industry or similar industrial award agreement.

3.name: Company over-award
3.desc: Company payment which is higher than an industry or similar award agreement.

4.name: Lump sum
4.desc: Payment is in the form of a single payment.

5.name: Company additional
5.desc: Additional company payment.

6.name: Company voluntary
6.desc: A company payment which is paid on a voluntary basis.

7.name: Member voluntary
7.desc: A member payment which is paid on a voluntary basis.

8.name: Member additional
8.desc: Additional member payment.

9.name: Member individual
9.desc: Single payment by an individual member.

10.name: Group

11.name: Other
11.desc: Contribution type differs from any of the other coded values.

ZZZ.name: Mutually defined
ZZZ.desc: Mutually defined contribution type.

AAA.name: Calculation net
AAA.desc: The price stated is the net price including allowances/ charges. Allowances/charges may be stated for information only.

AAB.name: Calculation gross
AAB.desc: The price stated is the gross price to which allowances/ charges must be applied.

AAC.name: Allowances and charges not included, tax included
AAC.desc: The price does not include the allowances and charges, but includes the taxes.

AAD.name: Average selling price
AAD.desc: Average selling price of a product.

AAE.name: Information price, excluding allowances or charges, including taxes
AAE.desc: The price stated is for information purposes only and excludes all allowances and charges. Taxes however are included in the price.

AAF.name: Information price, excluding allowances or charges, and taxes
AAF.desc: The price stated is for information purposes only and excludes all allowances, charges and taxes.

AAG.name: Additive unit price component
AAG.desc: A code to indicate that the price described is an additive component of the total price.

AAH.name: Average purchase price
AAH.desc: Average purchase price of a product.

CAL.name: Calculation price
CAL.desc: The price stated is the price for the calculation of the line item amount.

INF.name: Information
INF.desc: The price is provided for information.

INV.name: Invoice price
INV.desc: Referenced price taken from an invoice.

ZZZ.name: Mutually defined
ZZZ.desc: A code assigned within a code list to be used on an interim basis and as defined among trading partners until a precise code can be assigned to the code list.

AAA.name: Petroleum tax
AAA.desc: A tax levied on the volume of petroleum being transacted.

AAB.name: Provisional countervailing duty cash
AAB.desc: Countervailing duty paid in cash prior to a formal finding of subsidization by Customs.

AAC.name: Provisional countervailing duty bond
AAC.desc: Countervailing duty paid by posting a bond during an investigation period prior to a formal decision on subsidization by Customs.

AAD.name: Tobacco tax
AAD.desc: A tax levied on tobacco products.

AAE.name: Energy fee
AAE.desc: General fee or tax for the use of energy.

AAF.name: Coffee tax
AAF.desc: A tax levied specifically on coffee products.

AAG.name: Harmonised sales tax, Canadian
AAG.desc: A harmonized sales tax consisting of a goods and service tax, a Canadian provincial sales tax and, as applicable, a Quebec sales tax which is recoverable.

AAH.name: Quebec sales tax
AAH.desc: A sales tax charged within the Canadian province of Quebec which is recoverable.

AAI.name: Canadian provincial sales tax
AAI.desc: A sales tax charged within Canadian provinces which is non-recoverable.

AAJ.name: Tax on replacement part
AAJ.desc: A tax levied on a replacement part, where the original part is returned.

AAK.name: Mineral oil tax
AAK.desc: Tax that is levied specifically on products containing mineral oil.

AAL.name: Special tax
AAL.desc: To indicate a special type of tax.

AAM.name: Insurance tax
AAM.desc: A tax levied specifically on insurances.

ADD.name: Anti-dumping duty
ADD.desc: Duty applied to goods ruled to have been dumped in an import market at a price lower than that in the exporter's domestic market.

BOL.name: Stamp duty (Imposta di Bollo)
BOL.desc: Tax required in Italy, which may be fixed or graduated in various circumstances (e.g. VAT exempt documents or bank receipts).

CAP.name: Agricultural levy
CAP.desc: Levy imposed on agricultural products where there is a difference between the selling price between trading countries.

CAR.name: Car tax
CAR.desc: A tax that is levied on the value of the automobile.

CST.name: Commodity specific tax
CST.desc: Tax related to a specified commodity, e.g. illuminants, salts.

CUD.name: Customs duty
CUD.desc: Duties laid down in the Customs tariff, to which goods are liable on entering or leaving the Customs territory (CCC).

CVD.name: Countervailing duty
CVD.desc: A duty on imported goods applied for compensate for subsidies granted to those goods in the exporting country.

ENV.name: Environmental tax
ENV.desc: Tax assessed for funding or assuring environmental protection or clean-up.

EC.name: Excise duty
EC.desc: Customs or fiscal authorities code to identify a specific or ad valorem levy on a specific commodity, applied either domestically or at time of importation.

EP.name: Agricultural export rebate
EP.desc: Monetary rebate given to the seller in certain circumstances when agricultural products are exported.

FET.name: Federal excise tax
FET.desc: Tax levied by the federal government on the manufacture of specific items.

GST.name: Goods and services tax
GST.desc: Tax levied on the final consumption of goods and services throughout the production and distribution chain.

IND.name: Individual tax
IND.desc: A tax levied based on an individual's ability to pay.

LAC.name: Business license fee
LAC.desc: Government assessed charge for permit to do business.

LDP.name: Light dues payable
LDP.desc: Fee levied on a vessel to pay for port navigation lights.

LOC.name: Local sales tax
LOC.desc: Assessment charges on sale of goods or services by city, borough country or other taxing authorities below state or provincial level.

LST.name: Lust tax
LST.desc: Tax imposed for clean-up of leaky underground storage tanks.

MCA.name: Monetary compensatory amount
MCA.desc: Levy on Common Agricultural Policy (European Union) goods used to compensate for fluctuating currencies between member states.

MCD.name: Miscellaneous cash deposit
MCD.desc: Duty paid and held on deposit, by Customs, during an investigation period prior to a final decision being made on any aspect related to imported goods (except valuation) by Customs.

PDB.name: Provisional duty bond
PDB.desc: Anti-dumping duty paid by posting a bond during an investigation period prior to a formal decision on dumping by Customs.

PDC.name: Provisional duty cash
PDC.desc: Anti-dumping duty paid in cash prior to a formal finding of dumping by Customs.

PRF.name: Preference duty
PRF.desc: Duties laid down in the Customs tariff, to which goods are liable on entering or leaving the Customs territory falling under a preferential regime such as Generalised System of Preferences (GSP).

SSS.name: Shifted social securities
SSS.desc: Social securities share of the invoice amount to be paid directly to the social securities collector.

STT.name: State/provincial sales tax
STT.desc: All applicable sale taxes by authorities at the state or provincial level, below national level.

SUP.name: Suspended duty
SUP.desc: Duty suspended or deferred from payment.

SUR.name: Surtax
SUR.desc: A tax or duty applied on and in addition to existing duties and taxes.

SWT.name: Shifted wage tax
SWT.desc: Wage tax share of the invoice amount to be paid directly to the tax collector(s office).

TAC.name: Alcohol mark tax
TAC.desc: A tax levied based on the type of alcohol being obtained.

TOT.name: Total
TOT.desc: The summary amount of all taxes.

TO.name: Turnover tax
TO.desc: Tax levied on the total sales/turnover of a corporation.

TTA.name: Tonnage taxes
TTA.desc: Tax levied based on the vessel's net tonnage.

VAD.name: Valuation deposit
VAD.desc: Duty paid and held on deposit, by Customs, during an investigation period prior to a formal decision on valuation of the goods being made.

VAT.name: Value added tax
VAT.desc: A tax on domestic or imported goods applied to the value added at each stage in the production/distribution cycle.

1.name: Handling commission
1.desc: Fee for the processing of documentary credit, collection and payment which are charged to the customer.

2.name: Amendment commission
2.desc: Fee for amendments in documentary credit and collection business (not extensions and increases of documentary credits).

3.name: Acceptance commission
3.desc: Fee for the acceptance of draft in documentary credit and collection business which are drawn on us (also to be seen as a kind of 'guarantee commission').

4.name: Commission for obtaining acceptance
4.desc: Fee for obtaining an acceptance under collections on the basis of 'documents against acceptance'.

5.name: Commission on delivery
5.desc: Fee for delivery of documents without corresponding payment.

6.name: Advising commission
6.desc: Fee for advising documentary credits (charged also in case of confirmed credits).

7.name: Confirmation commission
7.desc: Fee for confirmation of credit.

8.name: Deferred payment commission
8.desc: Fee for the deferred payment period under documentary credits confirmed by bank. This fee are charges for the period from presentation of the document until due date of payment.

9.name: Commission for taking up documents
9.desc: Fee charged to the foreign bank for the processing of documentary credit.

10.name: Opening commission
10.desc: Fee for opening revocable documentary credit.

11.name: Fee for payment under reserve
11.desc: Fee charged to the customer for discrepancies in credit documents in the case of which the bank have to stipulate payment under reserve.

12.name: Discrepancy fee
12.desc: Fee charged to the foreign bank for discrepancies in credit documents.

13.name: Domicilation commission
13.desc: Fee for the domicilation of bills with the bank.

14.name: Commission for release of goods
14.desc: Commission for the release of goods sent to the bank.

15.name: Collection commission
15.desc: Fee for settling collections on the basis of 'documents against payments'.

16.name: Negotiation commission
16.desc: Fee for the purchase of documents under sight credit for the first ten days.

17.name: Return commission
17.desc: Fee for cheques, bills and collections returned unpaid and/or recalled.

18.name: B/L splitting charges
18.desc: Fee for the splitting of bills of lading.

19.name: Trust commission
19.desc: Fee for the handling on a fiduciary basis of imported goods that have been warehoused.

20.name: Transfer commission
20.desc: Fee for the transfer of transferable documentary credits.

21.name: Commission for opening irrevocable documentary credits
21.desc: Fee for opening irrevocable documentary credits. This fee is a kind of 'Guarantee commission' as compensation for the commitment into which the bank have entered on the customers behalf; similar to confirmation commission, acceptance commission.

22.name: Pre-advice commission
22.desc: Fee for the pre-advice of a documentary credit.

23.name: Supervisory commission
23.desc: Fee for the supervising unconfirmed documentary credits with a deferred payment period.

24.name: Model charges
24.desc: Fee for decoding telex messages.

25.name: Risk commission
25.desc: Commission in addition to the confirmation commission for documentary credits from sensitive countries.

26.name: Guarantee commission
26.desc: Commission for drawing up guaranties.

27.name: Reimbursement commission
27.desc: Fee for reimbursement of, for example, documentary credits.

28.name: Stamp duty
28.desc: Tax payable on bills in accordance with national bill of exchange legislation.

29.name: Brokerage
29.desc: Brokers commission arising, in trade with foreign currencies.

30.name: Bank charges
30.desc: Charges deducted/claimed by other banks involved in the transaction.

31.name: Bank charges information
31.desc: Charges not included in the total charge amount i.e. the charges are for information only.

32.name: Courier fee
32.desc: Fee for use of courier service.

33.name: Phone fee
33.desc: Fee for use of phone.

34.name: Postage fee
34.desc: Fee for postage.

35.name: S.W.I.F.T. fee
35.desc: Fee for use of S.W.I.F.T.

36.name: Telex fee
36.desc: Fee for telex.

37.name: Penalty for late delivery of documents
37.desc: Penalty imposed when documents are delivered late.

38.name: Penalty for late delivery of valuation of works

39.name: Penalty for execution of works behind schedule
39.desc: Penalty imposed when the execution of works is behind schedule.

46.name: Contractual retention

47.name: Other retentions
47.desc: Retention charge not otherwise specified.

49.desc: Cost of using money.

51.name: Charge per unused credit cover
51.desc: Unit charge per unused credit cover.

52.name: Minimum commission
52.desc: Minimum commission charge.

53.name: Factoring commission
53.desc: Commission charged for factoring services.

54.name: Chamber of commerce charge
54.desc: Identifies the charges from the chamber of commerce.

55.name: Transfer charges

56.desc: Charges for repatriation.

72.name: Technical modification costs

73.name: Job-order production costs

74.name: Off-premises costs

1.name: All charges
1.desc: All amounts calculated by the carrier in accordance with tariffs or in case of special events during the voyage (e.g. Rail - freights costs - additional costs).

2.name: Additional charges
2.desc: Charges calculated by the carrier for specific events like re-weighting, re-loading, unexpected operations, services required during the voyage, etc.

3.desc: Transport charges plus Additional charges (e.g. for re- loading, re-weighting or unexpected operations) that must be precised in the payment conditions by the consignor (other charges must be taken in account by the consignee).

4.desc: The basic freight payable on the cargo as per tariff.

5.name: Destination haulage charges
5.desc: Haulage charges for transporting goods to the destination.

6.name: Disbursement
6.desc: Sums paid out by ship's agent at a port and recovered from the carrier.

7.name: Destination port charges
7.desc: Charges payable at the port of destination.

8.name: Miscellaneous charges
8.desc: Miscellaneous charges not otherwise categorized.

9.name: Transport charges up to a specified location
9.desc: Transport charges to be paid by a specified party for a part of a voyage, i.e. up to a specified location.

10.name: Origin port charges
10.desc: Charges payable at the port of origin.

11.name: Origin haulage charges
11.desc: Haulage charges for the pickup of goods at origin.

12.name: Other charges
12.desc: Unspecified charges.

13.name: Specific amount payable
13.desc: Amount that the consignor agrees to be invoiced or to pay. This amount is part of the total charges applied to the consignment.

14.name: Transport costs (carriage charges)
14.desc: Monetary amount calculated on the basis of the transport tariffs or contract eventually including charges or other costs.

15.name: All costs up to a specified location
15.desc: All amounts to be paid by the consignor for a part of the voyage, i.e. up to a location that must be precised. (The remaining part of the voyage to be paid by the consignee) The amounts are calculated by the carrier in accordance with tariffs or in case of special events during the voyage (e.g. rail - freight costs - additional costs).

16.desc: Code to indicate weight/valuation charges to be either wholly prepaid or wholly collect.

17.name: All costs

21.name: Supply of non-categorised documentation in paper form
21.desc: Charges payable for the supply of one or more documents in paper form that are not otherwise categorised.

23.name: Supply of customs formalities, transit
23.desc: Charges payable for the supply of transit customs formalities.

24.name: Supply of customs formalities, import

16.desc: Code specifying the interest percentage.

138.name: Valuation based on price paid or payable without adjustments
138.desc: The valuation is to be based on the total payment made or to be made by the buyer to, or for the benefit of the seller for the imported goods, and includes all payments made as a condition of sale of the imported goods by the buyer to the seller, or by the buyer to a third party to satisfy an obligation of the seller.

139.name: Valuation based on price paid or payable with adjustments
139.desc: The valuation is to be based on the total payment made or to be made by the buyer to, or for the benefit of the seller for the imported goods, and includes all payments made as a condition of sale of the imported goods by the buyer to the seller, or by the buyer to a third party to satisfy an obligation of the seller but requiring applicable adjustments.

140.name: Valuation based on transaction value of identical goods
140.desc: Valuation is to be based on the transaction value of identical goods.

141.name: Valuation based on transaction value of similar goods
141.desc: The valuation is to be based on transaction value of similar goods that is goods closely resembling the goods being valued in terms of component materials and characteristics or goods which are capable of performing the same functions and are commercially interchangeable with the goods being valued or goods which are produced in the same country as and by the producer of the goods being valued.

142.name: Valuation based on deductive value of imported goods
142.desc: Valuation is to be based on the unit price at which the imported goods or identical or similar goods are sold to an unrelated buyer in the greatest aggregate quantity in the country of importation.

143.name: Valuation based on computed value
143.desc: The valuation is to be based on the cost of production of the goods being valued, plus an amount for profit and general expenses usually reflected in sales from the country of exportation to the country of importation of goods of the same class or kind.

144.name: Valuation based on the residual method
144.desc: Valuation is to be based on reasonable means consistent with the principles and general provisions of the Agreement, Article VII GATT and on the basis of available data (fallback method).

145.name: Valuation adjustment for price influence
145.desc: Valuation to be adjusted for price influence on account of relationship between buyer and seller.

146.name: Valuation adjustment for royalties
146.desc: Valuation to be adjusted for royalties and licence fees related to the goods being valued that the buyer must pay, either directly or indirectly, as a condition of sale of the goods being valued, to the extent that such royalties and fees are not included in the price actually paid or payable.

147.name: Valuation adjustment for assists
147.desc: Valuation to be adjusted for goods and services, where supplied directly or indirectly by the buyer free of charge or at reduced cost for use in connection with the production and sale for export of imported goods, to the extent that such value has not been included in the price actually paid or payable. E.g. tools, dies, moulds, design work, engineering services.

148.name: Valuation adjustments for proceeds
148.desc: Value to be adjusted on the basis of value of any part of the proceeds of any subsequent resale, disposal or use of the imported goods that accrues, directly or indirectly, to the seller.

149.name: Valuation adjustments for commissions
149.desc: Valuation to be adjusted for commissions and brokerage, except buying commissions as per Article 8 WTO Valuation Agreement.

150.name: Valuation adjustments for insurance
150.desc: Valuation to be adjusted for insurance charges.

151.name: Valuation adjustment for freight charges
151.desc: Value to be adjusted for the cost of transport of the imported goods to the place of importation.

152.name: Valuation adjustment for handling charges
152.desc: Value to be adjusted for the costs of loading, unloading and handling charges associated with the delivery of the imported goods at the place of importation.

153.name: Valuation adjustments for allowances
153.desc: Valuation to be adjusted for allowances.

154.name: Valuation adjustments for other buyer-incurred costs
154.desc: Valuation to be adjusted for other reasons to the extent they are incurred by the buyer but are not included in the price actually paid or payable for the imported goods, such as the cost of containers which are treated as being one for customs purposes with the goods in question, the cost of packing whether for labour or materials, materials, components, parts and similar items incorporated in the imported goods.

155.name: Mutually defined valuation adjustment
155.desc: Valuation adjustments as mutually agreed between the interchanging parties.
