1.name: More than one quarter volume available
1.desc: Indicates that there is more than a quarter of the volume available.

2.name: More than half volume available
2.desc: Indicates that there is more than a half of the volume available.

3.name: More than three quarters volume available
3.desc: Indicates that there is more than three quarters of the volume available.

4.name: Empty
4.desc: Indicates that the object is empty.

5.name: Full
5.desc: Indicates that the object is full.

6.name: No volume available
6.desc: Indicates that there is no space available in the object.

7.name: Full, mixed consignment
7.desc: Indicates that the equipment is fully loaded, and includes a number LCL (Less Than Container Load) consignments.

8.name: Full, single consignment
8.desc: Indicates that the container is fully loaded with a single FCL (Full Container Load) consignment.

9.name: Part load
9.desc: Container represents part of a consignment declared on a single Customs declaration (i.e. the Customs declaration covers more than one container).

10.name: Part load mixed consignments
10.desc: Container represents part of the consignment declared on a single Customs declaration with the remainder being in other containers. Other goods, related to other declarations, are also in the container.

11.name: Single invoiced load
11.desc: Merchandise within a container/package covered by a single invoice.

12.name: Multi invoiced load
12.desc: Merchandise within a container/package covered by more than one invoice.

13.name: Full load, multiple bills
13.desc: A container representing a consignment of goods for one consignee with multiple bill of lading numbers.

1.name: Box tricycle
1.desc: Tricycle with a basket for delivering goods.

1.name: Continental
1.desc: The equipment is or will be moving across a continent on an intermodal or multimodal basis.

2.name: Export
2.desc: Transport equipment to be exported on a marine vessel.

3.name: Import
3.desc: Transport equipment to be imported on a marine vessel.

4.name: Remain on board
4.desc: Transport equipment arriving on a marine vessel is to remain on board.

5.name: Shifter
5.desc: Transport equipment is to be shifted from one stowage location on a marine vessel to another on the same vessel.

6.name: Transhipment
6.desc: Transport equipment is to be transferred from one marine vessel to another.

7.name: Shortlanded
7.desc: Transport equipment notified to arrive which did not arrive on the means of transport.

8.name: Overlanded
8.desc: Transport equipment not notified to arrive but which did arrive on the means of transport.

9.name: Domestic
9.desc: Transport equipment is used in domestic service.

10.name: Positioning
10.desc: Equipment is being transported for positioning purposes.

11.name: Delivery
11.desc: Equipment is being delivered.

12.name: Redelivery
12.desc: Equipment is being redelivered.

13.name: Repair
13.desc: The equipment is for repair.

14.name: Reloader
14.desc: Transport equipment to be discharged and subsequently reloaded on the same means of transport but in a different stowage location.

15.name: Returned
15.desc: The equipment is returned.

16.name: Dropped off
16.desc: The equipment is dropped off.

17.name: Cross terminal transshipment
17.desc: The transport equipment that is unloaded will be loaded in another vessel at another terminal in the same port.

18.name: Booking confirmed
18.desc: Notification of the confirmation of booking of a transport equipment.

19.name: Inspected at terminal gate
19.desc: Notification that a transport equipment has undergone a terminal gate inspection.

20.name: Arrived at offloading location
20.desc: Notification that a transport equipment arrived at the offloading location.

21.name: Departed from loading location.
21.desc: Notification that a transport equipment departed from the loading location.

22.name: Loaded
22.desc: Notification that a transport equipment has been loaded.

23.name: Unloaded
23.desc: Notification that a transport equipment has been unloaded.

24.name: Intra-terminal movement
24.desc: Notification that a transport equipment has been subject to an intra-terminal movement.

25.name: Stuffing ordered
25.desc: Notification that a transport equipment has been ordered to be stuffed.

26.name: Stripping ordered
26.desc: Notification that a transport equipment has been ordered to be stripped.

27.name: Stuffing confirmed
27.desc: Notification that a transport equipment has been confirmed as stuffed.

28.name: Stripping confirmed
28.desc: Notification that a transport equipment has been confirmed as stripped.

29.name: Sent for heavy repair
29.desc: Notification that a transport equipment has been sent for heavy repair.

30.name: Replaced
30.desc: One piece of transport equipment replaced by another during operations.

31.name: Empty
31.desc: Empty transport equipment.

32.name: Full
32.desc: Full transport equipment.

ADR.name: European agreement on the international carriage of dangerous goods on road (ADR)
ADR.desc: European agreement on the international carriage of dangerous goods on road. ADR is the abbreviation of "Accord europeen relatif au transport international des marchandises dangereuses par route".

ADS.name: NDR European agreement for the transport of dangerous goods on the river Rhine
ADS.desc: European agreement giving regulations for the transport of dangerous goods on the river Rhine, officially known as: "Accord europeen relatif au transport international des marchandises dangereuses par navigation sur le Rhin.".

ADT.name: CA, Transport Canada's dangerous goods requirements
ADT.desc: Canadian transport of dangerous goods requirements as published by Transport Canada in the Canadian Gazette, Part II.

ADU.name: JP, Japanese maritime safety agency dangerous goods regulation code
ADU.desc: Regulation regarding the handling of dangerous goods on vessels issued by Japanese maritime safety agency.

ADV.name: MARPOL 73/78
ADV.desc: International Convention for the Prevention of Pollution from Ships, 1973, as modified by the Protocol of 1978 relating.

ADW.name: GHS regulation
ADW.desc: The United Nations Globally Harmonized System of Classification and Labelling of Chemicals.

AD.name: Transport emergency (TREM) card
AD.desc: A card providing details on procedures for emergencies during transportation according to ADR.

AGS.name: DE, ADR and GGVS combined regulations for combined transport
AGS.desc: Combined German and European regulations for the transportation of dangerous goods on German and other European roads. ADR means: Accord Europeen relatif au Transport international des marchandises Dangereuses par Route. GGVS means: Gefahrgutverordnung Strasse.

ANR.name: ADNR, Autorisation de transport de matieres Dangereuses pour la Navigation sur le Rhin
ANR.desc: Regulations for dangerous goods transportation on the Rhine.

ARD.name: DE, ARD and RID - Combined regulations for combined transport
ARD.desc: Combined European regulations for the combined transportation of dangerous goods on roads and rails. ARD means: Autorisation de transport par Route de matieres dangereuses. RID means: Reglement International concernant le transport des marchandises Dangereuses par chemin de fer.

CFR.name: US, 49 Code of federal regulations
CFR.desc: United States federal regulations issued by the US Department of transportation covering the domestic transportation of dangerous goods by truck, rail, water and air.

COM.name: DE, ADR, RID, GGVS and GGVE - Combined regulations for combined transport
COM.desc: Combined German and European regulations for the combined transportation of dangerous goods on German and other European roads and rails. ADR means: Accord Europeen relatif au transport international des marchandises Dangereuse par Route. RID means: Reglement International concernant le transport des marchandises Dangereuses par chemin de fer. GGVS means: Gefahrgutverordnung Strasse. GGVE means: Gefahrgutverordnung Eisenbahn.

GVE.name: DE, GGVE (Gefahrgutverordnung Eisenbahn)
GVE.desc: German regulation for the transportation of dangerous goods on rail.

GVS.name: DE, GGVS (Gefahrgutverordnung Strasse)
GVS.desc: German regulation for the transportation of dangerous goods on road.

ICA.name: IATA ICAO
ICA.desc: Regulations covering the international transportation of dangerous goods issued by the International Air Transport Association and the International Civil Aviation Organization.

IMD.name: IMO IMDG code
IMD.desc: Regulations regarding the transportation of dangerous goods on ocean-going vessels issued by the International Maritime Organization.

RGE.name: DE, RID and GGVE, Combined regulations for combined transport on rails
RGE.desc: Combined German and European regulations for the transportation of dangerous goods on German and other European rails. RID means: Reglement International concernant le transport des marchandises Dangereuses par chemin de fer. GGVE means: Gefahrgutverordnung Eisenbahn.

RID.name: Railroad dangerous goods book (RID)
RID.desc: International regulations concerning the international carriage of dangerous goods by rail. RID is the abbreviation of "Reglement International concernant le transport des marchandises Dangereuses par chemin de fer".

UI.name: UK IMO book
UI.desc: The United Kingdom (UK) version of the International Maritime Organisation (IMO) book on dangerous goods.

ZZZ.name: Mutually defined
ZZZ.desc: Additional and/or other information for the transportation of dangerous goods which are mutually defined.

1.name: Transport for the owner's account
1.desc: The owner of the transported goods is also the owner of the means of transport or rented it for this transport.

2.name: Transport for another account
2.desc: The owner of the transported goods does not own the means of transport or has not rented it for this transport.

3.name: Private transport
3.desc: A code indicating privately owned transport.

1.name: Export
1.desc: The transport movement is to export the goods from the country.

2.name: Import
2.desc: The transport movement is to import the goods into the country.

3.name: Transit
3.desc: The cargo is moving in transit through a country and will not become part of the commerce of that country.

4.name: Relay
4.desc: The cargo is being moved by more than one transport means in succession under the responsibility of the same carrier.

5.name: Transshipment
5.desc: The cargo is being moved by more than one transport means in succession.

1.name: Breakbulk
1.desc: Defines the movement of general cargo not carried in ISO standard containers.

2.name: LCL/LCL
2.desc: Defines the movement of cargo packed in and unpacked from containers by the carrier on behalf of the shipper/consignee. 'LCL' means Less than Container Load.

3.name: FCL/FCL
3.desc: Defines the movement of cargo packed by the shipper or shipper's agent and unpacked by the consignee or consignee's agent. 'FCL' means Full Container Load.

4.name: FCL/LCL
4.desc: Defines the movement of cargo packed by the shipper or shipper's agent and unpacked by the carrier. 'FCL' means Full Container Load. 'LCL' means Less than Container Load.

5.name: LCL/FCL
5.desc: Defines the movement of cargo packed by the carrier and unpacked by the consignee or consignee's agent. 'LCL' means Less than Container Load. 'FCL' means Full Load.

6.name: Consolidation
6.desc: A movement of multiple shipments to a single destination.

7.name: Parcel post
7.desc: A movement of material by parcel post.

8.name: Expedited truck
8.desc: A movement of material by expedited truck.

9.name: Consignor determined means
9.desc: A movement of material by the means determined by the consignor.

10.name: Private parcel service
10.desc: A movement of material by a private parcel service.

11.name: House to house
11.desc: Cargo packed in a unit by the shipper at point of origin and unpacked by consignee at final destination.

12.name: House to terminal
12.desc: Cargo packed in a unit by the shipper at point of origin and unpacked at the carrier's inland facility between the ship's point of discharge and the final destination.

13.name: House to pier
13.desc: Cargo packed in a unit by the shipper at point of origin and unpacked by carrier at ship's point of discharge (pier).

14.name: Air charter
14.desc: A movement of material by chartered aircraft.

15.name: Air express
15.desc: A movement of material by air express service.

16.name: Geographic grouped transport
16.desc: A movement of material from multiple origins to a single destination utilizing a single carrier and a single freight bill.

17.name: Less than truck load
17.desc: A movement of material on a truck that is not full.

18.name: Pooled piggyback
18.desc: A movement of material by a trailer on a railcar.

19.name: Consignee transportation provided
19.desc: A movement of material transported by the consignee.

20.name: Rail
20.desc: A movement of material to the consignee via rail.

21.name: Terminal to house
21.desc: Cargo packed in a unit at a carrier's inland facility between point of origin and the ship's point of loading and unpacked by consignee at the final destination.

22.name: Terminal to terminal
22.desc: Cargo packed in a unit at a carrier's inland facility between point of origin and the ship's point of loading and unpacked at a carrier's inland facility between ship's point of discharge and final destination.

23.name: Terminal to pier
23.desc: Cargo packed in a unit at a carrier's inland facility between point of origin and ship's point of loading and unpacked by carrier at ship's point of discharge (pier).

31.name: Pier to house
31.desc: Cargo packed in a unit at ship's point of loading and unpacked by consignee at final destination.

32.name: Pier to terminal
32.desc: Cargo packed in a unit at ship's point of loading and unpacked at a carrier's inland facility between ship's point of discharge and final destination.

33.name: Pier to pier
33.desc: Cargo packed in a unit at ship's point of loading and unpacked by carrier at ship's point of discharge (pier).

41.name: Station to station
41.desc: The consignment is moving from one container freight station to another container freight station.

42.name: House to warehouse
42.desc: The consignment is moving from the premises of the shipper to a warehouse.

43.name: Warehouse to house
43.desc: The consignment is moving from a warehouse to the premises of the consignee.

44.name: Station to house
44.desc: The cargo is moving from a container freight station to the premises of the consignee.

45.name: Geographic grouped transport, multiple origins, multiple destinations
45.desc: A movement of material from multiple origins to multiple destinations using a single carrier and a single freight bill.

46.name: Geographic grouped transport, multiple origins, single destination
46.desc: A movement of material from multiple origins to a single destination utilizing a single carrier and a single freight bill.

47.name: Geographic receiving
47.desc: A collection of shipments that involve a single origin, multiple destinations, and a single trailer, and are paid under a single freight bill.

1.name: Great danger
1.desc: Packaging meeting criteria to pack hazardous materials with great danger. Group I according to IATA/IMDG/ADR/RID regulations.

2.name: Medium danger
2.desc: Packaging meeting criteria to pack hazardous materials with medium danger. Group II according to IATA/IDMG/ADR/RID regulations.

3.name: Minor danger
3.desc: Packaging meeting criteria to pack hazardous materials with minor danger. Group III according to IATA/IDMG/ADR/RID regulations.

4.name: Not assigned
4.desc: No packaging danger level has been assigned.

1.name: Carrier
1.desc: Haulage arranged by carrier.

2.name: Merchant
2.desc: Haulage arranged by merchant (shipper, consignee, or their agent).

1.name: Loaded with empty 4-block for blocking purposes
1.desc: Loaded with empty 4-block for blocking purposes.

2.name: Empty container with dunnage
2.desc: The container is, has been, or will be returned with dunnage only.

3.name: Empty container
3.desc: The container is, has been, or will be returned empty.

4.name: Loaded with production material
4.desc: The package is, has been, or will be returned loaded with production material.

6.name: Obsolete material
6.desc: The package is, has been, or will be returned loaded with obsolete material.

7.name: Loaded with excess returned production material
7.desc: The package is, has been, or will be returned loaded with excess production material.

8.name: Loaded with rejected material
8.desc: The package is, has been, or will be returned loaded with rejected material.

10.name: Loaded with returned processed material
10.desc: The package is, has been, or will be returned loaded with processed material.

11.name: Empty container, folded
11.desc: An empty container, which is folded.

1.name: Paid by customer
1.desc: The freight charges involved with returning of the packaging are to be paid by the customer.

2.name: Free
2.desc: There is no charge for the freight of returning the packaging.

3.name: Paid by supplier
3.desc: The responsibility for the freight for returning the packaging is to be paid by the supplier.

ZZZ.name: Mutually defined
ZZZ.desc: A code assigned within a code list to be used on an interim basis and as defined among trading partners until a precise code can be assigned to the code list.

A.name: Special rail car order, schedule increase forecast change
A.desc: The reason for the excess transportation is due to special rail car order, schedule increase forecast change.

B.name: Engineering change or late release
B.desc: The reason for the excess transportation is due to engineering change or late release.

C.name: Specification (schedule) error/overbuilding
C.desc: The reason for the excess transportation is due to special rail car order, schedule increase forecast change specification (schedule) error/overbuilding.

D.name: Shipment tracing delay
D.desc: The reason for the excess transportation is due to shipment tracing delay.

E.name: Plant inventory loss
E.desc: The reason for the excess transportation is due to plant inventory loss.

F.name: Building ahead of schedule
F.desc: The reason for the excess transportation is due to building ahead of schedule.

G.name: Vendor behind schedule
G.desc: The reason for the excess transportation is due to vendor behind schedule.

H.name: Failed to include in last shipment
H.desc: The reason for the excess transportation is due to failure to include costs in last shipment.

I.name: Carrier loss claim
I.desc: The reason for the excess transportation is due to carrier loss claim.

J.name: Transportation failure
J.desc: The reason for the excess transportation is due to transportation failure.

K.name: Insufficient weight for carload
K.desc: The reason for the excess transportation is due to insufficient weight for carload.

L.name: Reject or discrepancy (material rejected in prior shipment)
L.desc: The reason for the excess transportation is due to reject or discrepancy.

M.name: Transportation delay
M.desc: The reason for the excess transportation is due to transportation delay.

N.name: Lack of railcar or railroad equipment
N.desc: The reason for the excess transportation is due to lack of railcar of railroad equipment.

P.name: Releasing error
P.desc: The reason for the excess transportation is due to releasing error.

R.name: Record error or cate reported discrepancy report
R.desc: The reason for the excess transportation is due to record error or cate reported discrepancy report.

T.name: Common or peculiar part schedule increase
T.desc: The reason for the excess transportation is due to common or peculiar part schedule increase.

U.name: Alternative supplier shipping for responsible supplier
U.desc: The reason for the excess transportation is due to alternative supplier shipping for responsible supplier.

V.name: Direct schedule or locally controlled
V.desc: The reason for the excess transportation is due to direct schedule or locally controlled.

W.name: Purchasing waiver approval Authorization code to be determined
W.desc: The reason for the excess transportation is due to purchasing waiver approved. The reason for the excess transportation is due to authorization code to be determined.

Y.name: Pilot material
Y.desc: The reason for the excess transportation is due to pilot material.

ZZZ.name: Mutually defined
ZZZ.desc: A code assigned within a code list to be used on an interim basis and as defined among trading partners until a precise code can be assigned to the code list.

B.name: Material release issuer
B.desc: The responsibility for excess transportation is with the material release issuer.

S.name: Supplier authority Responsibility to be determined
S.desc: The responsibility for excess transportation is with the supplier authority. The responsibility for the excess transportation is to be determined.

ZZZ.name: Mutually defined
ZZZ.desc: A code assigned within a code list to be used on an interim basis and as defined among trading partners until a precise code can be assigned to the code list.

1.name: Primary
1.desc: Main employment.

2.name: Secondary
2.desc: Secondary employment.

3.name: Tertiary
3.desc: Tertiary employment.

4.name: Profession
4.desc: To specify a profession.

1.name: Address ex delivery area
1.desc: The address for delivery is outside the area of the carrier/transporter.

2.name: After transport departed
2.desc: The goods/consignments/equipment arrived after the means of transport has departed.

3.name: Agent refusal
3.desc: The agent of the customer refused to accept delivery.

4.name: Altered seals
4.desc: The seals on the equipment have been changed from those notified.

5.name: Appointment scheduled
5.desc: An arrangement has been made to deliver at a specific time.

6.name: Attempt unsuccessful
6.desc: An unsuccessful attempt has been made to deliver the goods/consignments/equipment.

7.name: Business closed
7.desc: The goods/consignments/equipment could not be delivered/collected as the business was closed.

8.name: Changed schedule
8.desc: The goods/consignments/equipment cannot/will not be delivered/collected at the arranged time because of a change of schedule.

9.name: Complementary address needed
9.desc: A further address is needed to effect delivery/collection of the goods/consignments/equipment.

10.name: Computer system down
10.desc: The computer system is inoperative.

11.name: Credit approval requested
11.desc: The consignee requests delivery on a credit base.

12.name: Customer arrangements
12.desc: Goods/consignments/equipment require delivery arrangements by the customer.

13.name: Customs refusal
13.desc: The Customs authorities have refused to clear the goods/consignments/equipment.

14.name: Damaged
14.desc: The goods/consignments/equipment have been damaged.

15.name: Delivery at specific requested dates/times/periods
15.desc: Delivery of the goods/consignments/equipment is requested at specific dates/times/periods.

16.name: Destination incorrect
16.desc: The goods/consignments/equipment have been sent to wrong destination.

17.name: Departure delay
17.desc: The transport has been delayed in departing on the arranged transport action.

18.name: Derailment
18.desc: The train carrying the goods/consignments/equipment has been derailed.

19.name: Discrepancy
19.desc: There is a discrepancy between the details of goods/ equipment previously provided and the actual situation.

20.name: Dock strike
20.desc: The goods/consignments/equipment cannot be delivered/collected due to a dock strike.

21.name: Due to customer
21.desc: An action in the transport chain has been affected due to action of the customer.

22.name: Empty
22.desc: The package/equipment is found to be empty.

23.name: Equipment failure
23.desc: Delivery/collection could not be effected due to equipment failure.

24.name: Examination required by relevant authority
24.desc: An examination of the goods/equipment has been ordered by the relevant authority.

25.name: Export restrictions
25.desc: The goods/consignments/equipment have been prohibited from export pending further investigation.

26.name: Frustrated export
26.desc: Attempts to export the goods/consignments/equipment have been unsuccessful.

27.name: Goods units missing
27.desc: The tally of goods/consignments/equipment does not match the quantity as per advice. Result: less than advised.

28.name: Import restrictions
28.desc: The goods/consignments/equipment need import checks and tests pending being released for importation.

29.name: Incorrect pick information
29.desc: The goods/consignments/equipment were not collected due to incorrect pick information.

30.name: Incorrect address
30.desc: The address given for the action was incorrect.

31.name: Industrial dispute
31.desc: The action was frustrated by an industrial dispute.

32.name: Instructions awaited
32.desc: Further instructions are required.

33.name: Lost goods/consignments/equipment
33.desc: The goods/consignments/equipment have been lost in the course of a movement along the transport chain.

34.name: Means of transport damaged
34.desc: The means of transport on which the goods/consignments/equipment were being (were to be) moved has been damaged.

35.name: Mechanical breakdown
35.desc: There has been a mechanical breakdown of the means of transport/equipment on which the goods/consignments/equipment was being (was to be) moved.

36.name: Mechanical inspection
36.desc: A mechanical inspection of the means of transport/ equipment on which the goods/consignments/equipment were being (were to be) moved, is required.

37.name: Missing and/or incorrect documents
37.desc: The goods/consignments/equipment require complete and correct documentation.

38.name: New delivery arrangements
38.desc: Alternative delivery arrangements advised by consignee after failed delivery.

39.name: No recipient contact information
39.desc: No information available concerning the responsible person at delivery address.

40.name: Not identified
40.desc: The goods/consignments/equipment expected to be located and identified in the transport chain cannot be identified.

41.name: Not loaded
